Description: The pure material is virtually odorless. The commercial material has a faint, pleasant-resinous odor.
Very faint, woody and slightly piney odor.
Pungent ethereal-nauseating odor, in high dilution reminiscent of Coffee or Wine.
Mild, sweet, slightly green-fruity odor.
Mild, oily-green, somewhat vegetable odor.
Agreeable, refreshing, fruity-green odor.
Powerful, oily-green odor with a sweet, vegetable-like undertone.
Mild, somewhat sweet-floral odor.
Strong, ethereal-winey odor.
Powerful green, herbaceous-vegetable, oily odor, reminiscent of many natural products.
Pleasant, but weak floral odor, suggestive of Rose and Jasmin, with undertones of greenearthy, herbaceous character.
Powerful, ethereal, green-herbal and leafy odor and very natural character.
Sweet, but somewhat harsh, haylike odor with floral-animal notes. Suggestive of Hawthorne, Mimosa, Heliotrope, etc
Mild and sweet-spicy, balsamic-fruity odor, reminiscent of carnation. Earthy-fresh notes, or leafy-floral notes not uncommon
Fruity-balsamic, warm and faintly spicy odor, somewhat clove-like, but with rosy floral notes and vanilla-like sweetness
Pungent, stinging sour odor, unpleasant when concentrated, less repulsive when diluted below} 15$0 in water.
Powerful, dry-herbaceous, woody-orrisy odor, remotely reminiscent of cuminic derivatives.
Light ethereal-nauseating and powerful odor of very poor tenacity. Irritant at high concentration, rather pleasant in dilution
Ethereal-camphorlike odor.
Ethereal odor
Agreeable odor, mild and reminiscent of Bitter Almond oil, but less pronounced than But yronitrile.
Pleasant, sweet-ethereal odor.
warm-spicy odor, reminiscent of breadcrust, burnt caramel, etc. with a fruity-floral, sweet note in extreme dilution.
Pungent-sweet odor, in dilution resembling that of hawthorn or is harsh orange-blossom type. The effect in perfumes is generally a flowery one, coumarin-like, warm, slightly animal, powerful.
Warm, green-spicy, somewhat floral odor, varying according to the chemical purity of the product.
Heavy, sweet-floral, somewhat animal odor. The odor picture varies according to the quality of the reaction product.
its general toxicity would decrease or possibly prevent its use in perfumes and flavors.
Very faint, sweet odor, remotely reminiscent of Vanillin, but less spicy, somewhat fresher.
Ethereal-minty odor, somewhat metallic or “’chemical”. In high dilution, the flavor in aqueous medium is sweet, remotely reminiscent of Peppermint sweetness.
Mild, sweet-musky odor with a faint, animal undertone and good tenacity.
Powerful, creamy-sweet, heavy-buttery, oily odor, yet somewhat milder than Diacetyl
Heavy creamy-sweet, fruit y-buttev odor, often described as “quinone-like”. Less buttery, more fruity than the normal ketone
Powerful and sweet, oily-buttery odor with herbaceous-cheesy undenone, yet not rancid or unpleasant in dilution
Pungent, sweet-caramellic, somewhat choking- ethereal odor.
Peculiar fruity-buttery, somewhat sour odor.
Peculiar camphoraceous-sweet odor with a certain amount of floral tones
Camphoraceous, minty-herbaceous, also somewhat floral odor.
Peculiar, warm-woody, somewhat herbaceous odor, reminiscent of Tobacco leaves (cured).
Powerful bakamic-sweet odor with a tobacco- like, almost narcotic pungency. Floral undertones are of balsamic-cinnamic character.
Sweet-musky, somewhat animal and slightly sour-sweaty odor of great tenacity.
Sweet woody-musky odor of considerable tenacity.
Peculiar, strong and persistent odor, simultaneously non-floral and heavy-sweet-floral. Not nearly as pungent as Acetophenone, but still rather chemical in its general character.
Intensely creamy-fatty-buttery, penetrating odor, yet milder and less “quinone’’-like than Diacetyl, not as sharp or volatile. Pleasant in extreme dilution.
When pure and dry, almost odorless.
Oily-buttery odor, pungent and somewhat “quinone’’-like, less sharp and volatile than Diacetyl.
Powerful, almost choking, Cigar-tobaccotype odor, which becomes pleasant only at extreme dilution, then also more typical tobacco-like.
Powerful, diffusive, buttery and slightly animal, quinone-like odor, pungent and cheesy, but sweet in its oily character.
Powerful oily-buttery, somewhat fruity odor
Mild and sweet, floral-Vanilla4ike odor of good tenacity. Fresher than the odor of Vanillin, but lacks the warmth of Vanilla and Vanillin.
The latter material has very little odor and is of no substantial use to the perfumer
Practically odorless
Pungent, irritating odor (A. is a lachrymator), unbearable to human mucous membranes or eyes.
Its odor resembles that of acetic acid, but it is more acrid, corrosive to human mucous membranes, irritating to the eyes.
Practically odorless.
Peculiar sweet-medicinal odor, reminiscent of Anise, Estragon, etc. with a herbaceousminty note, quite tenacious.
Peculiar sweet-minty, slightly woody odor, faint but tenacious.
Powerful, heavy-sweet, somewhat floral odor, resembling that of Heliotropine.
Pungent, herbaceous-oily and heavy-sweet odor of considerable tenacity and displaying a gamut of “natural” odors.
Diffusive, fresh-gassy, herbaceous odor. The gassy notes are more predominant in poorer grades of Allo-ocimene, almost im-perceptible in good grade mat].
Sweet, woody-caramellic, rather mild odor of Furan-type, the woody notes resembling the odor of sawdust.
Musky odor of considerable tenacity, but low odor level
Very faint, but tenacious sweet-woody odor with some resemblance to Cedarwood. Trace of animal notes.
Ethereal-winey odor, somewhat similar to that of Ethyl acetate, but more pungent, rumlike, fruity, arak-like.
Sharp-fruity, very heavy balsamic-grapelike, sweet odor with a somewhat green topnote.
Weak, but pleasant berry-like, fruity odor with some cherry caracter
Sweet-ethereal odor with somewhat fruity undertone.
Fruity odor, somewhat Peach-Apricot-like, also resembling Apple.
Musky -herbaceous, heavy odor, reminiscent of Cumin, Angelica, Mintleaf.
Banana-Pineapple type odor, somewhat fatty- sweet and powerful without being pungent.
Slightly pungent, fatty-fruity odor reminis-cent of Pineapple, Rum, Arak, remotely of Peach. Less ethereal, but more natural Pine-apple-like than Methyl caproate
Powerful fruity, slightly fatty Banana-Pineapple like odor with a somewhat oily-winey undertone.
Weak, but tenacious Peach-Apricot type odor, winey, balsamic and somewhat Styrax like
Onionlike, but pleasant and rather sweet, not pungent
Pronounced “mixed-fruit y“ odor, sweet, lasting and less ethereal than the lower aliphatic acetates.
“Mixed-fruity” odor of somewhat fatty character, quite tenacious.
Rather weak, fatty-fruity odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and sweet-fruity odor resembling Pineapple. Smoother and sweeter than Allyl caproate. Fruitiness similar to that of Linalylacetate.
Heavy, sweet. mixed-fruity odor of great tenacity.
Peculiar oily-fruity odor, nondescript fruit type.
Sweet and fruity odor without having characteristics of any specific type of fruit.
Ethereal-fruity odor, slightly pungent and, in moist atmosphere, reminiscent of Mustard.
Peculiar sweet-musty, fungal, Champignonlike odor.
Caramellic-fruity odor, often classified as “’jam-like” or “cooked-preserve-like”, reminiscent of canned, syrypy fruit,
Very powerful, but quite natural and not very pungent green-leafy, violet-leafy odor, typical ‘foliage” odor, less gassy than the Methyl ester.
Sweet-fruity, somewhat pungent, vinous Banana-like odor.
Oily-sweet, slightly flowery, but also fruity, woody and bark-like green odor of considerable tenacity.
Penetrating and extremely diffusive onion-like, but sweet and not really pungent odor.
Fruity -winey, somewhat fatty-oily odor, resembling that of wine residue, cognac residue or the like. A trace of sharpness in the fruity notes resembles Pineapple.
Fatty and slightly nutty, green-fruity, somewhat Pineapple-1ike odor.
Weak, anisic, sweet odor, more pungent than Anethole, less sweet or mild.
Somewhat sharp, mixed-fruity, mainly Pineapple- like and honey-sweet odor of great tenacity.
Sweet honeylike, but faint odor with sweetfruity undertones and good tenacity. Less floral than the Phenoxy+ster.
Somewhat sharp, sour-fruity odor, suggest - ive of Apple and Apricot
Powerful onionlike-garlic-like odor. Not pungent, more garlic-like than oniorrlike
Sweet-woody odor reminiscent of Ionones, Cedarwood and Vetiver, quite pleasant and fairly tenacious.
Peculiar herbaceous-fruity odor, softer than Amylsalicylate, slightly more fruity, not as harsh. A faint undertone of ‘“Wintergreen” character.
Pungent-fruity, diffusive, Pineapple-1ike, sweet odor.
Extremely penetrating, pungent and stinging odor.
Mild, herbaceous-fruity odor with a faint green note.
Vinous-fruity, fatty and powerful Banana- Pineapple type odor with Coconut-like background. Also reminiscent of Peach and Mango.
Fatty, Coconut-Pineapple type odor, powerful Rum-like background, reminiscent of Rum-residue, heavy, oily-sweet
Powerful winey-fruity, “fermented”, Applelike odor.
White crystals of Vanillin-like odor, somewhat weaker than Vanillin, but also more naturaI Vanilla-like.
Arnbrein is an odorless solid material
rich and extremely tenacious floral-musky, sweet odor.
Faint, musky odor, weaker than Ambrelto-lide
Faint, musky odor, weaker than Ambret{olide.

The title materials are bridly mentioned in this work because of their potential interest to the perfumer. “They are natural components of Ambregris, and they are considered of major importance to the olfactory properties of natural Ambregris and Ambre~is tincture.
Heavy-sweet, somewhat animal-floral odor of considerable tenacity, faintly reminiscent of tobacco leaf odor.
In the dry state, this chemical has only a very faint caramellicsweet odor.
Practically odorless in the dry state.
Virtually odorless when pure. Commercial products often have a slightly sweet-musty, bland odor.
Strong odor of Ammonia,
Strong aqueous solutions and heated crystals show odor of Ammonia.
Powerful and very diffusive, volatile odor. Violent chemical reaction upon mucous membranes.
used in flavors
Its strong odor is mainly due to decomposition which takes place even at room temperature.
The compound material has a sharp, cheesy, but also somewhat sweet odor and taste.
Pronounced fruity-fresh odor, sweet but slightly nauseating. In dilution reminiscent of Pear, Banana, Apple. Very volatile.
Powerful and diffusive, fruity, Banana-like odor, also resembling ‘“overripe Pears”.
Fresh-minty, fruity odor, not quite as sweet as the common iso-Amyl acetate.
Fruity-fresh, somewhat green odor, reminiscent of Apples, not quite as sweet as the odor of the iso-Amyl acetate.
Ethereal-fruity, somewhat green-herbaceous, winey-sweet odor.
Peculiar green-leafy, “foliage” type odor, not as “fatty” as Octanal.
Somewhat harsh, chemical odor, reminiscent of Fusel oil, but not as heavy, however, more penetrating, nauseating, cough-provoking. Only in high dilution fairly pleasant.
Choking, disagreeable, cough-provoking, somewhat alcoholic odor, only in high dilution becoming pleasant, fruity-winey.
Winey-ethereal, rather choking odor, somewhat drier than that of commercial 4’Amyl alcohol”.
Unpleasant Ammonia type odor with a decay-like, “decomposition”’ odor.
Warm-herbaceous, yet refreshing-ethereal odor with winey-fruity undertones.
Mild, sweet floral odor reminiscent of Heliotrope, fresh, soft, agreable and very tenacious.
Fruity-Plum-like, Ambre-Neroli type of odor
Balsamic, mild, sweet, slightly musky Ambre- type odor. Fruity cloverlike background. Quite tenacious.
Peculiar green-floral, sweet and somewhat herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and somewhat honey-like odor of good tenacity.
Floral-fruity odor, somewhat greener, more herbaceous than Benzyl acetate, and much more tenacious. Overall more Gardenia-like, less Jasmin-like.
Strong ethereal-fruity odor, reminiscent of Apricot, Banana, Pineapple.
Powerful and diffusive fruity, sweet Apricot-Banana-Pineapple-like odor, somewhat sharper than that of the iso-Amyl-iso-buty rate.
Fruity-Apricot-Pineapple type odor, softer and sweeter than that of the iso-Amyl-n-butyrate.
Fruity, heavy-sweet, diffusive odor, reminiscent of Banana and Peach.
Musky, Ambregris-like odor with an oilyfatty note.
Oily-winey, brandy-like odor with mild fruity undertones.
Pungent-fruity, yet refreshing odor, reminiscent of Pineapple, Apple, and remotely of Pear.
Somewhat sharp, Apple-Banana-Pineapplelike odor.
Sweet-oily, fruity odor with distinct “perfumey” floralness: Orris-Elderflower notes, under a Banana-like topnote.
Peculiar oily-fruity, slightly animal odor reminiscent of Elderflower, with orris undertones.
practically odorless.
Faintly balsamic, mild Ambre-like, Cocoabean-like (fresh beans), with undertones of Orchid-Labdanum, slightly animal and very tenacious odor.
Very mild, oily-waxy-floral, sweet and pleasant, tenacious odor.
Very mild oily -herbaceous and somewhat floral odor, reminiscent of many types of natural flowers, but mostly of Jasmin, Gardenia and Tuberose.
Warm-oily, herbaceous odor, less floral, but warmer than n-Amy lcinnamic aldehyde, Its lower boiling point results in a poorer tenacity and a somewhat less delicate initial note.
Practically odorless when pure, but may introduce mild-herbaceous, oily-green and slightly vinous notes when used as a modifier of the Aldehyde or its lower Acetals.
Faint and rather nondescript odor, somewhat herbaceous and oily-green, overall nonfloral. Apparently weak, but quite tenacious.

This acetal is described as having a Caraway- type odor, but the author does not quite agree, since he finds only a very mild, warmherbaceous, almost floral-green odor with a trace of spicy undertones.
Faintly oily, green-leafy and simultaneously floral odor, reminiscent of the herbal-floral part of Jasmin. Good tenacity.
Peculiar animal-green odor, mild and reminiscent of parts of the Jasmin complex, although not very floral unless composed with related Jasmin chemicals.
Oily -herbaceous, somewhat green-balsamic odor, not very characteristic of any natural material
Sweet-floral, predominantly Orangeblossom-like odor with oily -herbaceous undertones, reminiscent of Honeysuckle, Gardenia, Tuberose, remotely of Jasmin and other heavy florals.
Mild oily -fruity and somewhat green odor with balsamic and faintly floral undertones.
Oily-herbaceous, sweet and slightly green balsamic odor with some resemblance to Butter caramel.
Peculiar herbaceous-green, somewhat earthy- nutlike odor.
Mild fruit y, somewhat herbaceous-tobaccolike odor.
Very faint odor, vinous-herbaceous type.
Powerful, sweet and fruity odor of moderate tenacity. The fruity notes are rather nondescript, or they may be classified as remotely resembling Raspberry-Banana type.
Powerful, sweet-fruity odor of Banana- Pineapple-Pear type, but far from being a “natural”’ odor. Moderate to good tenacity.
Dry, pine-woody odor of good tenacity, yet of considerable diffusive power.
Very powerful, diffusive, woody-camphoraceous odor, slightly earthy, yet with some resemblance to Orris root, overall very dry.

Camphoraceous, balsamic-green and somewhat sweet odor, reminiscent of certain Pine needle oils, and with good tenacity. Its woody undertones makes it compatible with Patchouli oil, making the overall odor drier.

Fruity, fresh-floral and Jasmin-like odor, but it lacks the “bread-like” note of the Jasmine, a note found in cis-Jasmone and in the Methyl jasmonates. The odor of Amyl cyclopentenone is not as rich as the odor of the named materials.
Pecidiar faint odor, yet choking-nauseating when concentrated. Ethereal without being winey, green but not natural. Has a slightly metallic undertone. In dilution remotely reminiscent of Pear.
Sweet-spicy, somewhat herbaceous-floral, heavy odor of considerable tenacity
Heavy-sweet, balsamic-floral and very faintly spicy odor of exceptional tenacity.
Powerful ethereal-vinous, somewhat dry-earthy, yet fruity odor with earthy-green undertones.
Peculiar green-fruity, deep-sweet odor, almost nauseating undertone. Ethereal-volatile (diffusive) apple-winey topnote. Resembles also Blackcurrant and Plum.
Sweet-buttery, fruity and caramel-like odor, rather heavy, but also natural and pleasant in high dilution.
Sweet -green, somewhat floral odor with a distinctly fruity note, sweet-caramellic undertone.
Sweet-herbaceous, floral, somewhat spicy- Ambre-like odor of good tenacity.
Heavy, pungent, sweet-fruity odor, remi- niscent of Pineapple, Rum, fruit preserves, wine, etc. with a herbaceous-floral undertone.
Sweet-caramellic-winey, “fermented” odor.
Sweet-fruity, caramellic and somewhat floral odor.
Mild, herbaceous-winey, remotely floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful, but also sweet-leafy-green odor, closely resembling the odor of crushed Violet leaves. Less pungent, and less fatty than the lower alkyl heptin carbonates.
Mild citrusy-waxy odor with a faintly fruity note reminiscent of Banana pulp (the nonethereal note) or Peach (the dry note).
Peculiar oily-green, dry-fruity odor.
Peculiar green-fruity, somewhat grassy odor, reminiscent of Bananas and unripe fruits.
Oily-green, herbal odor, reminiscent of fresh-cut flowers stems, rather bitter-green, but refreshing and natural.
Mild, faint, oily -herbaceous odor, sweet and tenacious, like green wood
Faint, oily-floral, also somewhat herbaceous-green odor, overall very mild and bearing some similarity to the odor of Amylcinnamic aldehyde diethylacetal.
Fruity-winey, somewhat ethereal odor with caramellic undertone.
Rather sharp, fatty-fruity and sweet odor, reminiscent of Apricot and Orange.
Very mild oily -winey odor. To some people virtually odorless.
Its odor is extremely faint, oily-fatty, dependent upon the quality of the parent Laurie acid.
Warm, winey-carameliic odor of good tenacity.
Mild, fruity odor with a somewhat greenherbaceous undertone.
Extremely penetrating, unpleasant odor, typical of the mercaptans, sulfuraceous, choking, gassy.
Powerful ethereal, pungent, fruity-apple- Iike very diffusive odor. Somewhat choking, remotely reminiscent of Pineapple.
Fruity, somewhat green, but ak.o sweet and tenacious odor, remotely reminiscent of Strawberry, with a “cooked” note, almost caramellic.
Very mild, waxy odor, to some persons it is absolutely odorless.
Ethereal-fruity, vinous odor with a peculiar musty undertone, rather typical of many alkyl nitrates.
Extremely diffusive, ethereal-fruity, penetrating odor.
Somewhat nutty-oily, fruity-vinous, Apricotlike odor with a faint floral background, remotely rosy.
Powerful green foliage odor, less pungent and less sharp than the Methyl heptin carbonate, and not as fatty, overall more “oily”, yet pleasant.
Very faint “oily” odor, varying with the quality and age of the material.
Virtually odorless when pure, this ester may have a trace of an odor, depending upon its quality.
Sharp and pungent green foliags type odor, almost choking-gassy in the pure state, more pleasant at concentrations below 0.1 ‘?Oin an odorless solvent.
Very dry “phenolic” - medicinal odor, sometimes described as “’leatherlike”, but more appropriately “tanning-odor”.
Heavy green, “twig-like” odor, also bark- or sap-like with a fruity undertone.

Peculiar earthy-floral, somewhat camphoraceous and rather dry odor, remotely reminiscent of Rose and Hyacinth.

Sweet and somewhat floral odor of great tenacity. Faintly reminiscent of Amyl ‘salicylate, but more haylike-herbaceous.
no information
Very sweet-fruity, Apricot-Pineapple type odor with a somewhat harsh overtone and considerable radiance
Herbaceous and green-spicy, fairly tenacious odor, reminiscent of vegetables and condiments.
Sweet-herbaceous, slightly floral tobacco- Iike note, somewhat reminiscent of Elderflow - ers (animal undertones).
Sweet and somewhat floral odor, not without a note of animal, amine-like character. Overall less pleasant than many Alkyl pyridines
Fresh ethereal caramel-Rum-like odor with fruity-floral undertones.

Sweet herbaceous-green, slightly floral odor. Very tenacious, somewhat woody-earthy, sweet dryout notes. Refined qualities of this ester may show a marked difference in odor, particularly richer in sweetness and floral tones.
Very faint waxy-fatty odor, or practically odorless.
Virtually odorless, useful as a solvent, but does not seem to offer significant advantages over the much less expensive Diethyl phthalate.
Pleasant, mild, aromatic odor, suggestive of Gooseberry with a Grape-like, winey undertone, but overall weak.
Very faint odor, remotely reminiscent of Brandy, nondescript fruity
Dry-woody, somewhat camphoraceous odor.
faint, but pleasant aromatic- herbaceous odor, remotely reminiscent of Amyl acetate.
Herbaceous-winey, overall pleasant odor reminiscent of sweet medicinal herbs (meadowlike odor). The odor bears quite some resemblance to that of the -angelate.
Oily-rosy odor with vinous-brandylike undertone, overall mild and by some observers described as “odorless”.

Somewhat fatty-green, oily and fruity, Apricotlike odor with a faintly floral (Rose) undertone. pronounced brandy like, winey herbaceous in high dilution, but becomes rather unpleasant, almost “rubberlike”’ at high concentrations.
Fruity-ethereal, heavy, Apple-like odor, not as fresh-druity as the iso-Amyl-iso-valerate.

Fresh-herbaccous, fruity -minty odor, recalling the topnotes in Lavender and Lavandin (and many other herbaceous essential oils) less warm and not buttery as the alcohol, more citrusy, and almost geranium-like in topnote. Some observers find a rosy note in this ester.
Fruity -herbaceous, almost haylike-sweet odor, recalling topnotes in Lavender-Clary Sage. Less Lavandin-like, more Lavender- Clary-Sage-like than the Acetate, and also sweeter-warmer.

Reported as having a penetrating urine-like odor
Very sweet, herbaceous-wrarm odor, sweet taste. It is the prototype of odors described as “anisic”.
Pleasant, sweet-herbaceous odor, perhaps less sweet than Anethole, but with a freshness instead.
Peculiar spicy -caramellic, slightly acid odor.
lts intensely sweet-herbaceous, almost tobacco-like odor makes this chemical interesting for application in new fragrance types.

When absolutely pure, this material has a warm, sweet and actually pleasant odor - in suitabie dilution. Commercial grades are often unsuitable for smelling because of traces of very ill-smelfing Amines and other off-odors, by-product, etc.
Intensely sweet floral, yet somewhat “hayIike” odor, generally described as HawthorneIike.

Herbal-green, somewhat floral odor, suggestive of Lilac (“Lilac-green’”), Hyacinth, Appleblossom, etc.
Heavy-sweet, intensely floral odor with fruity undertones. Resembling the odor of the flowers of Robinia pscudoacacia, remotely resembling notes in Gardenia (fruity-Peachlike notes).
Practically odorless when pure, this chemical may carry some odor from the starting material (Anethole, or other).

Powerful and harsh, yet very sweet odor, rather chemical and not reminiscent of any natural material, except perhaps remotely of Anise, Its odor is often classified as “anisic”, but the author finds that this term would not be used by perfumers.
Mild fruity-floral, slightly balsamic-vanillialike odor in the Plum and Lilac type, also reminiscent of certain types of Cherry.

Intensely sweet, floral and slightly fruity, Cherry-preserve-like odor of good tenacity. It has considerable resemblance to Heliotropine in its overall performance in a composition. The main difference is in the fruity character, which is described as “Raspberrylike”’ by some perfumers (while Heliotropine is more ““Cherry-like”) and in the lack of “’powdery”’ notes in the
Mild-floral, very sweet odor, reminiscent of Lilac and Vanilla with a faint, delicate, balsamic background.
Very faint, balsamic-floral odor of great tenacity. The odor quality varies considerably with the origin of the material.
Reponed as having a sweet ““bitter Almond”’ and somewhat floral odor
Mild floral, intensely sweet and warmslightly fruity, Plum-like odor.
Heavy-sweet, floral and mildly fruity odor. Somewhat fresher than the n-Butyrate, and not as “jam-like”.
Sweet herbaceous-green, yet somewhat dry odor with a faintly musty, but not unpleasant undertone. Reminiscent of Vanilla beans (cured) with an exotic-floral background, much drier than the acetate.

Very faint fruity odor, reminiscent of Peach juice or Apricot juice. Very tenacious, and this ester may under proper condi~ions of blending contribute pleasantly to a composition of lower boiling materials.
Slightly pungent, but in dilution sweet, floral and creamy odor of considerable tenaIcity.
Very sweet, fruity -herbaceous, Mimosa- Honey-like, tenacious odor.
Very faint balsamic-rosy odor of great tenacity. Less honey like, more floral than Benzyl phenylacetate, also more fruity than this.
Sweet fruity, floral and somewhat Vanillalike odor.
Very sweet, fruity-Apricot-Nectarine-Grenadine- like odor.
Faint, herbaceous-warm, Parsley
Warm-herbaceous, more resinous-earth) than Apiole. Less Parsley-like.
Green-herbaceous odor, at the same time warm and minty, slightly bitter-woody.
Pure Asarone is reported to be virtually odorless
Nauseating “headachy” odor, chokingherbaceous, minty undertone
Woody-animal, rather powerful odor with pleasant sweet background.
Powerfull sweet odor, reminiscent of freshly crushed bitter almonds.
Sweet and mild, green odor, faintly reminiscent of the odor of Bitter Almond, but more herbaceous.
Mild-herbaceous, sweet and floral odor. The odor varies considerably with the age of the material; and samples from different suppliers have shown quite different odor characteristics.
Sweet-green and warm odor, remotely reminiscent of Nuts and Bitter Almonds.
Almost odorless
The acetal itself has a very faint odor, barely reminiscent of Bitter Almond
The acetal itself is practically odorless
The crystals have a very faint musty-rosy odor
Odorless when pure. However, the commercial product usually carries a peculiar, unpleasant ‘“Urine-like” or faint Carbylamine- like odor,
Very faint, sweet, nondescript odor.
Characteristic “gassy” hydrocarbon odor, choking, diffusive, warm.
stabilizer
Very faint, powdery-rosy, geranium-like odor with a slightly metallic note.
Powerful, but relatively sweet buttery- Iodine-like odor.
Penetrating Chlorine-Iodine-like odor, pungent,“medicinal”. The vapors are irritating to human mucous membranes and eyes.
Faint, but very tenacious balsamic-sweet, Vanilla-1ike odor of “’oriental” fragrance type. Also described as Tolu-balsam-like,
mild balsamic-spicy odor of great tenacity and warm underlines. The spicy notes are more pronounced in older material. Freshly prepared material may be almost odorless
Very faint, balsamic-sweet odor, usually carrying a trace of Vaniliin-like odor.
Powerful but “thin”, sweet floral, fresh and light, fruity odor reminiscent of Jasmin, Gardenia, Muguet, Lily and other flowers. Poor tenacity.
Pleasant balsamic-herbaceous and fruity odor, suggestive of “Oriental”’ fragrances, Ambre, etc.
Floral-green odor, fresher than that of Benzylacetate, more lasting. Stable in soap.
Mild and sweet, balsamic-floral odor of excellent tenacity
Faint, nondescript odor, rather sweet, but varies considerably with the quality of the alcohol.
Faint, but pleasant floral-citrusy odor, as always depending upon the quality of the ester, and the method of preparation.
Faint, sweet-balsamic odor, floral undertone. Trace impurities may ruin the odor picture from a perfumery point of view.
Heavy, fruity-floral odor, main]> fruit). like Plum.
Fruity-floral odor, somewhat fresher than that of the n-Butyrate, not as heavy.
Very faint, sweet-balsamic odor of great tenacity. Sometimes described as resembling the odor of Tolu balsam.
Very faint, fatty-waxy, remotely floral odor
Sweet, mild-fruity, slightly green odor, reminiscent of Apricot, but with a distinctly floral note.
Flat, but fruity odor, more peachy than Apricot-like, and with a herbaceous-fatty
Mild. sweet-balsamic and somewhat floral odor of great tenacity.
Rich, sweet-rosy odor, warmer than that of Citronellol.
Warm-herbaceous, mildly spicy, but not pungent odor of moderate tenacity
Peculiar herbaceous-green, yet very sweet and heavy-floral in its undertones. lt is reminiscent of the odor of Orange leaf water absolute, also of Orange flower water absolute.
Mild, but intensely sweet, floral odor in the  Jasmin-Orange flower theme. Excellent tenacity
Practically odorless
Warm-herbaceous-ethereal odor with fruityspicy character, quite powerful.
Mild, but rich-fruity, sweet, Plum-1ike, marmelade-like odor with a peculiar mint>- herbaceous character.
Powerful “bumt-caramellic” aroma, unpleasant at high concentration but resembling the odor of roasted carbohydrates when sufficiently diluted.
Sweet floral odor, reminiscent of the odors of Benzyl acetate and Benzyl propionate, sweeter, less pungent than that of the acetate, not as fruity as that of the propionate.
Su eet balsamic and very tenacious odor.
:%lild, oily -herbaceous, almost earthy odor with only a trace of fruity notes. Good tenacity.
Very faint, warm-spicy odor with a haylike undertone. Like most other crystalline materials, it can display a range of unusual odors mostly deriving from surface adsorption
Faintly rosy-balsamic-carnat ion type odor of exceptional tenacity. It is overall sweet and generally floral when blended with lower boiling components.
Very mild floral-spicy odor, balsamicsweet, delicate. Only in actual use it is reminiscent of certain flowers, such as Carnation, Rose, Magnolia, etc.
Powerful, fruity-green, herbaceous-earthy, yet somewhat floral, heavy, but not very tenacious odor.
Virtually odorless when pure.
Oily-green foliage odor with faintly floral undertone.
Herbaceous-fruity odor, remotely remini-scent of the fruity notes in Clary Sage or certain types of Lavender
Sweet, but rather pungent odor with a creamy-floral note.
Sweet floral, balsamic and heavy odor, somewhat herbaceous-warm undertone
Oily-spicy, warm, balsamic and very tenacious odor.
Rather sharp, fruit y odor, somewhat reminiscent of Strawberry.
.% eet-creamy, floral-balsamic tenacious odor. In dilution quite floral in the Sweet-Pea type, at higher concentrations it shows tendency of supplying spicy-warm notes.
Floral-earthy, slightly mushroom-like odor (Champignon-like).
Ve~ faint, fatty odor. Probably odorless to most people when this ester is absolulel> pure.
The odor is most frequently described as “Leek-like”, which - in the author’s opinion - is a more exact description than the older, still common “onion-like”.
Soft, warm, herbaceous-rosy odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet-floral and tenacious Hyacinth-green odor,
Sweet, fruity-floral, slightly balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, Jasmin-type odor, floral-fruity, of considerable tenacity.
Overall, it has little interest to the perfumer.
Faint, but fresh-balsamic, slightly fatty odor.
Mild, sweet, honey-floral odor, the honey note being almost imperceptible in pure material. In fact, a pure ester has an extremely faint odor.
Peculiar warm, nutlike and fruity, deep- sweet and oily odor of excellent tenaci~y.
Mild floral, somewhat Orris-like odor,
Fresh-floral, somewhat green odor, rather dry (compared to Dimethyl Benzyl carbinyl acetate ), and not as versatile, on account of the lack of sweetness.
Faint, sweet and remotely floral odor. However, most commercial products seem to have a pronounced “Bitter Almond” note, probably deriving from impurities in this chemical.
Heavy floral-earthy-mossy, “wet-green” odor, reminiscent of certain types of Rose. However, this ether is only pleasant smelling when properly diluted.
Fruity-sweet odor with pronounced floral undertone, overall type Jasmin. Less sharp, and more fruity than the acetate.

Powerful green vegetable type odor with considerable resemblance to the odor of raw stringbeans (or “Haricots-verts”). The warmherbaceous undertone is often accompanied by traces of a protein-like terminal note, possibly impurity-odor.

Very faint, sweet-floral, slightly balsamic odor. This ester is, according to the judgment of some people (including perfumers) absolutely odorless, while others find it “’musky”’ of odor. Trace impurities can greatly influence the odor of this high-boiling chemical.
Practically odorless when pure.
Very powerful Cress-odor, Watercress type, green-herbaceous, pungent.
The odor of this ester is very faint and uncharacteristic.
Peculiar fungus-like, mushroom-type odor with a rosy undertone.
Powerful fruity and somewhat musky, animal- like odor. The odor is less floral and more musky than that of the iso-valerate.
Powerful, fruity -herbaceous odor with a slightly musky undertone, reminiscent of cured tobacco leaves.
Powerful, sweet-medicinal-spicy odor, reminiscent of tanned leather, smoke and dry wood. In dilution reminiscent of the smokey - dry odor of Chinese tea
Pleasant, warm, sweet-spicy-balsamic odor, inevitably reminding the perfumer of Opopanax and “Oriental” fragrance types,
Sweet and very mild, delicately floral odor.
Dry-camphoraceous, woody-peppery odor.
Dry woody, slightly camphoraceous odor. Less peppery than dextro-Borneol.
Camphoraceous odor, not very woody, and not at all peppery. Overall more Camphorlike than Borneol.
Sweet herbaceous-piney odor with a balsamic undertone, Reminiscent of Pme Needles.
Mild oily -piney, balsamic-camphoraceous odor, reminiscent of Spruce Needles or certain Pine .Needles. The odor is overall thinner than that of Bornyl acetate.
Very faint, sweet-piney or balsamic-piney odor of considerable tenacity.
Fruity-herbaceous, slightly woody-mossy odor, resembling the odor of herbal saps
Peculiar earthy-nutlike, camphoraceous fir-cone-like odor.
Somewhat green-earthy. yet refreshing odor with a pine-needle undenone.
Green-earthy, herbaceous-camphoraceous odor, more piney than that of the Bornyl formate, and more camphor-like, less nutlike.
The commercial product has an extremely tenacious sweet-w oody and slightlj musky odor with considerable resemblance to Sandalwood.
The pure ester has very little odor, but could be used as a fixative.
Warm-herbaceous odor, less piney and more Rosemary -Lanvandin-like than the acetate. Slightly fruity topnote. Helpful in building up Juniper-Cypress-like notes for Men’s fragrances.
Sweeter, fruitier and less harsh than the acetate. The turpentine odor type is still there, but it is softer and combined with almost Lavender-like herbaceous notes.
Very mild, delicately sweet-powdery odor of considerable tenacity.
Fruity -herbaceous-camphoraceous odor, a herbal Pine type.
this ester has, in the author’s opinion, definitely an odor of its own, warmherbaceous, slightly earthy-green,
Its odor is similar to that of the iso-valerate, but the ester is less stable than the iso-valerate, and therefore not preferred.
Herbaceous-camphoraceous, warm and slightly green-woody odor.
Peculiar warm-terpeney odor, remotely reminiscent of Pinus Pumilio or Juniperberry, also reminiscent of Lemon (terpenes).
Pungent-sweet, gassy-floral odor, reminiscen~ of Hyacinth in extreme dilution. Slightly softer than the odor of omega-Bromostyrol.
Very powerful, pungent-floral and somewhat gassy odor, in extreme dilution reminiscent of Hyacinth, with emphasis of the greengassy pungency and very heavy sweetness.
Sweet-ethereal, nauseating odor, perceptible
Powerful, sweet-gassy, diffusive odor, in low concentration sweet and almost floral
Fresh, green-floral, delicately woody and quite tenacious odor.
Sweet-floral, slightly woody and wineywaxy odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, herbaceous-floral odor of rather poor tenacity.
Intensely sweet, but also pungent-herbaceous- balsamic odor resembling the odor of Anise and Fennel, but with emphasis on the woody -herbaceous notes.
Sweet and delicate, fresh-green, mildly floral and woody odor of moderate tenacity,
Powerful and diffusive, gassy-green odor in dilution more foliage-green or vegetable green with an “earthy” bitterness, yet introducing a distinct sweetness of floral and also Firbalsam character,

Very diffusive, ethereal-fruity, pungent odor, reminiscent of many kinds of (ripe and overripe) fruit. Very poor tenacity. The odor is often described as resembling that of Pear, Banana, Strawberry, etc. but it may be closer to Pear than to any other single fruit.
Very diffusive, ethereal odor resembling Rum (“fermented” odor) with a distinct fruity note.
Sweet-winey, brandy like, “fermented-fruit”- like odor.
The odor is somewhat fresher, not as “fermented “’as that of the n-But yiester.
The odor resembles that of para-Methyl acetophenone, but is somewhat milder, more refined, subdued. The character is more woody-hay-like, warm and quite tenacious.
Powerful, very sweet, balsamic-floral, discretely herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Penetrating oily-green, vegetable-and-foliage type odor, in high dilution reminiscent of the odor of raw beans, green beans, etc., also of the odor of raw potatoes.
.Mild ‘“fuseI’’-like odor, more volatile and more choking than fusel oil itself. Although somewhat winey in character, its odor is really nondescript, rather .-chemical”.
Choking, cough-provoking odor unless diluted; then rather mild, chemical, sweet, yet somewhat harsh.
Oily -vinous odor, sweeter than that of the n-primary-Butanol, and not as “fuseI-oil ““-like.
Camphoraceous and somewhat “mint) ““ odor, the dryness being characteristic and different from the other isomers.
Powerful, woody-green somewhat oily odor, reminiscent of fresh woodsap and bark. At proper dilution, the woody notes become more minty-earthy, root-like, dry.
pronounced camphoraceous odor
Warm-herbaceous, winey odor with distinct caramellic undertone.
Fresh-herbaceous, winey-fruity odor, less warm, more fruity than the odor of the n-Butylester.
Very faint, sweet and nondescript-floral odor, reminiscent of Mimosa, Cassie, and of the “dryout’’-notes of heavy floral fragrances, e.g. Ylang-Ylang. It has good tenacity, but lacks character.
Faintly vinous, fruity-sweet odor with a rather heavy woody-floral undertone. It is characteristic of many odor descriptions of this type, that [he word “Mimosa” or the word ‘“Banana” appears.
Faint, but heavy-woody-floral odor with an almost camphoraceous dryness. It is the least sweet of the three Butylanisates mentioned in this work.
Mild, sweet-fruity-floral odor including the inevitable Orangeblossom theme, but overall flat and not as fresh in its type as the iso- Butylester.
Renounced fruity, very sweet and deep (warm) odor, yet fresh and with only a faintly floral undertone.
Warm-herbaceous, almost spicy odor of considerable tenacity.
Very mild floral-balsamic odor with woodyspicy undertone.
Weak, but fresh and pleasant, tenacious orrisy odor with green-rosy undertones, less balsamic than the n-Butylester.
Peculiar camphoraceous-earthy, aromatic odor, remotely reminiscent of the odor of Carrot seed.
Peculiar woody odor, often described as reminiscent of Sandalwood (or burning Sandalwood) and therefore suggested for use in incense-type fragrances.
Green-floral, fresh and slightly sweet-herbaceous odor, somewhat reminiscent of iso- Butyllinalool. Very good tenacity.
Fresh-floral, fruity and slightly green, natural- herbal odor. Good tenacity.
Sweet floral, somewhat pungent odor, reminiscent of Rose and Geranium, but with a “chemical”’ note. In the description of the odor one often finds the word “metallic”
Fresh-floral, somewhat “chemical”, but overall sweet odor. Fresher and fruitier, but less rosy than the n-Butylether.
Heavy, sweet-herbaceous, somewhat spicy odor of good tenacity. Woody undertones.
Fresh and sweet-fruity, powerful and rather diffusive odor, reminiscent of Banana (over-ripe) and Pineapple.
Fresh-fruity, rather penetrating odor, reminiscent of Apple, Banana and Pineapple.
Ethereal fruity, somewhat -pungent odor reminiscent of Pear, Pineapple and Banana. Fresher, but not as soft as the n-Butyl-nbutyrate.
Sweet-fruity, but also rather harsh-Pineapple- like, diffusive-ethereal odor. Fresher, but less characteristic (a non-descript fruit type) than the other isomers.
The classical odor picture: Cumin-Anise- Ambregris is rather vague, and does not really describe the material, be it pure or contaminated.
Sweet-sour “Buttermilk’” type odor with a mild-fruity undertone.
Heavy, oily-sweet, Brandy (Whisky-Cognac)- like odor with fruity topnote. Not very pleasant at high concentration. Odor resembles residue of Cognac or Whisky.
Heavy vinous-fntity odor, reminiscent of overripe Pineapple, yet pleasant in high dilution,
Heavy winey-fruity Pineapple-like odor.
used in flavors
Mild-herbaceous-woody, but overall fruit yoily odor with a faint, winey undertone.
Sweet-oily-balsamic-fruity odor, remotely reminiscent of the odor of fresh Cocoa beans. Floral undertone and good tenacity

Herbaceous-balsamic odor with a faint. fruity undertone, warm and ““Oriental “’over-all type. The overall odor pattern is also described as Ambre-Cocoa like, mild, sueet and tenacious, which however, more describes the use of this chemical.
Green-oily -herbaceous odor, usually with a floral undertone.
Rather penetrating, oily-fatty, herbaceous odor.

Powerful and diflusive, waxy-fatty-floral odor, yet refreshing and natural odor. lt is much sweeter and less lemony than Citral, and it has more of the natural Citral-Nerol character as for instance observed in Lemon Petitgrain oil, or in terpeneless Lemon oil.
When absolutely pure, this ester has virtually no odor. However, a trace of Butanolodor is of[en perceptible.
Dry-woody-leathery odor, usually described as ‘“Russian Leather’’-odor (Cuir de Russie).
Powerful, dry, Leather-like odor of moderate tenacity.
The author is of the opinion that it smells  very unpleasant, pungent and that it is a lachrymator.
Powerful, camphoraceous-piney, mostly minty and somev hat tarry odor of great tenacity.
Extremely dry, woody-camphoraceous, almost “tarry” odor with a Ieather-like undertone.
Powerful and diffusive camphoraceous- woody, rather dry and musty odor of moderate tenacity
Powerful and diffusive woody-camphor-aceous and warm odor of moderate tenacity
Powerful, dry-camphoraceous, slightly minty odor with woody Cedar-Patchouli-like undertones.
Powerful fruity odor, remotely resembling Raspberry, but rather chemical and harsh at high concentration.
Piney-woody - fruity, powerful and fresh odor with a slight}y green undertone
Musty-dry, somewhat leathery-woody and Orris-like odor of moderate tenacity.

Sweet, almost ‘“creamy ’’-woody odor with a soft-floral undertone, reminiscent of tonones, Cedarwood and Benzyl salicylate. Some descriptions include the name Ylang-Ylang, but most perfumers agree that it is primarily an Orris-type of odor.
The practically pure cis-isomer has a pronounced fruity note over the woody sweetness and velvety softness that make it resemble Orris products
Mild, but rich and tenacious fruity-sweet odor with a Benzaidehyde-like undertone (impurity ??).
Sweet and warm, rather powerful floral odor of nondescript type, and with a percept woody-herbaceous undertone. A complex of generally pleasant notes.
Powerful, rich, oily-fatty, fruity odor, reminiscent of the peel section of Peach and Apricot. Natural-green undertones and moderate tenacity.
Its odor is mild, sweet, more .balsamic than floral, and rather unnatural in its overall character.

Powerful, but not very pleasant “tanning” type of odor, sometimes describes as “Oakmoss- like” - at other times described as “Cuir de Russie” type. Most observers will agree that the odor is distinctly phenolic, very dry and almost woody, tarry.
Peculiar, somewhat animal, Skatole-like, woody odor in the Vetiver-Cedar type, with a chemical note. Not exactly pleasant in the pure state.
Virtually odorless when pure.
Sweet musky, somewhat pungent odor.
Mild, oily-winey odor of moderate tenacity.
Very dry, mossy, Oakmossy-phenolic odor, yet with considerable sweetness and excellent tenacity.
Very diffusive, ethereal, Rum-1ike odor. Volatile (very poor tenacity).
Mild-ethereal, pleasant odor, reminiscent of Rum and Raspberries, the “ethereal”’ odor arising from a barrel of Raspberries, freshly picked.
Musty-floral odor, between theherbaceous and the floral, sweet and slightly green
Floral-herbaceous, sweet and somewhat cloverlike odor.
Peculiar Brandy-like odor, woody ethereal, not very tenacious.
Fruity -winey, Brandy-like odor with bitterwoody undertones and moderate tenacity
Brandy-like, sweet, somewhat “burnt “’odor with a woody note.
Winey-Brandy-like odor, more woody, somewhat chemical and not as pleasant as the n-Butylester.
Pou erful fatty-green, floral and sweet odor with fruity undertones.
Powerful, but relatively pleasant violetgreen odor. Less fatty than the Methylester, not as pungent
Fresh, fruity-green, Apple-peel like (unripe Apple) odor, also described as ““Marigold ““- like.
Fruity-winey, fresh odor, not as green as that of the n-Butylester
Green-buttery, slightly “metallic’’-chemical odor.
Slightly green, woody-floral, somewhat chemical-metallic odor, remotely reminiscent of topnotes in Bois de Rose or Lavender.
POW erful, warm-aromatic odor with a peculiar complexof rather unnaturalnotes, slightly woody-fruity, but not entirely pleasant.
Oily, but slightly pungent-fruity, herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Less winey than ,Methylnon, and not qui[e as Orange-like.
Warm, mossy -netlike, root-like odor of excellent tenacity. The sweetness has some similarity to that of Musk Ambrette and Vetiver, while the earthy notes resemble Walnut and Oakmoss.
Very faint phenolic type odor.
Used as a preservative
Used as an Antioxidant
Its powerful, grassy-green, pungent odor and rather poor tenacity could place it among materials for perfuming of household products, detergents, etc.,
Very powerful odor reminiscent of Celery juice and Celery seed, warm, penetrating and tenacious (soup-like dry-out odor).
Warm-carameliic odor with a winey type of undertone.
Heavy, warm-herbaceous. “soupy” odor, suggestive of Lovage root and somewhat reminiscent of Celery, but heavier.
Powerful Celery-like, warm-herbaceous, spicy odor of great tenacity.
Pou erful, diffusive odor, less pungent than that of Indole, overall milder and more floral,particularly in proper dilution.
Powerful diffusive odor reminiscent of Skatole more than of Indole, but considerably milder, not as offensive as Skatole.
Powerful, fruity odor with winey-caramellic undertone.
Powerful, diffusive, fruity and sweet odor, often with a “butyric” undertone, poor tenacity.
Faint buttery-fruity odor with caramellic undertone.
Mild oily odor, bul very pure grades of this chemical are vinually odorless.
Sweet and slightly pungent-caramellic odor with fruity undertones. Overall warm and almost herbaceous with some similarity to Valerolactone.
Sweet-fruity, somewhat floral and richwoody odor.
Vinous-fruity and floral odor with a distinct Melon-Apple-like note.
Faint, winey odor of good tenacity, but with a chemical undertone.
Mild, ethereal-winey odor with a fruity undertone, yet somewhat hard or chemical.
Powerful, diffusive odor, reminiscent of Cabbage. Often described as Skunk-like, or just ““sulfuraceous”’.
Powtrful, diflusive, gassy-ethereal, sueelherbaceous odor u ith a warm-winey undertone and rather poor tenacity.
Powerful, woody-floral odor of considerable Ienacity.
Sweet-musky, rather harsh-herbaceous odor.
Powerful herbaceous, rather sweet odor, reminiscent of Clovercomplex, including the Coumarin-type of odor.
Sweet and floral-fruity odor of Petitgrain-Grapefruit type. Good tenacity and very attractive overall fragrance.
Powerful, penetrating green ‘“foliage”’ odor, between Violet leaf and Cucumber, but rather pungent-gassy in its approach, not as pleasant as the higher esters.

Fresh, floral-green odor of moderate to good tenacity. The floral notes are predominantly Lily -Muguet-like, while the green notes resemble Watermelon rind. The material displays a distinctly balsamic undertone.
Sweet, yet refreshing and intensely floralgreen odor of considerable radiance, although at the same time quite tenacious
This chemical resembles in odor not only Sandalwood as such, but it carries an “’intense”’- like note that attracted the attention of the first observers.
Mild, oil} -fatty odor reminiscent of Castor oil.
Pungent-sweet, Mushroom-tobacco-like odor of moderate tenacily, but of great pen-etration.
Very faint, oily, Linseed-oil-like odor, mild, but persistent.
Faint, nondescript odor between fruity and winey, rather pleasant but weak.
Fresh, slightly oily-rosy, fruity odor reminiscent of Applepeel, Orange and Apricot,
Almost odorless, but develops a flower-waxlike odor in blends with lower boiling fragrance materials.
Pou erful dry-leathery -phenolic odor, remotely reminiscent of the odor of certain Oahmoss products.
Sweet-herbaceous, Honey-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Pleasant, floral-green odor with soft-woody or green-bark-woody undertones. Fair to moderate tenacity.
Somewhat hard or chemical Rose-Honey, slightly animal odor of “good tenacity.
They are sweet, anisic-type odors of moderate tenacity.
Musty-fruity odor of moderate tenacity and an overall unnatural character

Powerful and very diffusive leafy-rosy- musky odor with ewxptional topnote effect. Distinctly fresher and more diflusive (not really volatile) than the n-Butylester. Slightly waxy notes (fresh, Narcisse-like ) are typical of the pure product, while unpleasant or pronounced animal-honeylike notes dominate the poorer grades.
Mild floral odor, slightly green, wood}- barklike. One manufacturer classifies it as “Orris-like”.
Mild floral odor, suggestive of Lindenblossom, a delicate combination of woody and floral with a discrete dryness.
Fresh-woody, delicately fruity and green odor of moderate tenacity.
Harsh-chemical odor, sweet, but with metallic- chemical background, remotely reminiscent of Anise.
!Miid and sweet, floral-fruity odor with a faintly balsamic and animal undertone. Reminiscent of Strawberry, Rose and Lily.
Practically odorless when pure.
Warm-spicy, herbaceous odor, reminiscent of concentrated vegetable soup, suggestive of Celery and Lovage
Mild, balsamic-sweet and very tenacious odor, faintly floral, and warm
Ethereal-rumlike, rather heavy odor, yet Iola~ile. diffusive.
Diffusive, ethereal-fruity and sweet odor, reminiscent of Rum. Overall fresher and more rumlike than the n- Butylester.
Heavy-floral odor, somewhat reminiscent of Heliotrope
Green-woody. slightly bark-like odor with striking resemblance to the odor of cured tobacco leaves (unflavored, but cured). In fact, the odor resembles that of a Cigarshop (without the smoke!)
Woody earthy-mossy, slightly spicy odor, somewhat resembling Oakmoss (certain types of extract), Cardamom (with emphasis on the earthy notes) and, in extreme dilution, Ambre-like.
Powerful earthy-tarry-mossy odor, at the same time sweet and dry, root-like.
Powerful “Nicotine’’-type odor, reminiscent of Tobacco-tars, “ashtray-odor”, rather unpleasant. In extreme dilution almost floral and sweet.
Tobacco-Ii ke, also Nicotine-like, sweetamine- type odor, not as unpleasant as that of 2-secomfary-Buty lquinoline.
Powerful earthy-spicy, warm and woody odor, remotely reminiscent of certain types of Oakmoss extract.
Very faint oily odor, strongly dependent upon purity of chemical.
Somewhat rough-herbaceous-chemical-odor, resembling Ethyl benzoate (but weaker) with a trace of Wintergreen note. Not as floral as iso-Butyl salicylate
Overall sweet, but somewhat harsh-herbaceous- floral odor, generally described as resembling Clover and Orchid.
Very faint, dry-musky odor, not as interesting as that of the n- Butyl sebacate
Fat t y, somewhat dry odor, practically odorless ~’hen pure. However, this ester does introduce interesting notes to fatty-fruity fragrances or flavors.
Virtually odorless, to some people displaying a faintly musky odor.
Practically odorless when pure.
Musky-woody, sweet and slightly camphoraceous odor, remotely reminiscent of Sandalwood odor.
Lach~mator. Green-sharp, vegetable odor, diffusive and pungent-painful on human mucous membranes unless extremely diluted.
Lacrymator. Sharp, pungent, green-vegetable odor.
Lachrymator. Sharp, but refreshing, vege- table odor lype, slighttj green. Pleasant in dilutions of less than 1 ppm.
Faintly fruity, resembling Butylacetateodor, but much weaker and not really Rumlike.
Warm-herbaceous, diffusive and almost gassy ethereal odor, sweet and of moderate to poor tenacity.
Buttery-fatty, winey odor, reminiscent of Brandy-residue. Very good tenacity.
Ethereal-fruity, somewhat choking odor, harsher than that of the iso-iso-ester.
Slightly fresher than the n-Butyl-n-valerate,
Ethereal-fruity, Apple-like, somewhat pungent odor.
Fruity-ethereal Apple-Raspberry-like odor.
Dry-tarry-leathery odor of considerable tenacity.
Very diffusive, penetrating, pungent-irritating odor. Only in extreme dilution will truly fruity, Banana-like, green-fresh odor become perceptible.
Extremely diflusive, penetrating odor, pungent and - undiluted - unpleasant, sour, repulsive. In extreme dilution it becomes almost pleasant, fruity, Banana-like, “overripe fruit-Iike”.
Powerful, penetrating, diffusive sour odor, reminiscent of rancid butter.
Powerful, diffusive sour (acid) odor, less repulsive, and also less buttery than  n-Butyric acid. In extreme dilution the odor  becomes almost pleasant, fruity.
Sharp, irritating, acrid odor.
Faint, sweet-aromatic odor, rather nondescript.
Buttery-creamy, nutlike, somewhat herbaceous odor.
Sweet and warm, woody-floral odor of Mimosa-Y1ang type, carrying an oily, but not unpleasant overtone, resembling the topnote in Ylang-Ylang.
Strong, sweet musky odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, ethereal-creamy odor. in dilution just sweet and bland, but rat her pleasant, caramellic dryout.
Mild, dry-woody, sli~tly medicinal-tarry odor with some similarity to spices or condiments (herbs) in the Cumin-Thyme famil}.
Virtually odorless.
Virtually odorless
Virtually odorless.
Practically odorless.
Mild, oily-camphoraceous odor
The odor of the chemical itself is sweet, woody and very tenacious. The wood-note has resemblance to Sandalwood, but is not quite as sweet.
Green-woody, moderately sweet and very tenacious odor.
Warm-minty almost ethereal-diffusive odor of very low tenacity.
Very tenacious, mild Sandalwood type odor, not as sweet or balsamic as Sandalwood oil, and not nearly as powerful in active use.
Peculiar mild, warm-herbaceous odor, overall weak

Extremely volatile. Diffusive odor, choking-Iy repulsive, ethereal-sulfuraceous. It has often been claimed that the malodor is due entirely to impurities, and the author can confirm that this chemical, coming out of the exhaust vent of a Gaschromatograph, does not smell truly repulsive, but rather sweet, cabbage-like, almost herbaceous, slightly green.
Dry, but pleasant ““Russian-leather”’ type of considerable tenacity.
Sweet, duffusive, penetrating odor, somewhat reminiscent of a refined Limonene.
Warm-herbaceous, yet refreshing odor.
The material is virtually without odor
Penetrating, dry-medicinal (“-phenolic”) - herbaceous odor with a spicy undertone. Main difference from Thymol odor is the lack of sweetness in Carvacrol, the latter being more “tarry”.
Aromatic-mild odor, very tenacious and somewhat reminiscent of the odor of Carrot seed.
Mild, but very tenacious odor, reminiscent of the Fougere-theme, mild-herbaceous, sweetwoody with a faintly medicinal undertone.
Warm-spicy-herbaceous odor, somewhat reminiscent of the odor of Carrot seed, sweeter than the odor of Carvacryl acetate.
Green-spicy, “’vegetable” type of odor, more interesting than that of the acetate.
The odor is more Caraw’ay-iike than Spearmint- like
Warm-herbaceous, breadlike, spicy and slightly floral odor, reminiscient of Caraway seed or Dill seed.
Warm-herbaceous, breadlike, penetrating and diffusive odor, somewhat spicy, in extreme dilution also floral, overall reminiscent of Spearmint oil (rectified).
Warm, herbaceous-spicy odor, reminisce t of Carvone, with less character.
Refreshing, green-minty, Spearmint-1ike odor, more “cool” than Carvone, not as penetrating, but with a peculiar “metallic”’ undertone.
Sweet, warm, minty-spearminty, warmer and more herbaceous than the acetate, also displaying a slightly fruity undertone
Woody-spicy, dry and tenacious odor.
Mild fruity-woody odor, fresh-green, saplike, quite tenacious.
Warm, earthy-mossy, spicy odor, remotely resembling that of Trimethyl cyclohexanol, slightly minty, basically woody, and of good tenacity.
distinctly floral note.
Sweet Vanilla-1ike odor, weaker than i anillin, but a heavier note with a trace of Anisic sweetness in it.
Reported as being an interesting perfume chemical with Geranium-Rose type odor.
Reported as being an interesting perfume chemical with a conspicuous Rose-geranium
Pleasant, sweet, floral odor, remotely resembling Anise and Heliotrope, but more diffusive and of poor tenacity.
.%eet-floral, herbaceous, Jasmin-like odor of good tenacity.
Woody-camphoraceous, somewhat dry and green odor, reminiscent of CedarWood (American).
Dry-woody, but very pleasant odor with certain sweetness in its undertone.
Generally of mild woody odor, Iess dry, more balsamic than the Cedrene.
soft-woody odor
Faint, fresh-woody odor of good tenacity,
Very faint odor (when pure, almost odorless) of Cedarwood type. A more “’balsamicsweet” odor is perceptible in low-grade Cedrols.
Refined-woody, pleasantly green odor of good tenacity.
Refined-woody, pleasantly green odor of good tenacity.
Very faint, mainly woody odor with more sweetness than that of Cedrol, and with exceptional tenacity. The woody notes seem to dominate the terminal odors of this material,
Mild, but persistent dry-woody odor. The woody notes are accompanied by a discrete amount of greenness, which completes an ensembie of some similarity to part of the Ambergris odor picture.
Very faint, woody-floral odor, somewhat reminiscent of the refined Methylionones. Extremely tenacious, but lends very little odor itself.
Practically odorless and tasteless, except for a distinct burning mouthfeel and pungency on mucous membranes.
Almost odorless.
Powerful, dry, tarry-medicinal “phenolic” odor, very penetrating and persistant.
Fruity, rather sharp, but clean odor of considerable tenacity. Overall type: Jasmin- Gardenia.
Odor similar to that of Muse Baur*), sweet, heavy, musky, slightly more pungent and less tenacious.
Diffusive, heavy, sweet-ethereal odor with considerable anesthetic effect.
Sweet, but rather pungent-floral odor of Hyacinth-type.
Phenolic-spicy odor, somewhat fruity, anisic- sweet, suggestive of Ylang-Y1ang, Narcisse, Lily, etc.
Penetrating, rather harsh-floral, Hyacinthtype odor, not as sweet as that of Bromostyrol.
Almost insoluble in water, soluble in alcohol and oils. Thymol-like odor, but not as sweet, more “’medicinal”, less condiment-like.
Mild-phenolic type odor, rather dry but weaker than that of phenol or cresol.
Diffusive camphoraceous-fresh odor, more camphor-like, and not as sweet as Eucalyptol
Fresh, diffusive, camphoraceous-cool odor of poor tenacity.
Very faint honeylike, balsamic odor, easily contaminated from outside odorants
Overall Hyacinth-type odor with some resemblance to Rose.
Warm-spicy -balsamic odor, suggestive of Cassia-cinnamon. Good tenacity and lasting sweetness.
Faint, but fresh-green, slightly spicy, oily-sweet odor.
Soft, tenacious, natural Cinnamon-type odor, not nearly as harsh as Cinnamic aldehyde, yet rich and lasting as the aldehyde itself.
Fresh-green, spicy-herbaceous Cassia-cinnamon type odor, more Cassia-like than the Diethyl acetal, yet less harsh than the aldehyde.
Pleasant, soft-spicy, warm, sweet odor suggestive of Cinnamon. rather than of Cassia (a softness resembling that of Clove). Not nearly as harsh as the odor of the aldehyde.
The spicy cinnamic note is rarely wanted along with Orangeblossomnotes, except in certain variations of the Oriental fragrances.
Virtually odorless
Sweet, mild-balsamic and slightly floralfruity odor. The spicy note has a tendency of ‘“showing through”
Mild, but extremely tenacious fruity-floral odor, mostly Rosy-floral, almost Magnolialike.
Mild-spicy, tenacious and balsamic odor. Freshly prepared and pure grade materials are odorless to many people, faintly “musky” to others.
“Fruity-balsamic, rather faint, but actually heavy odor, resembling Phenylethyl butyrate, but less floral. The undertone is floral and rich, but the overall impression is fruitybalsamic.
Fresh-fruity, mild-balsamic very sweet odor somewhat reminiscent of ripe Banana with an added fragrance of Plum.
Fruity-green, slightly spicy, sweet and warm odor, remotely reminiscent of Banana and Mango.
Very mild, balsamic-winey odor, slightl> oily-fruity, (nondescript fruity).
\“ery mild, but very tenacious balsamicfloral, soft odor. Hardly any spice note at all.
This ester is, to the author’s knowledge, very rarely used in perfumes or flavors.
Very mild, spicy -balsamic odor. It is claimed that when this chemical is absolutely pure, it has no perceptible odor.
Green-herbaceous, yet “’cinnamic” odor, balsamic, but more “&y’’-fruity than the higher cinnamates. Powerful and of good tenacity.
Sappy-green, slightly woody-earthy, but overall sweet floral-balsamic, slightly fruity odor, reminiscent of Hyacinth-foliage or Iris-foliage
lntcnscly sweet, but somewhat pungentfloral- herbaceous odor of considerable tena-city
Tenacious-floral, balsamic-green odor
In[ensely sweet, honey-like, tenacious odor with herbaceous-tobacco-like undertone.
Powerful, warm-spicy, oily and slightly floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Faint, but sweet and fruity-oily odor of somewhat orrisy type and excellent tenacity.
Mild, but deep and sweet, Tolubalsam-like odor with herbaceous-floral undertones and outstanding tenacity.
Fruity -balsamic, but also floral (rather rosy) odor with mild cinnamon-like undertone.
Very faint, sweet and pleasant balsamic odor. A trace of a rosy or nondescript-floral undertone. Good tenacity
Very pleasant, floral-herbaceous odor, suggestive of Styrax and Peru balsams, or rather of the distillates of same. A faint, green note is perceptible in the undertones. Good tenacity.
Delicate]} floral, rather rosy odor of good tenacity and with a trace of fresh-green, herbal tone.
Fresh, but delicately floral, rosy odor. Balsamic, almost sweet-tobacco-like undertones. Good tenacity.
Widely used as a powerful Lemon-fragrance chemical, but suffers from poor stability in many types of functional products
Floral-citrusy, delicate odor, very different from that of Citral. Sweeter, fresher than Citral, and more floral (Lily -1ike).
Mild and fresh, green-citrusy, almost vegetable- juicy odor with a pleasant, natural oily-fruity undertone. The odor is very heavily influenced by the presence of small amounts of Citral.
Very mild, oily-green, vegetable-fresh and slightly citrusy odor.
Sweet, fruity-rosy odor, somewhat resembling that of Neryl acetate, but lighter and fresher of character.
Stability and odor type depends strongly upon the method of processing and the ratio of Citral,’Indole used in the reaction.

The odor, which may vary from sweet Orange-blossom to fresh Orange peel-like, or Grapefruit-peel-like, is strongly dependent upon the method of preparation and the ratio of Aldckyde,’Anthranilate used.
Very pleasant, sweet-citrus) lemon-orangelike odor, mild, oily and somewhat green.
Virtually odorless

Powerful, fresh, green-citrusy, slightly woody odor, lacking in sweetness and fruitiness as compared to Citral, and more suggestive of Citronella oil, inevitably if the observer is familiar with that oil.
Mild, green-herbaceous and sweet odor of considerable tenacity. Commercial products vary in odor type and strength, probably because of differences in composition and purity.
Very faint odor when absolutely pure (free from Aldehyde). More lemony-green than the aldehyde proper
Very faint, grassy-green, slightly lemonyoily odor. The pure acetal has only very little odor at all.
Very faint, soft-floral-fresh odor of good tenacity.
Fresh-green-citrusy, almost herbaceous odor, usually contaminated with a Dill-weed like odor from iso-Pulegyl acetate.
Fresh-floral and very tenacious odor, recalling the delicate as well as the deep-exotic notes from natural flower material, mostly in Jasmin-Tuberose direction.
Very tenacious, sweet-floral, Orange-peel and Orange-blossom complex odor.
Faint, fresh-green, somewhat grassy odor, not very pleasant, rather weedy-oil y note.
Powerful, spicy-weedy, somewhat camphor- aceous odor.
Powerful weedy-camphoraceous-minty odor with a herbaceous undertone, including some sweetness, but not enough to call the material \ overall pleasant smelling
Fresh rosy odor, variable according to purity, content of Dimethybctanol, Geraniol, etc. Overall sweet, fresher, lighter rosy-floral than Geraniol.

Colorless oily liquid of very fresh, light and quite diffusive, rosy-leafy, slightly waxy, petallike odor. It is sweeter than ordinary Citronel- 101,and has absolutely no “minty” notes, yet a certain “coolness” in its fresh odor.
Fresh-rosy-fruity odor, somewhat reminiscent 01’Geranium
Rich, sweet, floral-rosy, fruity odor of considerable tenacity
Very mild rosy, somewhat dry-woody odor of considerable tenacity, but of low odor value, overall not too interesting
Intensely fruity, sweet and somewhat rosy, leafy (rose-petal-like) odor. Overall warm, deep and very pleasant.
Fresh, almost citrusy-rosy, intensely fruity and sweet odor, lighter than that of the n-Butyrate, not as warm or deep.
Faint, but rather heavy and very tenacious, musky-fruity odor of Pear-Peach type with somewhat dry undertones (musky).
Delicately floral, pronounced fruity (Apple- Pear-Pineapple notes) and somewhat rosy odor of fair tenacity.
Very faint, sweet-floral and somewhat oily odor of great tenacity.
Fresh-herbaceous, slightly green and warm-rosy odor of moderate tenacity. A winey note seems to be normal in this ester.
The above material has been reported as being an interesting perfume material with a floral, sweet-rosy and deep, lasting odor.
Its odor has been described as sweet rosy, more honeylike and longer lasting than that of the Acetate.
Sweet, delicately green-leafy-oily odor with a fruity note. Much sweeter than the Citronellyl methyl acetal (see monograph).

Colorless mobile liquid, powerful leafygreen, fruity-rosy, fresh and light odor reminiscent of Geranium leaves, somewhat dry and honeylike undertone, There is an overall fresh-vegetable character in this odor picture
Its odor has been described as sweet-rosy, somewhat green, fresh and honeylike, longer lasting than that of the Acetate
Green-leafy, Geranium-Rose type odor, diffusive, fresh and natural. Somewhat reminiscent of Citronellyl vinyl ether
Very faint, sweet-rosy, deep and tenacious odor.
Very faint floral-rosy odor.
Powerful and moderately diffusive greenrosy, sweet Lily- Muguet-like odor. Its tenacity is comparatively good
Very faint, delicate, Rose-M uguet type odor. Somewhat more oily, also more tenacious than the aldehyde, but much weaker.
Sweet-herbaceous-rosy, yet heavy and very tenacious odor, reminiscent of the petals of roses, the waxy -honeylike, deep-sweet odor.
Fresh-fruity, sweet-rosy odor, richer, rounder than that of the acetate, also more berrYIike, fruity.
The odor has been described as freshfruity- rosy, more powerful than that of the esters of lower alifat ic acids, somewhat less sweet, more rosy, less fruity, and more tenacious.

Someu hat dry, but very ‘“natural” leafyrosy, deep and slightly floral-balsamic odor. The word “balsamic”’ should be taken as an extension of “herbaceous” in the direction of deep sweetness, resembling the undertones in Clary Sage, etc
Warm-fruity, somewhat herbaceous, slight- Iy rosy odor with undertones reminiscent of dried herbs or tobacco ]eaves, also slightly honey-like.
Warm-rosy, herbaceous, chamomile-like, tobacco-like and very tenacious odor.
Green-foliage-like, Rose-Geranium type, fresh and rather powerful odor of modest tenacity.
Fresh-herbaceous, Bergamot- and Pear-like odor, also reminiscent of Lemon and Rose. Good tenacity.
Sweet-herbaceous-fruity, somewhat gassy odor.
Powerful, yet Iight and fruity-floral odor with a peculiar “’breadlike” undertone, somewhat limiting the versatility of usage for this chemical.
Delicately sweet-animal, rather musky odor, more musky than Exaltone, but not in any way repulsive or unpleasantly animal. Extremely tenacious.
Dry-woody, spicy odor, remotely reminiscent of Ambre (the dry notes) and Leather. Good tenacity.
Sweet-balsamic, pleasantly phenolic-spicy odor, somewhat rem iniscent of the odor often encountered in “’old” iso-Eugenol. Also described as having an unmistakingly Maple-like odor, caramellic-sweet.
odorless
Sweet, herbaceous-warm, somewhat spicy odor, in extreme dilution more haylike, nut- Iike, tobacco-like.
Sweet-spicy, phenolic-leathery odor with distinctly Vanilla-1ike undertones, balsamic warm sweetness, but overall too medicinal to become classified as a versatile, floral-bal-samic ingredient.
Powerful and penetrating odor, resembling that of smoke (from wood).
Dry-tarry, medicinal-leathery odor, conventionally described as “phenolic”’.
Tarry-smoky, medicinal (“phenolic”) type odor. Strongest of the 3 isomers. In extreme dilution sweeter, almost floral, less leathery than nrem-Cresol.
Floral-herbaceous, Cananga-like odor with a green undertone.
Heavy-floral, rather pungent, Jasmin-like odor.
Heavy-floral, but rather soft and sweet odor, much less pungent than that of the -ethyiether, also more tenacious. More woody undertone.
Pungent-floral, sweet and heavy odor of leathery Cananga type
Powerful, pungent-floral, deep-sweet, warm odor, suggestive of Ylang-Ylang, Pandanus and other exotic flowers.
Peculiar metallic-green, smoky odor with oily -herbaceous undertones, remotely remi- niscent of Lily flowers.
Sweet, almost balsamic-herbaceous, slightly medicinal odor, resembling the odor of Salol
Somewhat dry-metallic, green, Narcissuslike, odor, sharper than that of the or~ho+her, and less herbaceous.
Although this ether has an overall floral fragrance, it is more earthy, and much less sweet than the paru-ether. Pungent, semi-dry, nut-like. almost mossy odor
Pungent-floral, warm, but almost “gassy” (undiluted) odor u ith earthy-WaInut-like un-dertones

Pungent, sharp-sweet odor when undiluted, Hyacinth-Wallflower-Ylang type odor when modestly diluted (concentrations below 5-6% in perfume composition), greener and more fruity when highly diluted, almost Marigold like.
Somewhat harsh-metallic, Geranium-like odor of good tenacity
Somewhat harsh-green, metallic, Geraniumlike odor, reminiscent of the odor of Diphenyl oxide.
Pow erful, heavy-floral, some~vhat green and sharp odor, reminiscent of Narcisse, Rose and OrangebIossom.
Pungent, sweet-herbaceous, slightly floral odor, remotely reminiscent of Lily and Narcissus, however, mainly anisic in type.
Powerful and pungent-floral odor of Narcissus- Ylang-Ylang type - sharper than the Cresyl ethers, but also fresher and more penetrating. Some observers find an animal note in this odor.
Pungent Lily-like odor, penetrating, floral, Narcissus-like in high dilution, Horse-like, urine-like undertones in higher concentration.
Very faint odor, somewhat sweeter than that of para-Cresylsalicy late, more floral
Herbaceous-sweet, yet somewhat pungent and very tenacious, floral-green odor with resemblance to Narcissus and with pleasant, balsamic, Ambre-bbdanum-like undertones.
Narcissus-like odor, softer and fruitier than that of the Acetate, and not at all “urine-like” in its undertones,
Pronounced Lily-Narcissus-like odor, someas a catalyst. what pungent and intense, but in proper dilution pleasant floral-oily-green Lily-Ylang-like.
Floral and somewhat indolic.Narcisse-like odor with soft and oily-herbaceous undert ones, good tenacity.
Very faint, delicately floral, sweet odor of considerable tenacity. Overall Lily-like, but mild enough to become a fixative background of other floral types, Oriental fragrances, etc.
Metallic-green, Geranium-like, moderately tenacious odor, somewhat resembling that of Diphenyloxide, yet slightly sweeter, less “cool “’.

Sweet, rather powerful floral, Narcissus-like odor of modest tenacity. The chacteristic difference between this material and the conventional Cananga-Narcisse-Lily chemicals lies mainly in the soft sweetness, the power of the ethylcarbonate without harshness, as compared to e. g. the ethylether.

Very powerful Lily-Jasmin-Lilac type odor. The herbaceous and green notes are more pronounced in this ester than in the Acetate, and the overall odor impression bears some resemblance to Lilac and Jasmin.
Mild, sweet-herbaceous. slightly green and oily odor with variable amounts of cresylic notes. most conceivably derived from impurities (decomposition ?).
See also CREOSOTE
Lily -Narcissus-YlangYlang type odor.
Rarely, if ever, offered commercially. This ester is the rarest and least useful of the three isomers.
Very tenacious Lily-Hyacinth-Jonquil type odor. The nuances in odor occur when the material is not chemically pure, e. g. from traces of Phenylacetic acid
Very faint, sweet-floral odor of considerable tenacity. Reminiscent of Rose and Narcisse with emphasis on the green-woody undertones.
Very faint floral-green, tenacious odor, reminiscent of Narcissus, Hyacinth, etc. but more delicate than the conventional para- Cresyl esters.
Herbaceous-green, warm and somewhat tobacco-like or honeylike odor, yet not distinctly sweet, rather caramellic.
Animal-floral odor, sometimes described as musky.
Tobacco-like, animal, sweet-herbaceous odor with undertones resembling Civet.
Soft, floral-green, almost herbaceous-green odor, not unlike the lower ‘.ca(binols” ( Dimethyl benzyl carbinol, etc. ) but overall sharper, lighter, fresher.

This material is comparatively toxic, irritant and a pronounced Iachrymator. Its odor and flavor suggests a use similar to that of common (Allyl-)Mustard oil, and the material finds some use as a modifier of imitation Radish and Garlic flavors.
Balsamic-herbaceous, warm odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm, oily-herbaceous, winey odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm and very sweet, Honey-Tobacco-like odor with warm, herbaceous undertones.
Pungent, slightly green-sharp, kerosene-like odor of poor tenacity.
When absolutely pure, the material is virtually odorless, but the scarce commercial lots have shown a distinctly herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity,
Oily-spicy odor, suggestive of Dillseed or Caraway, but not pungent or sharp like Carvone.

Pungent, green-herbaceous odor with notes of animal and vegetable character at the same time. Generally described as “unpleasant” in high concentration. At concentrations well below 1% the odor appears more attractive, warm-spicy, still vegetable, condiment-picklelike.
Mild, oily-green, herbaceous-winey odor.
Herbaceous-sweet- very tenacious odor. In dilution reminiscent of Mandarin peel oil, but overall rather sharp and not as .’Orangeblossom”-- like as most of the conventional Schiff”s bases
Very faint, green-woody-spicy odor, resembling sap from wood, yet overall dry.
Refreshing-herbaceous, sweet and delicately woody odor of moderate tenacity.
Diffusive and powerful floral-green floralstem like odor with pronounced vegetable, Cucumber-Melon-like notes. Overall resembling the odor of Lindenblossom.
Intensely sweet, fresh-floral odor of great tenacity, somewhat reminiscent of the flowers of the Lemon tree.
different odors.

Powerful, and diffusive, foliage-green, “dark’’-weedy and dry odor, sometimes described as “’F1ower-shop odor”. The earthy and wet-g em notes are quite natural in high dilution and resemble the odor of stems from plants and flowers fresh from the soil.
Mild floral-woody, somewhat oily-herbaceous odor, remotely reminiscent of Rose with similarity to the odor of hydrogenated Ionones.
Sweet-woody, rather heavy odor, resembling that of bera-Ionone. More fruity than really floral, but not as tenacious as the Ionone,
Sweet herbaceous-woody, quite powerful odor with some resemblance to the odor of bera-Ionone. More diffusive, less tenacious, and not quite as floral.
The odor varies according to isomer ratio, but can generally be classified as warm, Violetlike, sweet, yet somewhat powdery and very tenacious.
The odor of Ionones and their homologies is a subject generally avoided in written publications.
Soft, floral, sweet odor of rather poor tenacity. In the author’s opinion, it is not nearly as useful as Geraniol, although it cannot be compared to Geraniol as any sort of a substitute
Rather minty, fresh and slightly green odor, reminiscent of that of Pulegol, but more Eucalyptus-like, cool, and not very floral. Diffusive and not very tenacious.
Green-camphoraceous odor, both reminiscent of Ionones, but overall sharper, less sweet.
Tenacious, woody-musky. but rather weak odor, not as sweet as Cyclopentadecanone, but more resembling Cyclohexadecanone.
Tenacious animal, mostly musk-like odor, more woody and less sweet than Cyclopentadecanone (“Exahone”’ ).
Rather sharp-acetic odor, not very characteristic.
Bitter-almond-like, pungent odor with some resemblance to Nitrobenzene.
Damp-earthy, camphoraceous-minty, Walnut- Vetiver-Oakmoss-like, relatively powerful odor of moderate tenacity
Practically odorless.
Warm-camphoraceous odor.
Powerful, mint y-camphoraceous, “cool” and “solvent-like” odor, generally described as “unpleasant” (by non-professionals).
Powerful and diffusive, somewhat gassyminty odor, often deseribed as “industrial” or “chemical”.
Commercial grades of this ketone have an odor which is most often described as “Urinelike’”. It is somewhat ethereal, sweet-solventlike, Acetone-like in purer grade material.
Refreshing green-floral odor of poor tenacity. Mild, yet quite diffusive, overall more sweet-floral than Cyclohexenyl acetaldehyde.
Sweet-fruit y, but rather chemical odor. Often described as similar to Amylacetate, but the odor of Cyclohexyl acetate is sharper, less “candy-like”, less ““natural”’.
Faint, fruity -Orangeblossom-type odor of good tenacity.
Mild, faint, warm-balsamic, floral and somewhat herbaceous odor of good tenacity. The hcrbaceous notes appear as undertones barely perceptible except in compositions with other materials.
Overall fruity, but has a nondescript floral note, remotely reminiscent of Phenoxyethyl isobutyrate. The Cyclohexyl butyratc is, however, much more powerful in its odor, and less tenacious.
Powerful, sweet-fruity odor, more etherealdiffusive than Amyl acetate, sweeter, but overall resembling that esler in odor. The background appears almost Oriental-animal or Ambra-like.
Fruity-winey, but somewhat “’metallic” odor of considerable tenacity. Overall resemblance to Pineapple-fruity odors

Sweet-balsamic, somewhat Almond-like and very tenacious odor. The “Almond-like” note resembles that of Heliotropyl esters with a touch of Bmtzaldehyde-note. The balsamic note resembles that of Benzyl cinnamate.
Woody-camphoraceous, slightly minty and rosy odor, but overall dry and rather “chemical”.
Herbaceous-minty, comparatively sweet odor, overall pleasant and of great tenacity
Woody-camphoraceous, faintly herbaceous, but rather dry odor.
Dry-camphoraceous odor with some (but not much) resemblance to Rose and Patchouli notes.
Very slightly soluble in water, miscible with alcohol and oils. Sweet-fruity, fruit-preserverlike odor.
Oily -herbaceous, grassy and slightly fatty, overall not very pleasant odor.
