Powerful and diffusive, refreshing, sweetfloral odor of poor tenacity. It has been classified as “nondescript” and it is true that the material has an odor which is difficult to describe, but it should not be understood as ‘“bland” or “mild”.
Pronounced fruity and somewhat floral (Jasmin) odor. Overall sweeter and more tenacious than Benzyl acetate.
Musty-camphoraceous, slightly minty odor, remotely reminiscent of part of the Patchouli odor-picture.
Delicately fruity, Pineapple-Apricot-like odor of good tenacity. Tealike, almost Clary Sage-like undertones.
Fruity, slightly oily, bitter-sharp, rather pungent odor with a pleasant herbaceouswiney undertone.
Fruity -herbaceous, berry-like, slightly camphoraceous odor reminiscent of notes in Geranium and Lavender.
Almost odorless as such, but introduces a mild-herbaceous odor in compositions.
Faint, but tenacious, oily-fruity odor with a green-winey undertone.
Herbaceous-green, very tenacious odor with  sweet-honey-waxy and somewhat Chrysanthe- mum-like notes.
Very mild-balsamic. floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very mild, sweet -balsamic, but rather “flat” odor of moderate to poor tenacity. It is less floral than Hydrocinnamic alcohol, and does not have the rosy character of that material
Intensely fruit y and sweet odor, somewhat reminiscent of Banana, Pineapple and Peach. Not very tenacious.
Mild and agreeable, slightly fruity and sweet odor.
Fruity, slightly animal, deep-herbaceous odor
Fruity odor, but less animal than that of the n-Valerate. Tenacious and sweet, more versatile than the n-Valerate.
Powerful, sweet-Ambregis type odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Weak, musky odor
Delicately animal, musky and sweet, extremely tenacious odor of outstanding uniformity.
Musky, somewhat animal odor, much weaker than that of Cyclopentadecanolide.
Powerful musky odor, very similar to that of MuScone (Methylcyclopentadecanone) and, in the opinion of many perfumers, superior in type and beauty.
Diffusive, gassy, woody, musty odor. Genera[ ly described as unpleasant “industrial”.
Powerful, sweet-herbaceous, diffusive odor of relatively poor tenacity. In high concentration rather gassy and not very pleasant, it develops sweet and agreeable notes upon dilution.
Woody, rather dry odor. Only in extreme dilution will a musky odor appear clearly
Pleasant, mild-piney, camphoraceouswoody odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Miid, ethereal-piney, sweet-camphoraceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Commercial grades display a typical “gassy’’- kerosenlikeke odor, while highly purified material smells more citrusy, reminiscent of Lemon and Bergamot topnotes, having more freshness.

Extremely powerful, Orange-1ike, sweet and fresh-citrusy odor, diffusive, yet quite tenacious. The Orange character is more attractive and natural at dilutions below 0.1 ~0, while higher concentrations display fatty-green notes.
Fatty, but sweet and very tenacious odor with a pleasant fruity freshness in extreme dilution.
Oily, but fresh and citrusy odor, somewhat reminiscent of Linalool, but overall of Orange- Bitter Orange, Grapefruit-character.
Peculiar dry, musty, powerful odor, reminiscent of certain notes in Ambergris.
Mild, sweet, slightly camphoraceous-woody, also warm and mildly spicy odor of fair tenacity. The odor has been compared to that of Dihydrocarveol, but such description does not help many perfumers,
Semi-dry, musty-woody odor with a remote resemblance to notes in Ambergris. However, the olfactory picture is very incomplete and the tenacity very poor - compared to Ambergris products.
Sweet-fruity, slightly oily and floral odor of Jasmin type.

Sweet-woody, musty and slightly green odor of moderate tenacity. The Sandalwood-like notes, for which this ester is still appreciated, appear most conspicuously in dilutions of less than 10% of this ester with significant amounts of mild, sweet and woody blenders.
Refined, oily-peachy and extraordinarily tenacious odor. More Peach-like, less Nut-like than Nonanolide-1,4.

Very powerful and very tenacious, sweet creamy, Nut-1ike odor with a heavy fruity undertone. The undiluted material displays a rather coumarinic sharpness in its topnote, but at concentrations of O.10; or lower, it seems to grow in volume, sweetness and oilycreamy softness.
Semi-dry, tenacious odor resembling part of the Ambregris-picture, also woody, remotely reminiscent of Sandalwood. Odor variations are observed in materials from different sources of supply.
Mild, sweet and faintly musky odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet and rather fresh, musky odor of good tenacity.
Penetrating and very powerful, sweet-waxy, Orange-peel-like odor. In extreme dilution refreshing, Citrus-peel-like.
Fresh-citrusy, green-oily odor with more or less pronounced aldehydic undertone, according to the chemical purity of the Acetal.
Green-fruity, Citrus-waxy odor.
Powerful odor, mainly of Orangeblossomtype, overall floral, but with perceptible notes from the parent materials. Very tenacious.
Very faint, sweet-musty odor.

Woody-camphoraceous, but also floral odor of good tenacity. The odor may appear sweet to some observers, rather dry to others. It is conceivable that the commercial material, only occasionally offered, is not a pure, single chemical.
Powerful, somewhat musty-fatty, Walnutlike odor, with a vague resemblance to alifatic Aldehydes in its diffusive power and radiant odor.
Rather unpleasant, sour-fatty, “rancid” odor.
Sweet, slightly fatty-oily odor, waxy and floral, mainly rosy, also reminiscent of Lily and Orangeblossom, but fresher, in the same way as CitroneIlol is fresh.
Very powerful, waxy-Orange-like, sweet- “aldehydic” odor of fair tenacity and high diffusive power.
Powerful, waxy-harsh odor when undiluted, almost Stearin-like unpleasant fatty. Sweet, refreshingly fruit y and slightly oily-waxy

Powerful, fatty-oily, waxy-rosy odor of considerable tenacity. The rosy notes are particularly conspicuous in dilutions, best at 1% or lower, while higher concentrations bring about more waxy-oily notes.
Powerful and very diffusive, fatty-buttey, oily-Nut-like odor of considerable tenacity. Sweeter and less fatty than Decalactone.
Pleasant, oily-rosy, Rose-petal-like odor of considerable diffusive power and tenacity.
Delicately floral-oily, sweet and slightly fruity odor with rosy overtones and ~soft, but tenacious Ambrette-seed-like background.
Sweet fatty-fruity odor of Pineapple-Orange- like character, and rosy waxy undertones.
Fresh-citrusy, rosy-sweet odor, somewhat reminiscent of Linalyl acetate, not quite as sweet, and rather fresher.
Very tenacious, but comparatively mild, herbaceous-earthy odor with a musky note.
Sweet, oily-fruity, Apricot-like taste with a slightly floral note. In spite of apparent power, its taste is rather bland, nondescript fruit>.
Mild, oily-herbaceous odor of good tenacity
Fresh-unctuous odor with undertones.
Weak, oily, sweet-fatty, remotely fruity and very tenacious odor.
Oily-herbaceous, sweet odor with some resemblance to Opopanax and Heracleum fruits
Almost odorless when pure, but is capable of introducing pleasant oily -herbaceous and very tenacious notes in compositions
Mild, oily-ethereal, faintly herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Faint, oily-rosy odor of considerable tenacity. The odor of the undiluted material is not really pleasant, but the effect of the Decylether in perfume compositions can be quite attractive.
Light, fruity, almost sharp odor with floral, Honey suckle-Orangeblossom character. Its floral notes are accompanied by a heavy proportion of leafy, deep-green notes.
Powerful, floral-green, very diffusive, yet tenacious odor, reminiscent of Rose petals, Lily, Muguet, Peony, etc., but overall greener than the straight florals.
Very mild, oily-waxy odor. Virtually odorless when pure
Orange-like, oily-fruity, also floral andwiney, Grape-like odor of good tenacity.
Mild, sweet and very tenacious floral odor, remotely reminiscent of Rose or Peony, but with somewhat herbaceous undertone.
Fatty -aldehydic, musky, sweet and pleasant odor, somewhat reminismnt of certain notes in Ambrette seed.
Warm-herbaceous, somewhat winey-caramellic odor of modest tenacity.
Faint, fresh-oily odor. This could possibly be notes from traces of surplus Decanol in the ester.
Ethereal, oily-fruity, faintly Apple-like odor, also reminiscent of the fatty notes in Pineapple.
Refreshing, citrusy-waxy, light and floral (mainly rosy) fragrance of moderate tenacityj but good radiation.
Very powerful, sweet, green-floral and somewhat tobacco-herbaceous odor of good tenacity. In extreme dilution reminiscent of the odor of Safran (Saffron).
This chemical constitutes a trace impurity in commercial lots of synthetic Linalool
Mainly used as a solvent in flavor compositions. Practically no use in perfumery.
Very powerful and diffusive, pungent, buttery odor. Chlorine-Quinone-like in high concentration, oily-buttery in extreme dilution.
used in flavors
Pungent odor, not truly reminiscent of Garlic, but heavier, more “sulfide-like”, obnoxious odor.
Pungent odor, reminiscent of Radish
Powerful, penetrating Garlic-Radish-like odor of poor tenacity. Not a lachrymator, but does produce some irritation of eyes and mucous membranes.
Ethereal, but not winey, rather solvent-like, unnatural odor with sweet undertone of re-motely fruity character.
Powerful and diffusive odor with peculiar dry-floral, almost tarry-medicinal odor in high concentration, pleasant floral and almost sweet in extreme dilution.
Faint, sweet odor of Anisaldehyde character, but much weaker. Certain commercial lots have “Almond” odor,
Sweet, but rathtr faint, fruity -almondy odor of considerable tenacity
Swset, floral-animal, musky typs of odor wi:h good tsnacity, Harsher and less tenacious than .Musk Ambrette and Musk Ketone, but has an ov:rall resemblance to the Nitromusks.
Oilyj Coconut-buttery odor of considerable tenacity. In suitable dilution (best about 5 ppm in sweetened milk) it displays a pleasant creamy-Coconut-like taste.
It is described as having a Geranium-Rose type odor.
The above chemical is desmibsd as having a Geranium-Rose type odor with a Honeylike note
Sweet-herbaceous, warm and fungoid, but pleasant odor of moderate tenacity.
Oily fruily, somew hat harsh odor u ith some resemblance to Banana and Passionfruit.
pleasant Ambre-musky type of odor itself
Sweet Oakmoss-like penetrating odor with floral undertones.
Fruity, but very mild and oily odor of considerable tenacity. To some people it appears vifiually odorless.
Very useful as a natural green topnote in Geranium and Violet bases.
Oily-sweet, buttery taste, often with a slightly cheesy note.
Sharp and pungent, fruity-buttery odor, sharper, fruitier and sweeter than that of the Di-n-butyryl, not as cheese-like.
Extremely powerful, diffusive, gassy-fruity odor. In very high dilution pleasantly Applelike with a rose-like sweetness.
Penetrating and repulsive “Skunk” odor.
Sweet, mild-aromatic, but rather “chemical” odor.
Sweet ethereal odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Its fruity notes are pleasant, but not characteristic of any particular fruit.
Very powerful and diffusive, fresh, vegetable-green odor, sometimes classified as “’Ozone-like”’ or Melon-like. Its odor has also been compared to that of fresh sap from wood or bark
Sweet and rather mild Bitter-Almond type odor with herbaceous-haylike undertone.
Green-floral, slightly oily and rather heavyodor of good tenacity.
In any event, this chemical is included in the present work in order to describe one rare group of chemicals of possible interest to the perfumer.
Camphoraceous-rosy, rather faint odor. overalI more crude and harsh than that of Citronellol.
Quite powerful, fruity, Pear-like odor.
This chemical serves mostly as a solvent for perfume materials, but it is not quite odorless and therefore not as desirable as Diethylphthalate. Toxic
Faint, ethereal odor with a musty undertone,
Faint, rather dry-musty, somewhat ethereal odor, not exactly pleasant.
Very diffusive, sweet-ethereal odor. Actually a poor odorant, it gives impression of power by its very high vapor pressure at room temperature
Very faint, winey-ethereal odor.
Mild, winey-fruity odor with a pleasant oily-herbaceous undertone, overall reminiscent of the odor of Apple skins (peel).
Presumably not usedin perfume compositions.
Sweet, soft and pleasant fruity-green, slightly balsamic odor, reminiscent of Apples.
Pleasant, light, ethereal odor of good diffusive action and poor tenacity.
Weak, somewhat musky odor, slightly herbaceous and Mushroom-like.
\’irtually odorless when pure
Faint, but pleasant, winey-fruity odor, resembling that of Quince and Melon.

Faint, pleasant odor, remotely winey-ethereal. The odor type is somewhat similar to that of Ethyl benzoate, but of much less power. Burning taste in high concentration, mildly tart-fruity upon dilution.
Very faint, winey odor.
Powerful and diffusive, sweet-herbaceous, caramellic odor of very poor tenacity
Powerful, repulsively sulfuraceous (sulfidelike) odor, only in extreme dilution becoming Company, Organic attractive, caramellic-burnt, “roasted” odor.
Peculiar fatty “’wet wool” odor, with notes often described as “metallic”.

Powerful “gassy’’-green, rat hcr choking odor, in high concentration almost cabbagelik~ but not sulfuraceous. At proper dilution, the odor has some similarity to the odor of Orange leaf (or Bitter Orange leaf water oil).
It has warm, herbaceous-winey, slightly green and quite tenacious odor of versatile use in perfumesy.

Peculiar, wartn-herbaceous-floral odor with a woody undertone. The odor has sometimes been compared to that of the “Strawberrytree” (Mediterranean Arbutus), at other times it seems that the observer has great difficulties in describing the odor in common terms.

Typical musky, sweet odor of great tenacity and fixative power. When compared to Ambrettolide, the DHA is less floral, somewhat weaker and lacks the radiant beauty of the.4mbrettolide. The animal notes are slightly more perceptible in the DHA, and it should not be considered as a cheaper replacement for .4mbrettolide.

Sweet-herbaceous, quite powerful odor, less candylike and more dry, almost woody, as compared to Anethole. The overall impression is that of a ‘-clean” odor, not as “round” and “full”” as Anethole, yet overall ‘“anisic” of type.
Very powerful, warm-spicy-herbaceous and sweet odor of excellent tenacity.

The dexrro-isomer has a woody-floral odor, somewhat sickening-swmt, while the luevoisomer is rather unpleasant, slightly gassy, rather nauseating-animal, resembling the odor of Chenopodium (Wormseed) oil
Warm-herbaceous, powerful and diffusive odor, similar to that of laevo-Carvone, but slightly milder, less pungent, sweeter and in dilution less “’medicinal”.
Sweet, slightly minty, floral, rosy odor with a herbal undertone.
Peculiar dry-musty, almost Ambergris-like odor of excellent tenacity.
Rather sharp, minty and “terpeney”’ odor, not exactly pleasant.
Powerful, fresh-green lemony-sharp odor with a floral, Lime-like note.
Fresh, rosy-green, foliage-type, slightly floral odor with ethereal notes
Faint, animal-musky odor, sweet, and slightly woody with good tenacity. Compared to Civettone. the DHC is considerably weaker and less characteristic “clean-animal-musky” in its overall performance.
Sweet-herbaceous, nutlike, haylike odor, usually described as “coumannic” or “tobacco- like”.
Warm-herbaceous, spicy odor, suggestive of Dill and Spearmint, but with a very diffusive and refreshing, almost fruity note
Woody-minty, sIightIy oiIy, but not very sweet taste. Very powerful.
Powerful fatty-spicy, oily -herbaceous odor, reminiscent of Dill, Cumin and Gingergrass (green-oily, weedy notes).
Practically odorless.
Camphor-like, cool-herbaceous odor.
Weak, woody-floral odor with camphoraceous undertone.
Mild, oily-rosy, fruity and somewhat green odor. Much weaker than Geranylacetate, and not as Apple-like.
Mild and relatively sweet woody -piney odor of moderate tenacity.
Refreshing light, woody-piney odor with mildly herbaceous-fruity undertones.
Warm-spicy, sweet and slightly floral-balsamic odor, reminiscent of Eugenol, but milder and sweeter than this
Sweet and mildly floral odor with a soft, woody undertone and good tenacity. The odor is even milder than that of Famesol, and the tenacity is poorer.
not a well-defined perfume chemical.
Woody and slightly floral odor, considerably weaker than the odor of alpha- and bera- Ionones.
Rather ‘thin” oily-woody odor, somewhat “’gassy’” and weaker than alpha-lonone with respect to Violet-note.
Of little or no interest to the perfumer.

The most appreciated odor type is that of Ambregris, and the title material is normally described as having such odor type. A general odor descnpt ion of Dihydro-gamma-i on one is therefore of little value
From an odor point of view, they are rather disappointing, being weaker or milder than alpha-lonone and resembling that ketone in character.
Dry and rather hard odor, generally considered undesirable, yet reminiscent of bera- Ionone in overall type.
it has failed to interest the perfumers, partly because it is very unstable, partly because it seems to be difficult to produce in a pure state and consistent quality.
Intensely floral and fresh odor with fruity and somewhat Myrrh-like undertone.
The odor is mere fruity, less floral than that of Dihydro jasmone

Heavy floral, but also fatty (Coconut-fatty) and waxy odor. The floral notes resemble those of Gardenia (undertones) and Tuberose, but the beauty of these notes is somewhat marred by the interference of fatty notes.
Refreshing herbaceous-minty, also Pulegollike, Lavender type odor of moderate tenacity
Pleasant and refreshing, Lavender-Lavandin- type note. Not as sweet as Linalylacetate. More woody and mildly camphoraceous. Richer and more tenacious than Linalyl acetate.

Powerful, herbaceous-resinous, slightly minty odor with woody-Lavender-like undertone and moderate to poor tenacity. It is quite possible that the “’vamishy” or “resinous” notes derive from Mymene-denvatives as trace components from the process.
Comparatively powerful, fresh-floral, citrusy (with emphasis on Lime) and diffusive odor. Less woody than LinaIooI, more powerful and more Lime-like than Tetrahydro Iinalool.
Mild, oily-woody odor of alpha-Methyl ionone type, but much weaker.
Warm, bu~ rather dry Ambre-gris type odor of good tenacity. The woody and delicately d~ notes of deltu-Methylionone are further refined, but appear less woody, more Ambregris- like.
Refreshing and powerful, green-leafy, rosy and sweet odor with a sweet-caramellic, in high concentrations almost “burnt” note, but in dilution pleasantly sweet, slightly fruity.
Powerful, fresh Lime-like, overall citrusy - floral and sweet odor with little or no terpenic undertones.
Sweet, spicy-herbaceous, fresh and somewhat fruity odor with Bergamot-Lime character. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful herbaceous-green and fresh-woody odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet, honey-tobacco-like odor with warmherbaceous undertones. Overall milder, sweeter and less harsh than iso-Phorone.
Sweet, root-like, floral-anisic odor, warm and somewhat spicy. Weaker than Safrole, often described as “less sassafrassy”.
The odor is generally described as “floral, heavy, sweet and tenacious”, but there seems to be some difficulty in obtaining samples of identical odor from various suppliers.
Pleasant, floral, Lilac-type odor, softer, yet richer than Terpineol, not quite as lasting.

Fresh-piney, citrusy and somewhat hcrbaceous odor. Sweeter and fruitier than Terpinyl acetate, the Dihydro terpinylacetate seems to be cool and warm at the same time (minty-camphoraceous, herbaceous). Its tenacity is not very outstanding.
Not a perfume chemical
Faint, musty -vinous odor
Sweet, diffusive, somewhat ‘“gassy” odor.
Very faint, warm-woody odor. The effect is, however, quite perceptible when this material is used in combination with lower boiling fragrance materials.
Very faint, u arm-camphoraceous and woody odor. When compared to Dill-apiole, it is more camphoraceous than that.
Sweet and faintly Bitter-almond-like balsamic odor of good tenacity.
Sweet-woody, very tenacious odor with a pleasant, floral undertone.
V.e.ry faint, sweet-herbaceous odor with a nuthke, oily-sweet unrJertone
Warm-spicy, sweet, almost balsamic-woody odor with rich, sweet and slightly nutlike, long lasting undertones.
Sweet-balsamic, slightly animal and heavy odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and warm-floral odor of balsamic- Vanilla-like character and excellent tenacity
Sweet-floral, woody odor, rather pungent in the pure state, but almost Mimosa-like in extreme dilution or in proper composition with other perfume chemicals.
Powerful and very diffusive, penetrating “gassy” odor of green-ethereal character. Very poor tenacity.
Sharp, green-oily, somewhat ““gassy’”odor. When properly diluted, it displays rather pleasant, winey-fermentation-like notes

Powerful and relatively diffusive, fruity- floral odor of Pineapple-Jasmin character. The fruity notes are refreshingly green, without being sharp, the floral notes are intense and sweet, yet very fresh and lively.
Mild ‘“Bitter-Almond+’ type odor, weaker and sweeter than that of Benzaldehyde, some- what floral and more stable towards oxidation.
Powerful, sweet-floral, rather fresh and somewhat fruit y odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous-floral, slightly animal odor, reminiscent of Lilac and Eldcrflowers with undertones of fresh cut wood
Warm, woody-rosy odor of moderate to good tenacity. When used with sweeter materials, it produces very pleasant, rich, mellow rose notes and “’depth”’ of warm undertones.
Fresh and powerful, floral-fruity, slightly herbaceous odor of Jasmin-Lily type.
Mild-herbaceous, fruity odor in the Plum/ Prune type. The undertones in a good-quality, acid-free ester are extremely pleasant, tea-like, warm and sweet.
The odor is slightly fresher (less “heavy”) than that of the n-Butyrate, less warm, more “chemical”, but also more stable than the normal ester
Dry, herbaceous-green, Narcissus-Lily -Jasmin type of odor. Rather pungent in its green notes, but not unpleasant.
Sweet-floral, fruity odor of good tenacity
Moderately powerful, sweet-green, leafy odor of mediocre tenacity.
Sweet, musky and nut-like, Hazelnut- Coconut type odor with discrete animal undertones, resembling certain notes in Musk, Civet and Castoreum, pleasantly free from any trace of faecal notes
Very diffusive, ethereal odor of poor tenacity. The sweetness resembles that of Acetone, but is not nearly as choking.
Somewhat dry, camphoraceous-rosy odor, vaguely reminiscent of the odor of Citronellol.
Powerful, herbaceous, somewhat weedy, but basically sweet odor of moderate tenacity
Sweet-fruity-woody odor, but somewhat drier than that of the 2,3-isomer (see previous monograph). Moderate tenacity and pleasant terminal notes reminiscent of refined, sweetwoody Oakmoss notes.
Sweet, fruity-woody odor of moderate tenacity. The fruity notes are rather ethereal or winey, while the woody notes are sweet and remo[ely resembling those of alpha-Ionone, jet not as powerful.
Sweet and lemony odor, not nearly as sharp as Citral, and much more tenacious.
Semi-sweet, oily-rosy odor, more waxy than that of Citronellol, more tenacious, but also somewhat drier.
This material, which is not yet commercially available (Sept. 1968) appears to be a very promising new type musk.
Intensely onionlike, very diffusive odor.
Intensely waxy, dry-floral odor, almost typical of the term ‘“aldehydic” and even drier than the odor of Methyl nonyl acetaldehyde.
Nauseating, Camphor-like odor, also slightly cool, minty, diffusive.
Sweet, somewhat woody-rosy odor with resemblance to the odor of distilled tail fractions rom Geraniol, yet not as tenacious.
Oily-green, powerful and sweet odor. Less Cucumber-like and more floral than the “Violet leaf alcohol”, also sweeter.
Very powerful, oily-green, vegetable-like odor, reminiscent of Melon-skins (outer peel of Melon). In extreme dilution sweeter, more typical Melon-like, refreshing.
Sweet and refreshing floral odor with discretely woody-herbaceous or mildly balsamic notes. Very suggestive of Lavender/Clary Sage.
Sweet, herbaceous-spicy, mildly balsamic odor of moderate tenacity. The spicy balsamic notes have some resemblance to OPopanax.

Its peculiar fruity -resinous-balsamic sweet-ness is quite characteristic of this series of esters, and it makes them suitable for Oriental fragrance creations with Opopanax, Labda-)(num, Patchouli, etc.
Fresh, citrusy-herbaeeous, balsamic-green odor of moderate tenacity.

Sweet, fruity -balsamic, mildly spicy odor of good tenacity. The balsamic notes have the same resinous sweetness as encountered in the acetate, but the fruity-bakamic character is generally emphasized in this ester.
Faint, camphorlike odor.
Powerful and, when undiluted, pungent, fatty-oily odor, in dilution more pleasant, almost fruity, herbaceous-Orange-like but with rather poor tenacity.
Peculiar musky-woody odor with initial notes of rather harsh-chemical character
Powerful green-ornsy, slightly woody odor. Rather dry without being pronounced camphoraceous.
Musky-ornsy odor, somewhat sweeter than that of the 2,2-Dimethylderivative, and less camphoraceous.
Sweet-eafihy, somewhat green-musty, also floral-ornsy odor with some resemblance to Vetiver.
Overall woody, orrisy with only a slight camphoraceous note, and with a peculiar fruity undertone that makes this derivative different from the other isomers.
Very powerful, warm-herbaceous odor, often classified as Celery-like, but only pleasant in extreme dilution.
Intensely caramellic-fruity, ‘-jam-like”’ odor with some resemblance to the odor of Palatone (Maltol). The odor is also reminiscent of that of “cooked Pineapple’”.
In extreme dilution of rather pleasant, sweet-floral odor, this Amine has only little of the “faecal” character commonly found in commercial grade Skatole (be?a-Methylindole).
e. g. in the reconstruction of certain Citrus oils.
Sweet-camphoraceous, warm and soft odor with a woody undertone. Upon standing, it may develop an odor resembling that of Celluloid.
Mild and sweet-woody odor with a floralpiney undertone
Refreshing and sweet, floral odor of moderate tenacity. The floral notes are accompanied by delicately citrusy notes resembling part of the lily odor complex.
Powerful, fresh, sweet and diffusive odor reminiscent of fruits and vegetables, greener and less fatty than DeCanal.
Waxy, dry-rosy odor.
Sweet floral-fruity, somewhat honey-waxy odor. Overall a pleasant and natural odor. Only its typical rosy notes prevent its wider application.
Deep-sweet, rosy-tobacco-like odor with a faintly honey-like, floral undenone, the floral notes resembling the undertones in Jasmin.
Sweet and rosy, oily odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Less “waxy” than the odor of Dimethyloctanol (“’DMO”), but “fattier”’ and less tenacious, and with more initial power.
Sweet rosy-fruity odor with an oily-fruity undertone and moderate tenacity. The oily notes of the title material are not as typically Apple-like as those of Geranyl acetate.
Powerful green, but sweet and slightly floral odor of moderate tenacity
Mild and delicately green-floral, sweet and tenacious odor.
Sharp-herbaceous, remotely Geranium-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The odor is sweeter than that of Allyl phenyl ether

Rosy-woody odor, somewhat fattier than that of Phenylethyl alcohol, and with a pleasant green-woody undertone. Overall drier and less floral than D. M. P.E.C. and much less green than Methyl phenyl carbinol.

Useful in perfumery for Clary Sage variations in Fougeres, Chypres, Lavender compositions, and as a green-floral undertone and variant in Gardenia or Tuberose. It blends well with Dime[hylbenzylcarbinol for Elderflower notes (“sureau”) and builds good undertones in a Honeysuckle, etc.
Sweet-fruity, heavy, Apricot-Peach-Plum- Iike odor with a rather dry, woody-green undenone.

Soft, floral-green, mildly herbaceous and oily odor reminiscent of Lily and Hyacinth, but Mith an unusual mildness in spite of great tenacity. Probably the most valuable and versatile of all the so-called “carbinols”.
Fresh and rosy, slightly leafy-fruity and tenacious odor. Overall floral in the Rose-Hyacinth-Jasmin type with a balsamic under- tone of pleasant softness.
Sweet-herbaceous, Tea-1ike and Clary-Sage-Iike odor of great tenacity and very pleasant overall character. The undertones are slightly fruity and tobacco-like, giving a very “’natural” impression.
Peculiar fruity-juicy, Tea-like and herbaceous, richly sweet odor, overall refreshing and somewhat reminiscent of the odor of Carob beans - without the cheesy notes of that material.
Dry, floral-rosy odor with emphasis upon Rose-foliage notes.
Sweet, fruity -herbaceous MirabeUe-like odor (sweet, non-almondy Cherry type of odor).
Green-floral, very “juicy” odor of remarkable “naturalness” and complexity.
Dry-woody-rosy odor of fair tenacity. Powerful, but displays some camphoraceousness in its overtones, partly ruining the fragrance picture.
Very faint, ethereal odor. It has been claimed that the material is virtually odorless, but that it hydrolyzes easily, producing a faint odor of Methanol.
Dry-musty, woody and very tenacious odor of some similarity to the dry notes in Ambregris.
Powerful and very dry, musty-woody odor of similarity to the dry notes of Ambregris. In proper dilution, the dry notes become more pleasant,
Pou’erful, tenacious and warm, spicy herbaceous odor, often compared to that of Safran (Saffron). The author finds more resemblance to Oakmoss.
This material is held chiefly responsible for the typical flavor of Potato
sweet, “fried” odor, resembling that of fried Potatoes, but not as typical as that of the 2,5-isomer
Apparently a result from research on Oakmoss chemicals, this Alkoxyaldehyde has only a faint, sweet Nut-like and remotely floral odor of considerable tenacity; remotely reminiscent of Heliotrope.
Pleasant and mild-ethereal-fruity odor
Pleasant ethereal-winey, dry-green, slightly fruity odor.
Extremely diffusive, repulsive odor, reminiscent of wild Radish, sharp, green, Cabbagelike. Only in very high dilution it becomes bearable and almost acceptable, pleasant, vegetable-like.

Pow erful, green and rather dry-waxy, but in dilution very refreshing odor of moderate tenacity. It lacks natural character, but is rarely used as the ‘“only aldehydic” component of any refreshing topnote or Aldehyde note.
SWeet-camphoraceous, heavy -anisic or Sassafras-like herbaceous odor with pronounced musky-animal undertones and considerable tenacity.
Powerful and penetrating Onion-like odcr, in extreme dilution almost pleasantly green. Vegetable-leafy and sweet.
Sweet and floral, rather pungent odor, in dilution with balsamic undertones, more woody-floral, moderately tenacious.
Sweet and tenacious odor resembling that of Musk Ketone, but somewhat sharper yet not quite as powerful.
Sweet musky odor, reminiscent of Musk Xylol, but not quite as harsh, and not quite as strong.
The odor of this Nitromusk resembles that of the previous musk (Musk Aldehyde).
Sweet and tenacious musky odor. The type is inbetween Musk Ambrette and Musk Ke-tone, but weaker than both.
Powerful minty, somewhat Tea-like, herbaceous odor
Very sweet, mild-ethereal odor.
Powerful and refreshing, green-lemony, herbal odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Faint and sweet-herbaceous, slightly woodytobacco-like odor, reminiscent of the odor of Coumarin, but much weaker.

Very dry, tarry-smokey odor of considerable tenacity. Upon dilution it develops a sweeter and much more pleasant mossy-dry odor of considerable resemblance to notes in certain types of Oakmoss extract.
Pure Dipentene smells pleasantly citrusy, almost Lemon-like, fresh and sweet.
Very mild, sweet, balsamic-floral odor of moderate tenacity.

Powerful and penetrating, but sweet and in extreme dilution pleasant-green foliage odor. The concentrated material is difficult to evaluate because of its repulsively strong odor. Upon dilution the herbaceous character seems to increase, finally turning greener, earthyvegetable- like just before the point of minimum perceptible.
Peculiar odor, gassy-green, remotely reminiscent of Geranium, but overall mild and rather nondescript, choking in high concentration, sometimss described as “metallic” odor
The pure material has a faint, sweet, floral odor, but most commercial lots display a “chemical” note, varying from gassy to fishy.
Mild, rather sweet odor of metallic-green Geranium type, not very natural, but quite pleasant in dilution. Tenacious.
Harsh Geranium-leaf, Orange-blossom type odor. More pleasant and less “metallic” when diluted.
Harsh floral-green, metallic Geranium type odor
Practically odorless,
Practical] y odorless.
Pungent buttery odor, not as diffusive or penetrating as Diacetyl, but resembling that.
Sweet, herbaceous-winey odor, often described as resembling that of Ambrette seed.
Sweet-herbaceous, slightly woody odor, often described as resembling that of Ambrette seed. Moderate to good tenacity.
Powerful fruity-floral odor of Jasmin type. Fair to good tenacity.
Pungent and rather harsh, but in proper dilution floral and pleasantly green odor.
Sweet, floral-musky odor of good tenacity. Often described as resembling the odor of Ambrette seed
Powerful and diffusive ethereal-fruity, pungent odor, in dilution reminiscent of Pineapple-Strawberry.
Ethereal, fruity -winey odor, mild and comparatively weak
Musk-like odor.
Very mild, winey-green odor with a tartfruity-note.
Musk type odor
Rose-Honey type odor.
Very mild, fruity -winey odor.

Flavor enhancing
Mild, green-rosy, somewhat woody odor of great tenacity.
Woody-rosy, rather faint odor with a remcue resemblance to Geraniol (low-grade).
Very powerful, Grapefruit-Orange type odor
Fatty-peachy, somewhat musky odor, fattier than Undecanolide.
Powerful, fresh-fruity, oily odor of good tenacity. Fruitier than the odor of gamnra-Dodecalactone, and not as musky.
pronounced and powerful musky odors,

Sweet, waxy-herbaceous, very fresh and clean-floral odor (Lily-Violet-like in dilution) with a faint, balsamic undertone. The odor is often referred to as “fresh-laundry-odor”, but it is only pleasant in extreme dilutions. The concentrated material has a rather fatty-waxy odor
Very faint, fresh-green and slightly oily odor with a fruity-waxy undertone.
Fatty-waxy odor, yet overall a refreshing note.
Very mild, oily-fatty, slightly waxy, but fresh and remotely “soapy” odor. Pure grades have a certain similarity to fragrance notes in Mimosa, Cassie, Tuberose in the waxy-green floralness.
Mild, woody-musky odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Powerful citrusy odor, unpleasant gassy, choking at high concentration, but interestingly natural, Orange-Mandarin-like in extreme dilution.
Orangewaxy, sweet-floral, fresh and somewhat fruity odor,
Sweet, fioral-musky, slightly oily odor with notes reminiscent of Orris absolute and Ambrette seed oil.
Refreshing, waxy-fruity odor with citrusy note.
Very little odor, and the odor has very little character.
Very mild, oily-rancid odor, not exactly pleasant, and not characteristic of any common natural odor.
Not more interesting than the n-Butylester
Musky, Coconut-like, fatty odor of great tenacity.
woody, orrisy and mildly floral compositions.
.Mild, green-fruity, somewhat floral, Honeysuckle-type odor, also resembling Lindenblossom and Lily
In extreme dilution the material shows a pleasant herbaceous, mildly oily-green odor, reminiscent of vegetables and leaves.
Warm, woody and slightly fatty -aldehydic odor with a spicy undertone.
Fruity-winey odor, reminiscent of Ambrette seed oi! with a fatty-Pineapple-like and slightly earthy undertone.
Oily-fruity, faintly floral odor with some resemblance to that of unripe Apples, but with an almost nauseatingly sweet-oily note.
Oily-fruity, fresh-Apple-like odor with a rather heavy undertone. Overall weak and not very natural.
odorless,
Very faint, but tenacious, sweet, slightly buttery odor.
Very faint, sweet, somewhat woody-floral odor with a spicy undertone.
Vew faint, sweet-woody odor with an almost floral undertone
Sweet, slightly fruity-citrusy and very tenacious odor.
Pratt ically odorless.
Sweet-herbaceous Anise-Fennel type odor. Much more herbaceous than Anethole, and not as intensely sweet.
Mild, sweet, nauseating-floral, warm-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet-herbaaous, somewhat green, and in high concentration rather gassy odor of moderate to poor tenacity. In dilution quite pleasant and more natural-herbaccous.
“Jasmin-like”.
Sweet, floral and somewhat herbaceous odor of good tenacity. Milder than Anisaldehyde, more floral, less herbaceous, but overall not quite as powerful.
sweet and spicy-warm, remotely Vanilla-like odor.
Pleasant, ethereal-fntity, Brandy-like odor, somewhat nauseating in high concentration.
Ethereal-fruity, sweet and Rum-like odor.
Sweet, warm, somewhat pungent-floral odor with a herbaceous-balsamic undertone.
Mild, caramellic-sweet, fruity-winey odor, reminiscent of ‘cooked” fruits.
Sweet, slightly Caramellic-fmity odor with a diffusive. winey note.
Acrid, penetrating odor, apparently very diffusive, yet surprisingly temcious
Pleasant, rat her powerful odor of vinousoily-slightly fruity character.
The odor is sweet-ethereal, mild
Fruity-green, sweet and ethereal odor, rather sharp and powerful in its initial note.
Oily-floral, but rather harsh and unnatural odor of poor tenacity
Oily-fruity, fresh-herbaceous, but overall not very natural odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Pungent, herbaceous-fruity, warm odor, somewhat spicy-buttery with distinct resemblance to the topnotes in Lavender oil.
Weak. rather camphoraceous odor wit h less emphasis on the herbaccous notes, and not overall warm
Winey-sweet odor of Grape- and Berry-like character.
Fresh-winey, sweet and fruity, but also ‘“tart”’ odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful and diffusive, warrn-herbaceous
Sweet-floral, anisic-FenneMike, mild odor with resemblance to Chervil, Haw~hom flowers, Anise and Fennel
Sweet-fruity, grape-like odor, milder and less harsh than the Methyl ester.
Tested as odor enhancers
Sweet, “sBitter-almond’’-type odor, weaker, but more tenacious than that of Benzaldehyde. A slightly gassy. floral greenness is perhaps the most characteristic feature of the Ethylbenzaldehyde.
Sweet. but somewhat “gassy” odor. If at all reminiscent of any natural material, it would be a Hyacinth-type of gassy sweetness.
This material is practically odorless
Warm, floral-fruity, somewhat heavy odor, reminiscent of tropical flowers and with a faint resemblance to Methyl salicylate.
Sharp-floral. yet rather weak odor, remotely Jasmine-like, and of good tenacit}.
Pecullar Brand} -like odor of surprising tenacity
Sweet-floral, slightly fruity odor of Jasmin-Gardenia type and good tenacity.
Bakamic, fruity-floral odor reminiscent of Labdanum, with a distinct Jasmin-like note.
Rather heavy, fruity odor, remotely reminiscent of Raspberry (jam).
Powerful, fresh-fruity, sweet and slightly green odor.
Somewhat floral, earthy, wet-green, yet refreshing odor with some resemblance to Hyacinth, but not very powerful or tenacious.
Fruity and slightly green, refreshing odor, not reminiscent of any particular fruit or natural product.
Powerful, fruity, rather sharp odor, remotely reminiscent of Pineapple and Pear.
Fmity, somewhat oily odor of rather nondescript type.
Oily-fruity, hcrbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, but tenacious, oily-fruity, somewhat woody odor.
Extremely diffusive, fresh-fruity odor, somewhat fruity-oily.
Powerful, green-fatty, somewhat fruity odor.
Camphoraceous-minty, rather harsh odor.
Mild. oily-fruity, somewhat ethereal odor of good tenacity.
Very mild, sweet-floral odor of excellent tenacity.
Powerful, oily-caramellic, ‘“burnt “’ odor, reminiscent of notes from roasted Coffee and Cocoa beans.
Powerful, ethereal-fruity odor suggestive of Banana and Pineapple, and very diffusive.
Diffusive, sweet+thered, fruity odor, milder and sweeter than that of the n-Butyrate. Overall more flora~ kss fruity than the n-But yrate.
Oily-fruity. acidulous odor, not as ““rancid”’ as that of Caproic acid
Peculiar deep-fruity, tart, “’bitter-sweet “’ odor
Fruity-buttery, sweet-sour odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, diffusive, fruity-winey odor, suggestive of Apple, Banana, Pineapple, with a slightly floral undertone.
Sveet-winey-fruity odor of great tenacity,
Fruity-wincy, sweet odor, reminiscent of Apricot, Banana and Pineapple with a “fcrmented’’-winey note.
Ethereal, sweet odor.

Powerful, winey-herbaccous, sweet and ethereal, very pleasant odor of intriguing complexity, and with a powerfully lifting minty undertone. The spicy-hcrbaccous, warm and almost green-floral notes resemble certain notes in the Jasmin complex.
Sweet-balsamic, fruity-honey-like odor of excellent tenacity. Undertones of Orange (rather Orange-preserve-) or Grape-like character, and considerable overall power.

Warm, oily-spicy, herbaceous odor, reminiscent of the condiment known as Capers, however, without the pungency or sharpness of that natural material. There is normally a Cinnamon-note in the aldehyde, but the author believes that it maY vary according to the purity of the chemical. Overall a greenspicy odor, pleasant and with good tenacity.

Powerful and diffusive, fresh lemony odor, richer than that of Citral, but less sharp The ““Ethyl citral”’ also lacks the peculiar (and mostly undesirable) caramellic note of commercial synthetic Citral, and it is longer lasting. This type of odor is sometimes referred to as an ““Epoxy-odor”.
Fresh, green (foliage-type) rosy odor, not very tenacious. Overall resembling the fresher. initial notes in Geranium.
Mild-rosy, but not distinctly floral odor, weaker than that of Citronellol, more oilywaxy and fruity.
Sweet, floral-musky odor with notes resembling those of Labdanum and Arnbrette seed, or the sweet notes of Ambregris
Heavy-sweet, herbaceous and nut-like odor with an oily -balsamic undertone. Overall with some resemblance to the lower Cinnamates.
Warm, spicy-floral, herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
It has a powerful and diffusive, sour caramellic-fruity odor, reminiscent of unripeberries.
The odor of this rare chemical is describad as green, earthy, oily, resembling Violet and Reseda.
Refreshing, oily-green, vegetable or Applelike odor.
Powerful fruity odor of Raspberry-Apple type, but in no way a “natural” fruit odor. Moderate tenacity.
Pow’erful, sweet-fruity odor of Pear-Peach-Banana type, but only in extreme dilution displaying a natural fruit odor.
Sweet, but rather pungent, gassy odor with a floral undertone.

Powerful, sweet-fruity odor of considerable tenacity. The fruitiness is of rather nondescript character, which is almost typical of the Ethyland Methyl-cyclohexanol esters, but their sweetness and power exceed that of the corresponding BenzYl- or Phenylethyl esters.
Powerful, sweet, deep-fruity, almost “jamlike” odor. Not reminiscent of any particular fruit, perhaps remotely Apricot-Plum-like.
Powerful, fresh-fruity. sweet odor with some resemblance to that of Pineapple.
Powerful, fresh-fruity odor with notes of ““overripe*’ Pineapple, a remote resemblance to Ethyl valeratc, but far more powerful and diffusive, greener and sharper.
Faint, but tenacious, mild-fruity, “cannedfruit ““-like odor, reminiscent of Quince and pear
Green and slightly earthy, herbaceous-rootlike odor, reminiscent of Reseda. Considerably softer than the Hcptin- and Octin carbonates. Comparatively tenacious.
Sweet, oily-nutlike odor with a nc~ wineycast type background.
Fatty-oily, yet refreshing and “clean”’ odor of moderate tenacity.
Fruity-floral and warm, sweet odor of good tenacity. The winey-””fermented-fruit-like”’ undertones resemble the odor of Strawberry
Fresh, floral-green, cool and vegetablejuicy odor, remotely reminiscent of Cucumber and Cyclamen. Comparatively powerful and tenacious.
Faint, but very tenacious and pleasant, sweet-Ambre type odor, so discrete, that many obsewers find it rather musky, a description often applied to chemicals of very faint, but persistent odor.
It has a very tenacious, dry-woody Ambregris-type odor of delicate effect and yet of great power.
Sweet-musky, somewhat oily odor of outstanding tenacity.
Faint, musty odor.
Faint, sweet, oily-winey odor.
Faint, ethereal odor
The odor varies amrding to origin and to the quality of the Thioglycolic acid used in the manufacture of the ester. Poorer grades yield esters of Hydrogen-sulfide-type odor.
Peculiar, earthy, mushroom-like odor.
Weak, but pungent-u arm odor, remotely reminiscent of Horseradish and Radish, or Mustard.
Commercial grade material has a faint earthy, mushroom-like odor, but very pure analytical grades seem to be virtually odorless.
Ethereal, Acetone-like odor, also resembling crude Methanol (wood alcohol).
Mildly rosy, but also “metallic”’ odor of poor tenacity.
Sweet, slightly spicy, vegetable, beet-like odor.
The odor of this material depends largely upon the chemical purity.
Pleasant, ethereal odor, but irritates eye and nose at high concentration of vapors.
Sweet and very tenacious, musk-like odor with a somewhat oily undertone. Not quite as pleasant and not as strong as Ethylene brassylate.
Faint, but tenacious, sweet, musk-like odor.
Warm-floral, swest and somewhat greenfruity undertone. Heavier and more fruity than Ethyl salicylate, more sweet and tenacious.
semi-dry, fruity, Grape-1ike, Petitgrain-like odor with a winey note.
Vinous-herbaceous odor, reminiscent of Mint and Spearmint (garden mint).
Somewhat musty, but sweet-herbaceoustealike, warm and delicately spicy odor.
Mild, sweet, balsamic-Camation-like, warm and floral odor with a faintly spicy, Vanillalike undertone.
Faint, but very tenacious odor of woodynutlike, earthy-mossy character and a peculiar dry sweetness.
Pleasant, ethereal, diffusive, warmfruity Rum-like odor.
Powerfuj and diffusive, sweet-ethereal. “burnt ““odor, in extreme dilution rather pleasant, warm and sweet.
Fruity-green, slightly woody, peculiar odor, rather sharp in character, but not vev powerful, mainly reminiscent of unripe fruit.
Mild, warm-spicy, somewhat leather-like, but not medicinal or phenolic odor, slightly dry-woody, yet overall sweet. Less Cinnamon-Iike than the Methyl-derivative, more Labdanum-like.
Somewhat woody, warm, Tea-like, slightly floral odor of limited tenacity.
Warm, fruity-floral odor slightly more pungent than that of Ethyl bcnzoate. There are very pkasant “o”verripc fruit” or Plum-Raisin-Iikc undertones.
Sweet-balsamic, floral odor of modest tcnacity.
Warm-caramellic, sweet and somewhat floral odor.
Sweet-fruity, warm-caramellic, somewhat “burnt” odor of moderate tenacity.
not known to the author as a perfume
Mild, woody-rosy, somewhat green odor.
The odor is fattier and less woody than that of Geraniol,
Slightly rosy, sweet and delicately musky odor.
Sweet-floral, fruity, soft and warm odor of fair to good tenacity.

Diffusive-green, fresh-leafy, somewhat grassy and sweet odor of moderate tenacity. The greenness tends to be vegetable-like, sometimes described as “lettuce-juice’’-like, while the sueetness is almost floral.
Peculiar ethereal, weedy+winey odor, often classified as ““Spearmint-like’”
Warm, sweet and spicy-medicinal, very powerful odor, reminiscent of Guaiacol and Eugenol at the same time. The odor is extremely diffusive and penetrating.
Very powerful, sharp-green, but refreshing odor (in high dilution) with a nut-like undertone, oily but not truly fatty.
Powerful green, fatty-oily, citrusy, Bitter- Orange-like odor, softer and less harsh than Methyl heptenone.
Pouerful foliage odor with pleasant oily -waxy undertone. The green note is somewhat Violet-leaf-like, yet sweeter and waxier than the odor of Methyl heptin carbonate.
Powerful, fruity-wine-like, Brandy- and Berry-like odor with an oily-sharp undertone.
Oily-green, somewhat harah-fruity, sharp odor, reminiscent of unripe berries
Comparatively mild, fruity odor, less fatty than n-octyl aldehyde, and lacking the “rancid” type odor of that aldehyde.
Peculiar “Witch-Hazel”-like odor, more often described as “musty”’ slightly earthy, overall weak.
Musty odor, often d scribed as ‘sWitch-Hazei-’-like,
Comparatively mild, oily, sweet and slightly floral-rosy odor.
Powerful leafy-green odor of moderate to pobr tenacity. Less gassy and less pungent than Methyl heptin carbonate, but not as fresh-leafy as Methyl hexin carbonate.
Very pleasant, sweet-fruity odor reminiscent of Raspberry juice, sweeter than Octyl acetate and free from its herbal notes.
Relatively weak, fatty-acrid odor of considerable tenacity. Less nutty, more fruity than Decanoic acid.
Oily-herbaceous, somewhat winey odor with distinctly green-herbal notes, reminiscent of undertones in Jasmin complex.
Powerful and diffusive, sweet-herbaceous, balsamic odor with a mildly “gassy.’ character
Heavy, fruity, slightly spicy-floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild clover-like, somewhat musky-sweet, tenacious odor.
Pleasant. mild odor. warm and sweet, slightly cinnamic, mainly balsamic.
Woody-coumarinic, somewhat weedy-Cedarleafy odor with an overall ““Bittersweet” character and good tenacity.
Powerful, fresh-fruity-oily, siightly green odor.
Fruity, herbaceous-sweet and overall refreshing odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes are rather diffusive, the herbaceous notes are warm, slightly spicy or rooty
Sweet-balsamic, fruity and slightly floral, herbaceous, warm odor, reminiscent of the most pleasant notes in refined Labdanum products.
powerful animal-tarry odor, in extreme di.Iution sweet and floral, somewhat animal. But not at all faecal. Very tenacious.
Pleasant, warm-woody, powdery type odor.
Warm and pleasant, herbaceous-winey, balsamic odor of good tenacity, yet with considerable diffusive power.
Its mild, ethereal-buttery odor may blend well with certain types of fragrance, but is not always desirable.
Oily-fatty, somewhat leafy and flower-petallike, mild odor with a trace of a fruity undertone.
Ethereal-fruity, somewhat green and sweet odor

Floral, only slightly woody-green, soft odor of moderate tenacity. The odor type compared to Linalool indicates that ““Ethyl Iinalool’” is softer, more waxy, less volatile, less woodygreen and overall more floral. It is more Coriander-like. less Bois-de-Rose-like.
Sweet. floral. refreshing and rather light odor with a trace of a fruity note. More floral and less fruity than Linalyl acetate.
Powerful and fresh-herbaceous, delicately floral and haylike, warm odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Slightly fruity, primarily sweet-floral odor of moderate to good tenacity. Overall fresher and richer than Linalylacetate, and less green than Methyl Iinalyl ether.
Very diffusive and penetrating, gassy-herbaceous, warm odor of very poor tenacity.
Sweet. warm-fruity and woody-spicy odor of moderate tenacity.

Sweet, floral, heavy-fruity, warm odor of good tenacity The floral notes resemble Hyacinth, Wistaria and Ylang-Ylang, while the fruity notes have a delightful complex of Grape, Orange and Wintergreen sweetness.
Very powerful and diffusive, warm-floral, pungent odor, reminiscent of Hyacinth at high concentration, of Rose at proper dilution.
Very faint, sweet-balsamic-anisic odor of good tenacity.

Sweet-herbaceous odor reminiscent of sweet, semi-dried hay. Only mildly fruity notes are perceptible, the sweetness being more floral  ethereal than fruity, when the material is compared to the Ethyl methyl phenyl glycidate.
Sweet and soft fruity-floral odor, reminiscent of Pctitgrain or Mandarin-petitgrain oils. Excellent tenacity.

Sweet and warm, rich-fruity odor with caramellic undertone. The fruity notes are rather uncharacteristic, but have some resemblance to Strawberry-Pineapple. There is also some resemblance to the odor of Ethyl phenyl glycidate.

Powerful and diffusive, foliage-green odor, practically without trace of fatty or “greasy” notes. However, the initial impression is that of a rather unnatural green, although it could be classified as a “Lilac-green” type of odor,
Powerful and diffusive, green-fruity, pungent odor, reminiscent of Apple peels, Pineapple skins or the peels of unripe plums.

warm-spicy, moderately tenacious odor, often compared to that of Nutmeg. It is true that it does carry some of the characteri stics of Nutmeg oil odor, but this is a very complex odor and needs more than one chemical to demonstrate similarity.

The material introduces natural notes in many types of warm-floral bases, Jasmin, Peony, Gardenia, Sweet Pea etc., and its fruity-winey character blends well with Labdanum in many non-floral fragrance types.
Powerful leafy-green, but rather gassy-pungent odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Sweet, non-descrirtt fruity odor of moderate tenacity.
powerful green foliage type odor. It is less ‘“gassy” than the conventional acetylenic esters,
Mild and sweet-fruity, slightly green, caramellic-vegetable type odor of moderate to-good tenacity. Often compared to the odor of Quince.
Sweet, Strawberry-Raspberry-Pear-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful and very diffusive. Fresh-green, oily but not waxy odor of poor tenacity.
Refreshing, herbal-green, vinous odor with a faint resemblance to garden Mint or Spearmint.
Sweet-herbaceous, anisic type odor of good tenacity and with only very mildly fruity undertones.
Pleasant Banana-Raspberry-type odor.
Powerful, fruity-green, diffusive odor of Banana-Pineapple type, in proper dilution also reminiscent of Strawberry.

The title material has a powerful, but rather sharp green odor of very poor tenacity. It is less stable than Methylheptin carbonate but ita odor is considered slightly superior to that of MHC in that it is leas fatty.
Sweet-fruity, “candy’’-like, warm odor with considerable similarity to that of Strawberry juice or Strawberry syrup.
Distinctly fruity, but also somewhat woody odor
Sweet-woody, herbaceous and slightly spicy earthy odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, deepfruity, slightly floral and woody odor with ‘“cooked fruit” undertones and very great tenacity.
Very mild oily ethereal odor with some resemblance to Orris and Violet.
Very diffusive, sweet, ethereal odor.
Slightly fatty-oily, fruity and nut-like odor with a winey undertone.
Sweet-green and slightly waxy odor, nearest in type to Methyl dccin carbonate.
Herbaceous-green, leafy, Violet-1eaf type odor with Coconut-like undeflones.
Fresh-fruity, sweet timon-like citrusy odor of good tenacity.
Sweet, mild, Orange-peel-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Delicate, yet intensely Violet-leaf-like, green odor, also mminisccnt of vegetables, Cucumber,etc.
Warm. herbaceous, oily and very tenacious odor, sweet in dilution, rather unpleasant when undiluted.
Fruity, aldehydic-herbal odor, more fruity than Methyl nonyl ketone and less “.Rue.’-like.
More fruity and less floral, also less fatty than n-Octanol with respect to odor.

This product is used occasionally in perfumery, e.g. in Citrus type fragrances and Citrus topnotes. It imparts a pleasant, natural, winey *’mellow” note which blends excellently with the light Citrus notes.
This ester may find a little use in perfumery as a solvcnt~modifier or a constituent of certain artificial flower abaolutes, but its main use in that in flavor compositions.
Sweet, somewhat camphoraceous-herbaceous odor with a Fimecdle-like note.
Used in flavor compositions
Very faint waxy odor, extremely mild, sweet.
Very faint, sweet odor, by some observers classified as ‘*musky”, others find the material virtually odorless.

Powerful and pencwating, gassy-green, oily-vegetable odor of moderate to poor tenacity. In extreme dilution it displays quite pleasant and almost natural, sweet-green tonalities, and it could be classified as one of the more attractive Acetylenic esters
Semi-sweet, tarry-medicinal odor, sweeter than that of phenol and more tar-like, smokey.
Powerful, woody-phenolic, medicinal, yet rather sweet odor, Sweeter than the Cresols, somewhat to the anisic type.

Sweet, somewhat honeylike, also floral odor of good tenacity. The honey-notes are less pronounced in this ester than in the conventional Ethyl phenylaeetate, but the floral notes are more perceptible and tend to point in the Hyacinth direction.
Somewhat gassy-earthy. but also floral odor, aldehydic-green, and, in suitable dilution, quite pleasant and sweet. Remotely reminiscent of the odor of crushed Lilac leaves.
Powerful, sweet, Honey-like, slightly animal and quite pcrsistant odor with a fruity undertone reminiscent of Apricot.
Harsh-anisic, rather powerful odor with sweet and somewhat floral character in higher dilution.
Sweet, fruity, Plum-like odor of good tenacity.
Pleasant, warm-aromatic, but somewhat pungent odor - more attractive in dilution.
Rather harsh-rosy, semi-dry.odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Leafy-green, delicately rosy and sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Very powerful, exotic-floral, pungent, sweet and warm odor of Hyacinth type with a Roselike undertone.
Warm, caramellic-fruity odor, reminiscent of cooked Strawberries.
Sweet, very light, fruit y-honeylike odor. Milder,. more rosy-honeylike and more Hyacinth-like than the Methylester.
Sweet-fruity and mildly balsamic odor with resemblance to Hydrocinnamic alcohol and Cinnamyl esters. Moderate tenacity.
Very faint, sweet-herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Powdery-hcrbaceous and slightly fruity odor of good tenacity.
Very volatile, ethereal, fruity-rum-like odor.
Warm, sweet, winey-Rum-like odor of good tenacity.

Very powerful, sweet-green, in the pure state nauseating, in dilution slightly minty odor with sweet-herbaceous, mildly tarrypungent undertones. There is a certain similarity to the odor of mushrooms and dry-rotted wood. In suitable dilution actually a pleasant odor.
Sweet hayljke, breadiike odor.
Sweet floral-fruity, warm odor of poor tenacity.
Very faint “oily” odor when pure. Less sweet, more harsh-smelling if poorly stored or oxidized.
Heavy, sweet, floral-fruity odor, milder than Methyl salicylate, more Cassie-like, more intensely sweet-floral undertones.
Warm-fruity and somewhat ethereal odor.
Virtually odorless when pure.
Sweet, deep, fruity odor of berry-like character.
Powerful and diffusive, sweet-herbaceous odor with a woody undertone.

The odor of this ester has been described as “onion-like”, but the author believes, based upon personal studies, that a good commercial grade of this ester has little or no such odor. The odor may be slightly herbaceous, green-fruit y, and not exceptionally pleasant.
Warm-ethereal, fruity odor of deep, slightly caramellic note.
Sweet, somewhat woody, but overall floral-ambre-like odor with a peculiar ‘“fishy” under-tone resembling that of Ally] Ionone.
Fatty, sweet-earthy, green and Reseda-like odor, weaker or milder than Ethyl decincarbonate, and not as closely resembling Rcseda. Good tenacity
Winey-fatty-fruity and somewhat nut-like odor.
Pleasant fruity-winey odor, more winey than Undecylic ester, and less floral (see previous monograph),

Powerful and diffusive, ethereal-fruity, Apple-like odor with a remote resemblance to Pineapple. Esters with traces of free acids will show this very perceptibly in the odor, not so conspicuously in the flavor (in aqueous media).
Powerful, diffusive and penetrating-ethereal, vinous-fruity odor. In extreme dilution sweet, Apple-like fruity

Intensely sweet odor, warm, slightly floral and with some resemblance to Vanilla in its creamy sweetness. The tenacity is outstanding, and the odor power only demonstrated in dilutions of this chemical.
Sweet, somewhat floral odor, remotely reminiscent of Vanilla, but much weaker than Ethyl vanillin (see previous monograph), and also weaker than Vanillin.
Sweet, somewhat floral odor, remotely reminiscent of Vanilla, more so than commercial “’Ethyl vanillin”, but not with the same strength,
Sweet-fruity and slightly floral odor, the fruity notes being more Cherry-and-Plum like, while the floral undertone is Jasmin-like.

This alcohol has found some use as a fixative for woody, floral and spicy fragrance types, lts very delicate, sweet-woody and warm notes tend to be floral in combination with more volatile components.
Sweet, fruity, slightly floral odor, reminiscent of Pear or Bergamot. The tenacity is exceptionally good.
Powerful, warm-spicy, rather dry and almost sharp odor, drier and harder than that of Clove bud oil, less peppery-woody than that of Clove leaf oil.

Mild and sweet, deep-floral ,very tenacious odor with great warmth and resemblance to Carnation, Sweet Williams or Wallflower. Poorer grades often show’ variable degree of dry-woody Eugenol-spiciness.
Dry spicy-green odor, more reminiscent of Bayleaf than of Clove.
Virtually odorless and tasteless when pure. However, most commercial lots show a faint balsamic-spicy odor.
Leafy-green, delicately rosy and sweet odor of moderate tenacity. remote resemblance to Orris and a fresh-spicy, slightly green undertone.
Fresh-green, sweet-woody, almost Orris-like odor with an unquestionable Clove-iike undertone.

Mild, but warm and sweet, slightly spicy odor of excellent tenacity. There are honeylike tonalities in most of the commercial products, but there are also products in which that note is absent or hardly perceptible.
Intensely sweet, Vanilla-Clove-like odor, overall warm and mild, but extremely tenacious and with Honey-tobacco-like undertones.
Semi-sweet, woody and slightly fruity, warm odor of good tcnacit y and some rescmbiancz to fum-Ionone, but more sweet, less woody than that material.
Very mild, sweet-oily, slightly woody, tenacious odor.
Very mild, sweet and warm, rather nondescript odor of good tenacity.
Very mild and delicate, sweet-oily odor, slowly developing a floral fresh-green note, reminiscent of certain notes from Muguet.
Very faint odor, somewhat green-floral, remotely rosy.
Intensely sweet, floral and creamy-winey odor of excellent tenacity.
Ethereal-floral, rich and sweet odor of considerable tenacity. The odor suffers considerably when the material is exposed to air, daylight or heat.
Fresh, Camphor-like odor of poor tenacity. somewhat sweeter than Camphor, also slightly cooler.
Warm-camphoraceous, powerful and diffusive, basicalIy sweet odor.
Mild, rather sweet Fir Needle oil type odor, somewhat milder than Bornyl acetate, and not quite as characteristic, conifer-like.
Powerful and diffusive, Camphor-like, but sweeter and more Citrus-1ike almost Lime-like odor with more or less of an earthy-dry character, according to the composition and isomer-ratio.
This rare ester finds a little use in perfumery as a fixative in Pine and woody fragrance types, in certain Fougere types and low-cost Oriental fragrances.
Mild and sweet-herbaceous odor with some resemblance to overripe fruit. Also reminiscent of fresh VaIerian root
Fresh-herbaceous, slightly Conifer-like odor of moderate tenacit y. It bears some resemblance to the odor of fresh Valerian root - but less so than the n-butyrate.
when properly diluted, preferably incorporated and well mellowed in a composition, it shows its exceptionally powerful, yet delicately dry, woody-Ambregris-like, extremely tenacious odor.
Although it can be said that the title musk has an initially stronger odor than Musk Ketone, its odor type is less desirable and its tenacity poorer.

Powerful, sweet-green, slightly floral, rosy odor of considerable tenacity. However, the overall character is not very distinct, since it seems to have notes from Rose, Hyacinth, etc. blended with winey-weedy tonalities in an overall odor impression that leaves the observer somewhat confused
Sweet, but faint, slightly fruity, Pear-like odor, remotely reminiscent of Terpinyl acetate or LinaIyl acetate, sweeter than the former, not as sweet as the latter.
Ethereal-fruity odor, reminiscent of Butyl formate and Dibutyl ether.
Very diffusive, sweet ethereal odor, some what reminiscent of Acetone and Methyl acetate
It has an extremely diffusive, ethereal odor, resembling that of Methyl formate or Ethyl nitrite, briefly: ethereal.
Very diffusive, ethereal odor, reminiscent of Dipropyl ether and Propyl formate.
Mild, sweet-floral and very tenacious odor.
Very sweet, floral-balsamic, warm, yet refreshingly clean odor.
Green, waxy-rosy, sweet, overall floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Very diffusive, slightly choking or nauseating, Pear-1ike odor of very poor tenacity. In aqueous dilution the odor appears very weak mainly due to the miscibility of the acetal with water.
Very mild, refreshing, green-floral, Citrus-Iike, Lemon-type odor of good tenacity.
Mild, sweet, rosy-green odor of moderate tenacity.
and hardly in a standard grade or composition. It was developed to produce a perfume chemical with the virtues of Rhodinol plus a refreshing greenness, a combination ideal for Muguet bases.
Herbaceous, sweet-green and slightly fruityethereal odor of moderate tenacity.
Ethereal-green, yet sweet and slightly tloral rosy odor of poor tenacity. The greennes resembles that of foliage mixed with flowers, but it is somewhat “gassy” ethereal, not quite pleasant.
Somewhat musty-woody, faintly musky odor with rosy undertones.

Rculiar oily-herbaceous odor, not unlike that of Amykinnamic aldehyde, but not as tenacious, not aa purely oily-herbaceous. The subject lcetal has a more musty note, quite typical of many glycol acetals.
Pungent odor giving a stinging sensation on the mocous membranes.
Virtually odorless
Peculiar spicy -smokey, slightly Cinnamonlike odor.
Pungent, but sweet, bread-like, caramellic, Cinnamon-Almond-like odor of poor tenacity
Mild, warm, spicy-woody, sweet odor,somewhat reminiscent of Cinnamon.
Mild, ethereal-floral odor, somewhat reminiscent of Ethyl acetoacetate, Benzyl acetate and the Glycol acetates, with a herbal-spicy undertone.
Very mild, warm-oily, “burnt” odor. Chem-ically pure Furfuryl alcohol is - in the opinion of many observers - virtually odorless.
Extremely powerful and diffusive, penetrating odor, only in proper dilution being agreeable, Coffee-like, caramellic-bumt, sweet.
Practically odorless
Sweet, buttery-cinnamon-like odor of moderate tenacity, but quite penetrating
Rather sharp, but warm, green-spicy, pungent odor.
Warm, sweet, woody~innamon-like odor, remotely reminiscent of Coffee.
Sweet and warm-herbaceous, also caramellic-balsamic odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild, sweet, fruity-caramellic, somewhat spicy odor.
Vinous ethereal, at times pungent, sometimes mild, oily smelling with considerable variations according to origin.
Mild, green-floral, also slightly weedy, but overall fresh and clean odor with woody undertones. It bears some resemblance to the odor of Geraniol tail fractions.
Mild and sweet, floral Rose-type odor. Warm and yet slightly dry undertones, but there are great variations according to the quality and”origin of the Geraniol.
Sweet-rosy odor, not as mild as Geranioi, and not as fruity, more herbaceous or remotely green, less “creamy”.
Powerful and lasting sweet-floral, overall green-rosy odor.
Light and fresh-rosy, green odor with some resemblance to Peony, although greener than the odor of that flower.
Sweet, fruity-floral, rosy, somewhat green and remotely Lavender-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet fruity, winey-green “fermented Apple”- like, overall very pleasant odor.
Fresh-floral, light, but rather penetrating, sweet-rosy, slightly green, Magnolia-like odor of moderate tenacity. The odor has some resemblance to that of Rhodinyl formate, yet somewhat sharper.
Heavy, sweet, floral and very tenacious odor of Honeysuckle-Frangipanni-type.
Faint-rosy, very tenacious, overall mildly floral odor with Ambre-like undertones.
Refreshing and sweet-floral, fruity-rosy odor of good tenacity.

Sweet, rather heavy, fruity odor reminiscent of Apples, with undertones of red Roses, slightly fatty-oily, but overall very pleasant. Needless to say that traces of free acid are detrimental to this odor picture.
Sweeter and more floral than the n-Butyrate, less acid (and it has less tendency to become acid), yet overall a fruity odor with rosy character,
Refreshing, sweet-peachy, but also musky odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-sweet, floral-herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
Fruity Geranium-like with rosy and slightly green undertones. The fruity notes resemble Banana-Pineapple.
Sweet, oily-herbaceous, overall rosy odor with fruity undertones, remotely reminiscent of Apricot and Mango.
Mild and sweet Ambre-Rose type odor with soft, balsamic undertones.
Warm-herbaceous, sweet odor with a rosy-woody undertone and good tanacity.
Rosy and somewhat green odor, milder than Geranyl acetate and much less fruity.
Sweet and mellow, rosy, and warm, tenacious odor.
Fresh, but somewhat dry, green-rosy, ‘leafy” odor, diffusive and remotely fruity. Reminiscent of Rose, Geranium, Bergamot, Ncroli, and with an intriguing note of Appleskins and ginger

Sweet -herbaceous, woody, slightly fruity (fruit-preserve-like) odor of good tenacity. This ester has notes resembling Geranium, but it is much softer and lacks the green freshness of Geranium materials.
Mild and fresh-floral-fruity odor of good tenacity. More fruity than floral, the fruity notes resembling Peach and Apricot.
used in artificial flower absolutes and in the more delicate and long-lasting floral perfume types, such as Muguet or Jonquil, also in Tuberose.
Very faint and mild rosy odor with such a lack of floralness that the odor is often described as musky
Penetrating and powerful, oily-green, lemony-fresh odor with some resemblance to that of Citral, but overall harsher, not as sweet and not as natural in its notes.
Faintly rosy, but overall fatty-acetic odor, remotely reminiscent of Acetic acid.
Fresh and leafy, Rose- and Geranium type odor, overall more resembling Geranium. Mild, oily winey undertones.
Soft and very sweet, tenacious, mildly floralhoneylike almost herbaceous odor with Geranium-like undertones and variable amounts of animal notes.
Practically odorless when pure
Sweet, fruity-rosy, warm and almost balsamic-Grape-like odor with a leafy-floral undertone and moderate tenacity.
Very weak, green and rosy odor.
Virtually odorless when pure, but the ester does contribute sweet, rosy-balsamic notes to a composition when lower boiling materials are present.

Very pleasant, sweet-herbaceous, Geranium-like and fruity odor. The Geranium notes resemble the middle and late notes in natural Geranium, and the fruity notes are deep, almost “jam-like”, tenaciously sweet, yet an overall refreshing odor with a touch of leafyness,
Powerful, fruity, almost Pineapple-like and Apple-peel-like odor with rosy-tobaccolike,herbaceous undertones.
Fruity, Apple-like, somewhat rosy odor with distinctly herbaceous-sweet undertones, also reminiscent of “’overripe fruit”.
Fresh, “leafy’’-green odor with some resemblance to the lighter “Rose” acetals. Warm-rosy undertones
Very faint, sweet-woody, somewhat herbaceous odor of extraordinary tenacity.
Virtually odorless
Virtually odorless,
The acid itself has a very faint odor resembling that of yeast or freshly baked bread (but much weaker),
Commercial grades usually have a faint odor,
When absolutely pure, it is almost odorless. Certain commercial grades have a mustysweet, slightly earthy odor, somewhat similar to that observed in Hexylene glycol
High-grade products have only a faint, sweet-oily odor
Glyceryl monostearate is used for the same purposes as Glyceryl mono-olein, and it has some advantages in having less odor and no tendency to turn rancid.
Very faint, sweet caramellic-rootlike odor
Powerful smoke-like, somewhat medicinal odor, sweeter than the prototype phenolic odor
Dry-peppery, rather choking and green odor with slightly fatty and remotely fruity notes.

Very sweet, earthy-herbaceous, somewhat musty-walnut-like odor of fair tenacity. The few variations of samples show occasional contamination with traces of Phenol, which largely disturbs the odor of the ether.
Woody, dry, slightly green odor with variable amounts of a medicinal note, according to purity of the chemical.
Virtually odorless when pure and freshly prepared.
Heavy, rather dry, woody-herbaceous odor with variable amounts of “phenolic” or “phenylacetic” notes, both of which will greatly influence the odor of the ester.
Pleasant sweet-woody, mild and almost balsamic odor with a discrete peppery undertone and good tenacity.
Mild, rather sweet and very tenacious balsamic-woody odor with an almost floral undertone and a pepperiness which seem to be apparent only in impure material (possibly traces of hydrocarbons).
Delicately sweet-woody, soft and warm odor reminiscent of Patchouli and Tearose.
This odor type is very suitable for certain variations of Rose, where Civet or Honeynotes are called for, and in Oriental Rose variations in combination with heavy woody and floral notes.
Peculiar green-woody, yet somewhat floral and tenacious odor with bark- or sap-like undertones.
Very faint, but delicately sweet and mildly woody-floral odor of outstanding tenacity.
Very sweet floral, warm slightly spicy and tenacious odor, sometimes described as “Cherry-like” (American tym Cherry).
Very mild floral, sweet odor of mildly greenspicy type, remotely reminiscent of Heliotrope and Hawthorne - but much weaker.
Very weak, sweet-fiord and somewhat green odor reminiscent of Heliotrope, but much weaker.
Very sweet, light, floral and tenacious odor with distinctly fruity (“Cherry-like”) undertones.
Intensely sweet, floral and very slightly woody-powdery odor reminiscent oft he sweetfloral notes in Mimosa and Cassie. Also remotely reminiscent of Heliotrope.
Weak, sweet, nondescript odor, remotely reminiscent of Vanilla.
Deepswect, very mild, overall fruity, berrylike odor with a “jam-like-’ and a trace of a floral undertone.
Sweet-balsamic and very tenacious odor.
Powerful and rather pungent, but sweet, somewhat floral odor, rather choking at high concentration, warm-exotic, floral at proper dilution.
Faint camphoraceous-minty odor, remotely reminiscent of Pennyroyal oil or Pulegone, yet slightly more medicinal-tarry.
Very powerful and diffusive oily-fatty, “rancid” odor. Penetrating and pungent at high concentration, almost fruity, “’fermentedfruit’’- like in extreme dilution.
Fresh-herbaceous, winey and foliage-green odor, sweeter and much less penetrating than that of the aldehydc.
Green-herbaceous, vegetable-like odor, reminiscent of green beans (haricots verts), almost cabbage-leafy, with sweet-oily, somewhat coconut-like underlines.
Winey-herbaceous, oily-green odor. Ethereal and mild when pure, but traces of free Aidehyde influemxs the odor picture considerably to the disadvantage of the Acetal.
Peculiar fungus-like, earthy-sweet odor, not very powerful.

Sweet-ethereal, diffusive odor of poor tenacity. Commercial grade material often carries off-odor of sulfuraceous, tarry, phenolic or “’gassy” Styrene-like character, deriving from trace impurities, while pure Heptane is not unpleasant smelling at all.
The commercial product has a very unpleasant, sour-sweat-like, fatty odor.
Fresh and light, green-fatty, winey and sap-Iike odor of poor tenacity.
Fresh, Lemon-like, grassy -herbaceous odor with a sweet-floral undertone. The overall “lift” is primarily fruity-green.
Powerful, hcrbaceous, warm-and-cool odor  of poor tenacity. In dilution sweet, more balsamic than herbaceous
Sweet-herbaceous, nut-like and slightly caramellic odor, practically free from fatty notes. Moderate tenacity.
Extremely powerful, fatty-green, somewhat vegetable odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent-green odor, only in extreme dilution becoming pleasant, vegetable-juicy-green, but more fatty than the Hexenoic aldehydes.
Powerful, fresh-fatty-oily odor, reminiscent of fresh cream.
Comparatively mild and pleasant herbaceous-fruit y, ““natural” odor. Overall reminiscent of Melon and Apple skins, but with a rich and rather complex herbal undertone.
Very powerful, fruity-green odor. In dilution mostly fruity and rather pleasant.
Very fresh, light, leafy-fruity odor with rosy undertones.
Powerful, sweet, fatty-green, rather heavy odor. . Under light, grassy notes there are fruity-floral, almost animal-heavy and quite tenacious nuances of nondescript character.
Somewhat fatty-oily odor, softer than that of Heptanol, and less fruity.

Fruity, fatty-green and slightly floral odor with pleasant, leafy undenones. The delicate,leafy notes resemble those found in Applerose or Hiprose. Some observers find an earthy. green or mushroom-like note.
Pleasant, warm, sweet, slightly fruity -balsamic odor with some resemblance to Opopanax and Myrrh.
A rather uninteresting, fruity-green odor.
Pleasant, oily-green, rich and sweet odor with vinous undertone and moderate tenacity.
Faint, but sweet, fruity-winey odor, occasionally with an Almond-like undertone.
Sweet, woody-floral, somewhat green, but very weak odor, remotely reminiscent of Petitgrain.

Mild woody-gseen almost weedy or Sagelike odor of good tenacity. The odor type is, however, rather unnatural, not exactly pkasant (like damp wood) and often further spoiled by trace impurities of metallic odor, etc.
Peculiar “metallic’” odor, yet remotely reminiscent of the odor of Geranium leaves
Sweet-green, yet fresh and slightly Tea-like odor. In higher concentration also reminiscent  of Violet leaf.
Peculiar, complex fruity odor with distinctly herbaceous, sweet undertones. There are notes resembling Chamomile and other notes resembling Apple, and there is an overall green floral odor.
Sweet fruity, Peach-like and musky odor, yet overall fresher, not as heavy as the gammaisomer. Very good tenacity.
Mild winey-brandy-like odor reminiscent of the odor of ‘“tail fractions from rectification of Fusel oil”, yet much milder. Remotely reminiscent of Cognac oil
Fresh-green, foliage and vegetable-like odor, reminiscent of the odor of freshly crushed leaves and stems, or the juice from same. Remotely reminiscent of Violet leaf greenness.

The odor of this ester does not remind of any particular natural material, and it is therefore a rather uninteresting ester. There are oily-fruity notes of the type often found as undesirable topnotes in certain essential oils (Amyns, CedarWood, etc.), notes which are sometimes described as “odor of green potatoes or of Peanuts”.
Mild, floral-green, somewhat bark-like odor with a woody-earthy undertone, remotely reminiscent of Hyacinth.
Very faint, mild, sweet-oily odor. In compositions with more volatile ingredients, this aldehyde shows a floral effect.
Powerful, sweet and tenacious, warmwoody, somewhat balsamic odor. Not reminiscent of any particular natural material.
Peculiar metallic-medicinal odor, not very pleasant or natural.
Camphoraceous-green, somewhat woody and quite tenacious odor. Not reminiscent of any particular natural material.
Powerful, camphoraceous-woody, somewhat green and Chris-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, fruity-floral and very sweet odor of moderate tenacity. It is less floral and more fruity than the corresponding ketone and it has a similar, but sweeter greenness.
Floral-green, fruity and warm, somewhat herbaceous odor with overall resemblance to certain notes in Jasmin

Powerful floral-fruity odor, overall less fruity and more floral than the average commercial type of “iso-Jasmone”. Moderate tenacity, and a somewhat green topnote seems to accompany the odor for most of the duration, except for the extreme dryout notes which are more floral.
Rather nondescript, herbal odor. Greenoily, almost fresh, but not reminiscent of any particular natural material.
