Very faint, fatty-oily “laundry’”-like odor. The odor is somewhat reminiscent of the odor of fresh vegetable oils.
Leather-like, somewhat tarry and dry odor (topnote), becoming sweeter on longer study, more fruity on dryout.
Mild and very sweet, also fruity and vety tenacious odor, remotely reminiscent of overripe fruit (Apples).
Somewhat sharp, fruity-fatty, Apple and Plum-like, remotely Orris-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Very mild green-herbaceous and warm odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm, somewhat caramellic-herbaceous odor of good tenacity. A complex of greenherbal and very sweet, deep notes produces an almost floral character.
Peculiar sweet-coumarinic, slightly woodyfloral odor resembling Cassie, Mimosa and New Mown Hay, yet milder than the latter.
Powerful, sweet-green, citrusy odor with some resemblance to notes in Lime oil. Good tenacity.
Winey-green, rather fatty, fermentation odor of considerable tenacity. The green undertones are much less grassy than those of the Hexylesters, and not as natural, more fatty
Fruity-floral, somewhat Jasmin-like, fattygreen and waxy odor with some resemblance to Orris undertones.

Powerful floral, slightly oily-fruity odor of good tenacity. Less fruity than the so-called “’iso-Jasmone”, but somewhat sharper than the better-known Heptyl cyclopentanone. Overall character of a floral-fruity Jasmin type chemical
Fatty and very ‘oily”, slightly green, but overall “rancid*’ type of odor.
Very sweet, green-floral, herbaceous-Orangeblossom-type odor of good tenacity.
Fatty-waxy, weak and somewhat Stearinlike odor of considerable tenacity.
Earthy-green, herbaceous and comparatively powerful odor of moderate tenacity.

Very weak, waxy, mild odor, characteristic of Stearic-Palmitic compounds. Excellent tenacity, and in pure esters, a pleasant overall odor, while poorer grades may show “rancid” type fatty notes, definitely disagreeable and useless.
Mild, winey-sweet, oily and floral odor with Orange/Orangeblossom and Rose-like undertones.
Rather unpleasant fatty-oily odor. often described as reminiscent of the odor of “’wet sheep” ( “Lamb’s wool odor”).
Mild, sweet-oily odor with a peculiar earthy-green note, resembling the odor of freshly crushed (fresh) peanuts. Also resembling the odor of the green peel,of potatcws or raw coffee beans
Very mild, oily-sweet odor, reminiscent of refined Peanut oil or good grade Olive oil.
Very mild oily odor, reminiscent of freshly refined Cod liver oil (no fishy notes !) or good grade Linseed oil.
Green and sweet, yet fresh-earthy saplike or barklike odor with a trace of resemblance to Verbena
Grectt-balsamic, warm-herbaceous odor, remotely reminiscent of Myrrh and Opopanax, but much inferior with respect to tenacity.
Powerful aromatic, warm-floral, earthy odor with some resemblance to Hyacinth and Gardenia.
Ethereal-winey, but somewhat “bitter” odor, or an ‘*astringent” odor-impression, similar to that of certain unripe fruits. Waxyaldehydic notes appear along with a rather dry undertone.
Very faint, sweet-herbaceous odor. To some observers, this ester is virtually odorless.
Fruity-floral, quite diffusive odor. One is tempted to compare the odor to those of the Jasmone-related chemicals.
Mild and fatty-floral, fruity and slightly “aldehydic” odor with some resemblance to Peach and Apricot.

Oily-fatty, not very pleasant odor with earthy-mossy undertones. Older odor descriptions include the words “smokey and ink-like”, but the author is unable to detect any such odor type in the few available samples of subject material.
Mild, woody-fruity odor, earthy-green and with sweet-soil-like undertones, remotely resembling of notes in Vetiverol or VetivcryI acetate
Ethereal and comparatively diffusive odor reminiscent of the odor of higher alifatic aldehydes, yet with much less power.
Peculiar fruity odor with a woody-animal-Iike undenone, even when no trace of Valerie acid seems to be perceptible.
Green-fruity, rather fresh and “juicy’” odorresembling that of freshly crushed unripe fruit (e. g. Gooseberry) with an undertone like wet grass.
Regular Hercolyn has a faint, woody-piney odor of considerable tenacity.
Mild Camphor-1ike odor of moderate tena-city, and not as “medicinal” as Camphor.
Faint, sweet-musky odor of excellent tenacity.
Weak and mildly floral, orrisy-waxy odor. Some observers describe the odor as “peachy”, but the author of this work fails to find any such note in subject material.
The pure material is virtually odorless. Lower grade commercial products may have a faint, sweet, oily odor and a bland taste.
Powerful but sweet-green odor, in dilution pleasant citrusy-fresh-green, in high concentration rather pungent, choking
Powerful, diffusive, sweet, somewhat gassygreen, but not really unpleasant odor of very poor tenacity.

Sweet-oily, green odor, somewhat grassyweedy, but quite refreshing and moderately tenacious. The alcohol oxidizes very easily in air and this process affects the odor considerably to the disadvantage of the pleasantness of this alcohol.
Oily-sweet, fruity-green, Apple- and Gabarium-like odor with more sweetness and fruitiness than Galbanum, and overall more fruity than green notes. Fair tenacity

Sweet-oily, citrusy and refreshing, green odor of moderate tenacity. Undiluted not very pleasant, rather oily-fatty, but at concentrations near 1%, or in proper composition, the odor appears more citrusy, sweeter, fresher.
Pleasant, sweet-rosy, citrusy odor, less floral than Trimethyl undecanal (known as Norhsxahydrofamesal) and Tetrahydro famesal. Very tenacious and waxy-petal-like.
Sweet and musky odor of good tenacity,
Peculiar earthy-sweet, musty odor of moderate tenacity.
Very sweet and herbaceous-winey odor with Basil-NeroIi-like notes and good tenacity.
Mild and sweet fruit y-woody odor of moderate tenacity. The fruity notes are without specific character, and the overall impression is that of a rather chemical odor
Powerful, sweet, green-floral and somewhat woody-earthy odor of good tenacity.
Apart from having a typical Musk odor and good tenacity, it does not offer any effects that can justify its preference over the newer, related materials.
Sw.wt and musky odor of good tenacity, but not quite as powerful as the isomer of Indan type
Sweet, herbaceous-floral, somewhat woody odor of moderate tenacity. The floral notes tend to appear rosy, the herbaceous sweetness is almost haylike/Lavender-like, and the undertones are also fruity.
Camphoraceous-musky, but also musky odor of considerable tenacity. Woody notes and degree of camphoraceous topnote seems to vary with the isomer ratio
Warm, powerfully herbaceous, sweet “Tobacco-like”’, coumannic type odor.

The subject ester however, has only a rough minty-camphoraceous odor, somewhat reminiscent of Pennyroyal oil, and the ester could find some use as a material for masking odors for industrial purposes.

Very powerful, penetrating, fat ty-green, grassy odor. In extreme dilution more reminiscent of freshly cut grass and unripe fruits (Apple and Plum). The acrid note of the concentrated material resembles that of rancid butter
Oily-green, rather mild, grassy odor of fairtenacity. The odor is strongly influenced by the presence (or absence) of free aldehyde.
Peculiar dry-musty, leafy-green, but overall mild and rather sweet odor. Traces of free aldehyde will naturally change the odor picture significantly.

Extremely powerful “burnt “-alliaceous- sulfuraceous odor. In dilution the odor becomes less repulsive, and shows resemblance to the odor of freshly roasted Coffee or Cocoa beans, still with some Onion-like character.
Heavy, acrid-acid, fatty-rancid odor, often described as “sweat-like’”.
Somewhat “chemical’’-winey, slightly fatt y and fruity odor, weaker than Amyl alcohol, but resembling that material, except that Hexanol seems fattier and fruitier.
Powerful, deep-green, leafy odor reminiscent of Strawbmy-leaf and wine-leaf, freshly crushed.
Powerful green-fruity, pungent vegetabielike odor, pungent in high concentrations, almost acrylic-sharp, but pleasant fruity and fresh-green in dilutions below 0.1 ‘a.
Fruity-green, refreshing and rather mild odor, reminiscent of Appleskins or unripe Apples,
no more than academic interest.
verry natural green odor in combining the forces and virtues of Leaf alcohol with the so-called ‘leaf aldehyde”
Fatty and slightly acrid-musty odor in the pure state, pleasant, fruity-sweet odor in dilution.
Powerful and intensely green, grassy odor. It appears more grassy-green and foliagegreen, less fruity than the mans-2-Hexenol.
Powerful, gassy-green, but rather sharp odor, even in dilution not closely reminiscent of any natural green odor.

Powerful, fruity-green, slightly caramellicfruity in its undertone and with an overall odor often compared to that of Chrysanthemum foliage, or wine leaves. The odor is sweeter, more winey-leafy than that of the cis-3-Hexenol.
Intensely green, but rather “bitter’’-foliagelike, somewhat fatty odor. More “Chrysanthemum-like” and less fruity than its two isomers
Intensely green, sharp-fruity and very diffusive odor, in dilution reminiscent of unripe Banana peel.
Powerful and fresh-green, sweet and fruity, very “natural” odor
Penetrating, gassy-green diffusive odor of poor tenacity. There are fruity undertones, but they appear only in proper dilution, when the pungent gassy green notes are subdued
Very sweet and tenacious, fruity, American I Concord-Grape-like odor.
Mild, but tenacious, green-herbaceous and woody odor.
Powerful, fruity+winey, green, Cognac-like or Brandy-like, slightly buttery-oily odor.
Fruity-winey, sweet-green odor of considcrabk power and diffusion.
Powerful, fruit y-green, herbaceous-sweet and somewhat winey odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful fruity-green, diffusive odor, more fruity, less green than the Acetate or the butyrate
Powerful, fruity, sweet and diffusive odor, reminiscent of Apple, Pear and Pineapple.
Mild balsamic-green, somewhat herbaceous and refreshing odor of considerable tenacity

It blends very well with Galbanum and with the “’carbinols” conventionally used in Iiyacinth or Lilac bases, and its greenness is different from the diffusive odor of some of the lower esters of the Hexcnyl series. Its peculiar dry note seems to rule out any predominant fruity tone which is so common in many of these esters.
Dry-green, petal-like and vegetable-like odor with waxy-sweet undertones. To some observers, it also appears floral
Powerful and very sweet, but refreshingly citrusy, floral odor of good tenacity.
Rich and powerful, warm-fruity odor of a distinctly ““unripe”AppIe-Pineapple character and pleasant overall freshness.
Mild and sweet, green-rosy-mossy odor with undertones of herbaceous-woody, somewhat condiment-vcgetabic-like character
Green-mossy, very tenacious odor with variabie amounts of the almost unavoidable honey-like notes
Sweet, powerful, intensely green, somewhat ‘“vegetable’”-like but also slightly fatty, oily odor.
Powerful and diffusive, fruity-sweet odor, free from fatty notes, More fruity, more sweet than the cis-isomer, and not so dry in its greenness
Sweet, spicy caramellic, relatively mild odor of moderate tenacity. The green notes are practically concealed in a warm-aromatic, almost spicy fragrance.
Sweet, slightly green-balsamic. tenacious odor. More green and less floral than Hexyl saiicylate.
Very powerful, in concentrated form “’gassy’’-grecn, but sweet and rich, in extremely diluted form more floral-sweet with a natural leafy note.
Fresh, powerful, yet relatively tenacious deepgreen foliage odor with slightly fruityfatty undertones.
Warm-herbaceous, green and sweet odor with a fruity undertone and moderate tenacity.
Relatively powerful, sweet-green, Apple-like odor with buttery-creamy notes.
Powerful and diffusive, sweet, butterycreamy and fruity-winey odor. It appears less Apple-like than the odor of the cis-.?-Hcxenyl iso-valeratc and much more creamy
Moderately powerful, but pleasantly freshgreen, vegetable-juicy odor with a faintly fruity undertone.
Powerful, fresh-green, vegetable type of odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Sweet fruity Berry-and-Pear-like odor, milder than Amyl acetate, less natural, slightly floral and green.
Sweeter and fruitier than Amyl acetate, less harsh. Not quite as floral as Hexyl acetate, and not as Berry-like”.
Sweet, floral-fruity odor with caramellic “jam’’-like note and good tenacity.
Warrn-herbaceous, tealike and winey odor.
Mild Cherry -anisic, fruity-floral odor with some resemblance to Hawthorne and Heliotrope. Excellent tenacity.
Sweet, but very weak, fruity-floral odor with resemblance to Plum and NeroIi. Excellent tenacity.
Woody-green, pincy-balsamic odor with sweet-herbaceous undertones.
Sweet and warm-balsamic, herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Green-fruity, somewhat harsh-floral or slightly sharp-floral odor with a vague resemblance to Gardenia and Jasmin.
Powerful, fruity, heavy odor, reminiscmt not of one particular fruit, but of a “melange” of unripe fruits.
Powcrful, but rather harsh-fruity, nondescript type of odor, even less natural than the n-Butyrate.
Sweet-fruity, but rather harsh, “chemical” odor with no obvious resemblance to any particular fruit.
Dry-fruity, unripe-Apricot-type odor with Ambre-like background.

Fatty, green-musky or slightly animal-heavy odor. Overall not as pleasant as the n-Hexyl lactone. Some observers find a similarity to Costus, others find Ambre or Musk. It is apparent that the odor is more animal, less fruity or floral than that of the other isomers.
Fresh-vegetable-like, slightly fruity odor resembling that of Stringbeans (haricots verts), but slightly more “grassy”
Oily -herbaceous, slightly green, condimentlike odor with sweet undertones.
Warm-herbaccous-balsamic odor with fruity -balsamic, yet somewhat dry and almost woody undertones. The odor has been compared to that of Cypress (twigs), but it has a somewhat sharper greenness.
Very mild, sweet-oily, slightly floral odor with a trace of herbaceous undertones.
Most of these ketones have woody, woodycamphoraceous, sweet-camphoraceous or Orris-like odors
Woody-Orris-like odor with earthy-minty, Vctivcr-like undenoncs and good tenacity.
Slightly Orris-like, mainly camphoraceousminty odor of good tenacity and considerable radiance.
Powerful, sweet-fruity odor with green herbaceous undenones.
Powerful and diffusive, dry-floral, greenherbaceous odor with considerable resemblance to part of the natural Jasmin complex.
Powerful fruity-green, oily and somewhat floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful, sharp-herbaceous, fruity-weedy grecn odor.
Refreshing, sweet-herbaceous odor with musky undertone.
Very tenacious, balsamic-Vanilla-like odor of peculiar “green”’ sweetness, giving an overall impression of Cocoa or Chocolate rather than of Vanilla.
Strongly diffusive, ethereal-fruity odor, refreshingly green and reminiscent of unripe Plums and Apples.
Peculiar fruity-earthy, yet sweet and Pearlike odor with a trace of fungus-like undertone.
Dry-herbaceous, somewhat musty-metallic odor with fruity-earthy undertones, not nearly as pleasant as the n-Hexylester, and not as mushroom-like.
Mild, green-herbaceous odor with swcetspicy undenones and a vague resemblance to Labdanum.

Fresh-green, but rather weedy, more sharpsour- green than ordinary leafy odor, yet with swee~-juicy undertones. The green notes have been compared to those of freshly cut stems of hollyhock. other observers find a Violet-leaf note. The overall impression is that of a rather unpleasant greenness, from a perfumery point of view.
Rich, leafy, Hyacinth-green odor, reminiscent of cut stems of Bluebell, and also -remotely - of Galbanum.
Powerful, green-floral, refreshing odor, reminiscent of Cyclamen and vegetables.
Powerful warm-floral and green-fruity odor with spicy-herbaceous undertones. Its topnote may appear rather sharp, but in dilution it becomes distinctly fruity-floral with a vegetable note.
Powerful, sweet, nut-like, creamy odor, in high concentration unpleasantly musty-musky in extreme dilution pleasantly oily-creamy with nutlike notes.
Very mild oily odor. In the author’s opinion, of very little interest to the perfumer
a striking similarity to the odor of “firecrackers”, or recently extinguished matches, etc. In other words, a “’burnt,sulfuraceous odor”.
Powerful, fresh-green fruity odor. Overall somewhat sharp in its note
Powerful, fruity-green, intensely sweet and diffusive odor, reminiscent of fruits and vegetables.
Winey-Cognac-like, somewhat oily, greennut-like odor. Not as fatty or sour-oily as the Caproate or the Caprylatc, overall sweeter.

Sweet-green, fruity-winey odor, overall rather weak, but tenacious and with undertones that may vary from rosy to musky, according to origin of sample. The term ““musky” is often used in panel descriptions of odors
Musty-rosy, mainly woody, and rather dry odor of moderate tenacity.
Peculiar sweetish-sour, almost “earthy” odor, resembling the odor of overripe fruit on the ground, with sweetearthy-herbaceous notes.

Very faint, sweet-herbaceous and floral odor with dry-bark-like green undertones, sometimesreferred to as ‘“Witch-Hazel-odor”.Poorer grades of this ester may be responsible for odor descriptions including the terms‘“phenolic” or ‘“ink-like” (which also refers to“-phcnolic’” in a secondary way) or “metallic”.

Green-fruity, almost medicinal or woody odor, vaguely resembling that of Blackcurrant. Traces of free Hydrogen sulfide - usually present in poor grade acids and esters - will completely ruin this odor picture.
Pleasant, sweet-green, oily-herbaceous and slightly winey odor, reminiscent of unripe berries or unripe Plums.
Very mild, earthy-root-like, mossy, mildew-Iike or slightly fungal odor. Some observers find the odor reminiscent of Parsnip.
Heavy-fruity odor reminiscent of unripe Apples, but with a musky undertone and sweetness. Overall less natural, less pleasant than the iso-Valerate.
Somewhat pungent-fruity, “unripe”-fruity, slightly herbaceous, but rich and natural odor with a dry tobacco-leaf-like undertone
Fruity, pungent odor with little or no resemblance to any particular fruit or other natural product. Its initial notes are rather sharp green, quite different from the odor of the common isomers.
Powerful, oily-green creamy-waxy odor with a discrete undertone of peppery-earthy -mushroomy character. Moderate tenacity.
MiId, sweet, herbaceous-spicy odor with a floral note. Overall weaker than Anethole,not typically anisic, and more floral

Powerful, sweet, but tarry-medicinal odor of considerable diffusion and moderate tenacity. Undertones - under the tarry notes - arc barely pmeptible as sweet-floral and actually pleasant, reminiscent of terminal notes from Ylang Ylang oil.
Very mild, Coconut-like, fruity-oily odor.
Sweet and mild, fruity-balsamic, pleasantly floral odor of moderate tenacity,
Sweet and delicately floral-spicy odor, very reminiscent of Heliotrope, in some observers” opinion more so than Heliotropine itself.
Faint ‘“metallic’”or .’ink-like” odor, presumably due to traces of free t)hcnol. other than have tendency to decompose during vacuumdistillation and break off traces of phenols.
Very powerful and penetrating, diffusive and tenacious, sweet, heavy odor, with some resemblance to Honey, Castoreum, Oakmoss, Tobacco (cured, burnt Cigar tobacco), etc.
Floral Vanilla-1ike odor, sweeter and more delicate than the odor of Vanillin
Very powerful and penetrating, greenearthy, foliage-like odor in extreme dilution becoming quite floral, Lilac-Hyacinth-like and slightly fruity.
Sweet-earthy, somewhat nut-like and floral odor, reminiscent of Hawthorne and Hyacinth, but much milder and more tenacious than the Aldehyde.
Sweet-earthy and nut-like odor resembling that of Coumarin, and with good tenacity. This Acetal is one of the least floral ones of the series, and its field of application is rather small.
Peculiar earthy-floral, musty-green odor. Some observers find a Peach-like note in this odor, but the author has not been able to personally underwrite this.
Powerful, earthy, warm-spicy and green, deep-fruity odor, reminiscent of Walnut Mushroom (Champignon) with a slightly floral-fruity undertone.
Powerful, but relatively soft, green-herbal, earthy-green odor, reminiscent of Reseda (Mignonette).
Soft floral, deep-green and very tenacious odor with some resemblance to Rose foliage or Rose calice in a bouquet of Roses.
Very earthy, sweet-green or musty, but delicate odor resembling that of Mushroom
Sweet-earthy, Mushroom-like odor with slight Iy fruity-green undertones and moderate tcnacit y.
Fresh-floral, powerful and fruity-green,slightly earthy-green odor more delicate than Phenylethylacetate, not as rosy, more Hyacinth-Lilac-like.
Sweet and honey-like, slightly fruity odor of considerable diffusive power and moderate tenacity.

Sweet-floral, but mther heavy odor of Lilac-Hyacinth type. Commercial products are mrely of high olfactory purity and may show variable amounts of harsh or “’gassy““or Acetophenone-like topnotes which partly or wholly ruin the overall odor impression.
Fruity-floral, and slightly spicy odor wilh faintly woody undertones. Overall rather heavy, but pleasant.
Fruity-woody, very sweet and somewhat heavy, but overall pleasant odor
Rather weak, woody and somewhat medicinal odor with an incense-like undertone.
Rather weak, sweet-medicinal, moderately tenacious odor with a faint resemblance to notes in Civet. Overall woody-hydrocarbonlike.
Very faint, dry-woody, slightly camphoraceous odor of considerable tenacity
Sweet odor reminiscent of mashed Bitter Almonds, but more woody and delicate.

Very unpleasant, chokingly repulsive odor, often described as reminiscent of “rotten eggs” or “decaying seaweed”, etc. both of which products are literally oozing out Hydrogen sulfide in the state described.
Peculiar woody -smokey odor, reminiscent of the Cresols, but sweeter and milder, more smokey, less medicinal.
Powerful and rich, sweet-floral odor with resemblance to Lilac. Slightly animal undertone and good tenacity.
The pure chemical is virtually odorless. Commercial grades may carry a faintly phenolic odor
Anisic-minty odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous and Nut-like, tobaccolike odor of considerable power and good tenacity
Sweet and moderately warm-herbaceous odor, reminiscent at the same time of Anise and Fennel.
Sweet-herbaceous odor, reminiscent ofAnisc and Fennel, but not as sweet as Hydroquinone met hylet hylet her.
Sweet, “aromatic” odor, reminiscent of Anisole, but much weaker and milder, not harsh. Chemically pure l-iydroquinone monomethylether has very little odor.
Sweet and rather heavy-floral, also somewhat herbaceous odor, reminiscent of New Mown Hay or Hawthorne in higher concentration, almost Mimosa-like in extreme dilution.
Heavy-floral, somewhat herbaceous or woody-haylike odor of considerable tenacity.
Herbaceous-sweet, somewhat dry odor. Overall rather mild and not very tenacious.
Very faint, sweet-woody-balsamic odor. Chemically pure aldehyde is virtually odorless.
Refreshingly green-vegetable odor reminiscxmt of Cucumber, Watermelon (rind) and very young, undeveloped leaves. There is an almost citrusy freshness in this delicate greenness.
Sweet-floral, at firsdtelicate and refreshingly mild, but often increasing in odor strength after short olfactory study. The floral notes are mild, light and resemble Lily of the Valley.
Very faint green-floral odor of considerable tenacity.
Its odor is very mild, in fact, some observers find it practically odorless.
Very faint, green and fresh-floral odor of good tenacity. Some observers find this material to be practically odorless.
Very mild floral odor, producing a rosy effect in compositions, but barely showing an odor of its own. Excellent tenacity.
Very sweet, heavy-floral and extremely tenacious odor of Honey -Orangeblossom- Magnolia type.
Sweet, floral odor of great tenacity
Very sweet, heavy-floral Orange-blossom to Lindenflower type odor of considerable tenacity
Heavy-sweet, herbaceous-floral odor of excellent tenacity.
Very mild (weak) clean-sweet, floral odor of considerable tenacity. The floral type is Rose-Peony, typically less green, less Lily or Muguet than the aldehyde.
Soft, sweet, balsamic-floral odor with pleasant ethereal overtones and moderate tenacity.
Very faint woody-medicinal odor with a nut-like, herbaceous tone.
Sweet-herbaceous, somewhat fungoid or mushroomy odor, in dilution reminiscent of Amylvinyicarbinol and related Lavender trace materials.
Dry-woody, camphoraceous-medicinal type of odor. Very good tenacity.
Sweet, balsamic-floral odor of considerable tenacity. lt has notes in common with Vanillin but is not as sweet and not as Vanilla-like, more floral and slightly greener.
Powerful dry-camphoraceous odor with l slightly floral undertone and moderate tenacity.
Swccamphoraccous-minty, Lime-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity
intensely sweet, fruity -brcadlikc, pleasant odor of immense tenacity in spite of considerable volatility at room temperature
Powerful ethereal, fruity-green, vinous odor of poor tenacity.
Warm-aromatic odor, rather pungent and not typically reminiscent of any specific natural material. Somewhat haylike, also remotely floral, heavy and sweet, with good tenacity
Aromatic, somcw hat medicinal, warm, woody -herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Woody -rootlike, d~-sweet and very tenacious odor with resemblance to Vetiver, Cedar and Amyns.
Fresh-green, oily and slightly floral odor, particularly in dilution. Moderate tenacity
Warm-herbaceous, whey-ethereal odor, remotely resembling that of Hungarian Chamomile. a similarity to Hay and Caramellic, Tobacco etc. is often pcrccpliblc.
Warm. herbaceous, slightly musty-mushroom-like odor with nut-like undertones andmoderate tenacity.
Musty-herbaceous, sweet. slightly earthy odor of moderate tenacity.
The odor is delicately sweet, light and floral
Rich, sweet, musky odor of good tenacity. Not quite as delicately ‘animal- as Cyclopentadccanolide,
Warm-herbaceous, somewhat earthy or Walnut-like, sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet and slightly pungent-buttery-nut-like odor.
Strong and tenacious musky odor. The Musk note is deficient in delicate animal tones,
Oily-pungent, somewhat cheesy-nut-like odor, overall rather unpleasant. The herbaceous notes are concealed in an oily character which leans toward the rancid note.
Very sweet, fruity and warrrt odor resembling Raspberry preserve and having a moderate tenacity.
Faint, sweet fruity-floral odor. mainly rosy.
Peculiar warm-herbaceous, almost caramellic odor, yet with little resemblance to a natural product
Musty-herbaceous, rather sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Comparatively powerful, warm-herbaceous ethereal odor with a peculiar resemblance to Pyridine or Quinoline, yet not nearly as penetrating.
Sweet-floral, almost rosy and slightly musty woody odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Fresh, vegetable-green odor with a floral undertone and good tenacity. some observers tind the odor similar to that of Watermelon.

The orfho- and the mem-isomers have sweet, floral-balsamic odors while the ptvw-isomer is so weak that it can bc classified as absolutely uninteresting, except for academic studies. A product containing a mixture primarily of the orfho- and the meru-isomer has been recommended for usc in soap perfumes.
use as a preservative with mild antioxidant effect
Very mild, herbaceous-haylike odor with variable amounts of rootlike or pungent notes.
Powdery -dustry, dry, Orris-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Practically odorless

Extremely diffusive and powerful odor, almost tarry-repulsive and choking when concentrated, but in concentrations lower than 0.10. or in compositions, it shows powerful floral notes and pleasant radiation.
Freshly prepared Indolene with a nearpcrfect chemical balance has a mild, delicate, but extremely tenacious floral odor of considerable radiation.
Powerful, sweet-floral and very tenacious odor of Hyacinth-Honeysuckle character.
Sweet, oily-herbaccous, warm odor with floral-balsamic undenones. There is some resemblance to Labdanum notes and the tenacity is moderate
Warm-woody, balsamic-floral odor of deep sweetness and moderate tenacity. Its rcsemblancetotheodorof Violet flowers is legendary.
Warm, woody, somewhat dry odor with a fruity undertone
This ketone is mentioned only for the sake of completing the picture of lonone isomers.
Intensely sweet, fruity-woody odor of great volume and excellent tenacity, suggestive of precious woods with floral background notes and a similarity to Raspberry.
Very sweet, deep, warm-fruity and tenacious odor with a woody undertone. Strikingly reminiscent of the odor of dried figs, dates or dried bananas. Often described as “jam-like”.
Heavy and very sweet-floral, “’Oriental”-balsamic odor of excellent tenacity.
Sweet-fruity, caramellic-marrnclade-like odor with woody undertones and good tcnacity.
The odor is soft, warm, Orris-Violet-lihe,sweet and extremely diffusive
Most perfumers agree that bera-lronc resembles befa-lonone in odor except that the Irene is somewhat more powerful.
Warm, soft, woody-Violet-like odor, gener-ally considered slightly weaker and not as radiant as that of alpha-lrone.
Powerful oily-fruity, rather fatty and tenacious odor with floral petal-like notes, There is some resemblance to the odor of refined linseed oil, and the fruity notes resemble Peach or Apricot.

Diffusive, warm-spicy, somewhat fruity, but in dilution more floral odor of good tenacity The pure material has notes reminiscent of Celery seed, some find it “’bread-like”, others find it ““fruity”,“waxy” etc.

“iso-Jasmonc”” is a name given to commercial products of very widely different composition. The fact that there are several “prices” also emphasize the difference in opinion as to which odor is closest to that of natural Jasmonc, and which is the most desirable for general perfumery use.
DilTusive, sweet-fatty, somewhat floral and slightly oily-fruity odor of good tenacity. The odor is less floral and more fatty than that of the ris-isorncr
Pleasant, dry-woody, Ambre-like and somewhat Orris-like odor of great tenacity and remarkable odor, uniformity
Chemically pure Lactic acid is odorless, but commercial grades have a faint odor reminiscent of Buttermilk
Virtually odorless when pure, or of good commercial grade
Oily-herbaceous, warm-rosy odor reminiscent of Geraniol and with a slightly spicy note. There are notes resembling those found in Cumin alcohol.
Very sweet, fruity-herbaceous and slightly warm to spicy odor of some resemblance to the odor of Linalyl propionate.
Very sweet, warm-herbaceous, Tea-like and Clary-Sage-like odor of good tenacity. Slightly fruity, fruit-preserve-like undertones.
Warm and mild, pleasant odor, balsamicsweet, slightly woody and very tenacious.
Mild caramellic odor, or almost odorless. Decomposition causes acid odor and pungency.
Sweet floral and very tenacious odor with Lily -Lindenblossom character and Orangeblossom undertones.
Fresh, light and sweet citrusy odor with strong resemblance to Orange peel oil.
refreshing, light, very clean odor, not reminiscent of Citrus fruits in particular, and not recalling any specific Pine or Mint.
Very faint, sweet-balsamic-herbaceous odor of good tenacity
Light and refreshing, floral-woody odor with a faintly citrusy note.
Powerful sweet-woody, penetrating odor with floral-woody-earthy undertones.
Soft and sweet fresh and floral odor with an overall “natural” note. It is somewhat more woody than the acetate, not as “candylike”.
Sweet, floral-fruity odor recalling Bergamot and Pear.
Soft-floral and very tenacious Lindenblossom-Acacia-Neroli type odor.
Balsamic-floral, Bergamot-fruity odor of good tenacity.
Heavy-fruity, sweet and Bergamot-like, Pearlike odor of moderate tenacity.

Peculiar dry-fruity and somewhat animal odor. The term “metallic” is sometimes included in the odor description of this ester, and not infrequently met with in description of Hexyl esters and hexoates.
Mild and somewhat dry-fruity, herbaceous odor of good tenacity. There is some resemblance to the odor of unripe Peaches.
Mild and balsamic-sweet, slightly herbaceous-floral, Muguet-like, Lily-like odor of great tenacity and uniformity.
Mild, floral odor of good tenacity.
Very fresh citrusy, green-Bergamot-like, herbaceous Coriander odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Floral, slightly green, Mimosa- and Lilylike odor of good tenacity
Sweet and very tenacious, mild but “heavyfloral” odor with balsamic-Lavender-Honeysuckle notes, sometimes with Orangeblossom character. The odor varies with the method of preparation.
Sweet-herbaceous, powerful odor with somewhat medicinal-woody undertones and moderate tenacity.
Mild oily-waxy, delicately floral Rose-Lily type odor of good tenacity.
Mildly floral, intensely sweet Neroli-Rose type odor of great tenacity and with variable amounts of Honey-like undertones, according to origin of sample or method of production.
Fruity-floral, fresh and very sweet Bergamot- Muguet-Pear-like odor of moderate tenacity
Peculiar, sweet-herbaceous, somewhat caramellic odor with floral-herbaceous undertones and moderate tenacity.
Very mild odor, in fact it appears odorless to many observers. Musky-sweet, faintly floral fruity odor of good tenacity.
Fruity, Citrus-Lavender type odor of moderate tenacity. Overall rather heavy and not typically refreshing. More herbaceous than the lower esters
Sweet, fruity, citrusy odor, rich, Apple-like, Clary-Sage and Tea-like undertones and moderate tenacity.
Pungent, yet light and nauseating-ethereal-herbaceous odor with sweet, breadlike undertones.
Powerful and diffusive minty-tarry odor of poor tenacity
Faintly caramellic odor.
Odorless or having a very faint, caramellic acrid odor.
Practically odorless.
Warm-fruity, caramellic-sweet odor with emphasis on the caramellic note in the dry state, while solutions of Maltol show a pronounced fruity, jam-like odor of Pineapple, Strawberry type
Caramellic-sweet, but rather pungent odor of good tenacity.
This material has been used to prepare the so-called “Bitter Almond Water”, a mild flavor corrigens employed in pharmacy.
Practically odorless.
Very delicate, woody, dry-sweet, and extremely tenacious odor with a distinct and typical Ambregris-like undertone.
Somewhat harsh, gassy and sweet odor, reminiscent of Fennel, and of poor tenacity.
Typical “hydrocarbon’’-odor, similar to that of para-Cymene, rather harsh, but in extreme dilution quite refreshing, almost citrusy. Poor tenacity
Sweet, haylike-minty odor, sometimes re-ferred to as “Lactone’’-odor.
Pungent, woody -minty, slightly camphoraceous odor.
Refreshing, light, diffusive odor with a sweet pungency
Odor very similar to that of Menthol, but somewhat more woody, not quite as sweet, and the cooling sensation is not perceptible at the same low concentration as it is in laevo-Menthol.
fresh non-citrusy and non-woody “lift” may be desirable.
Minty-refreshing and diffusive odor of moderate tenacity and slightly woody-dry undertones.
Powerful, refreshing and clean-minty odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild and sweet, slightly fruity -herbaceous, minty odor. Quite refreshing and delicately floral.
Mildly minty and somewhat woody-herbaceous odor. Less floral-fruity and less delicate than the laevo-Menthyl acetate.
Mild, sweet-floral odor of great tenacity.
To the author’s knowledge, it is not used as a fragrance material in perfumes (or flavors).
It has a mild, sweet-herbaceous odor re-miniscent of Clary Sage with a rosy undertone
Herbaceous-refreshing and slightly minty odor with an earthy-green undertone. Moderate tenacity. Some observers find a Narcissuslike floralness.
mild-floral and extremely sweet and tenacious notes
Mild and sweet herbaceous-floral odor with resemblance to Rose and Peony and with a trace of minty undertones. Good tenacity
Almost odorless when pure.
Sweet-herbaceous, somewhat balsamic minty and root-like odor of good tenacity.
Aromatic-herbaceous, ethereal odor, comparatively diffusive, reminiscent of Thyme, overall pleasant, not as gassy as Cymene.
The commercial grade has an unpleasant odor, sometimes gassy, green or vegetablepungent, acrylic
Extremely diffusive, “gassy “-sweet odor, in high concentration pungent and irritating, only in extreme dilution fairly pleasant herbaceous- balsamic and remotely Orange-like.
Powerful and warm, green-rosy, diffusive odor.
Powerful, penetrating and slightly gassy, overall fruity-ethereal odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, somewhat pungent-fruity, slightly gassy odor, in dilution reminiscent of Pineapple.
Powerful and sweet; herbaceous-floral odor of Bergamot-type.
Peculiar fatty vinegear-like odor, in dilution fairly pleasant.
Mild, oily-floral and sweet odor of considerable tenacity. There is some resemblance to Acacia or Lilac, but samples from various suppliers show considerable difference in odor type
Faint, sweet-balsamic and floral odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and powerful Rose-like odor of good tenacity. The type is mainly green-balsamic with some resemblance to Hydratropyl alcohol, yet more rosy and powerful.
Sweet Vanilla-like odor with variable amounts of phenolic-medicinal notes, most conceivably appearing in impure materials.

Mild, pleasant, floral odor of excellent tenacity. The sweetness and floralness is rather nondescript and it has been described with floral names from Rose to Hyacinth, from Tuberose to Lilac and Acacia.
Sweet and warm, spicy-floral odor of considerable tenacity. Has a peculiar fruity undertone resembling notes in Tagetes oil.
Warm and spicy-herbaceous odor. Less fruity and less floral than the odor of the orlho-isomer. Good teriacity.
Fresh, somewhat green, floral-sweet Lilylike odor with some resemblance to Hydroxycitronelial and Cyclamal.
Faintly herbaceous, sweet and very tenacious odor, but overall disappointingly weak.
Camphoraceous-woody, slightly green and sweet, Melon-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-spicy. Vanilla-like, woody balsamic odor of good tenacity.
Sweet-herbaceous odor of Anise-Fennel type, of good tenacity.

Powerful green, sap-like, sweet and somewhat floral odor of moderate tenacity. Some observers describe the odor as “florist-shop”- like, and it is true that the slightly earthy undertones contribute to this more complex, but interesting odor.
Sweet-balsamic, earthy-floral odor of considerable tenacity, but relatively weak overall
Warm-herbaceous-floral, slightly spicy odor with some resemblance to Hyacinth and Cananga. It displays a pleasant, deep-fruity undertone with slight resemblance to Blackcurrant and Grape.
Faint, warm-herbaceous odor with some resemblance to Wintergreen, but sweeter and much milder, somewhat more tenacious.
Sweet-herbaceous, Wintergreen-Anise-Fen-nel type odor of moderate tenacity.
Dry-musty, herbaceous, Leather-like and Tobacco-like odor of considerable tenacity
Sweet-green and somewhat floral odor”with good tenacity and rich, sweet, flower-stem-like undertones.
Sweet-floral, slightly green odor of good tenacity. It has notes resembling those of Lilac, Heliotrope and Hawthorne at the same time.
Mild, yet somewhat “gassy” Hawthorne- Anise type odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and comparatively powerful floral odor with a pronounced green-herbal undertone. The sweetness tends to be almost buttery-creamy, but not more than what is agreeable.
Sweet and woody-green, moderately floral odor of fair tenacity
Intensely sweet, creamy-floral odor of good tenacity. The undertones are somewhat herbaceous, but only add to the pleasant, natural overall character. Dilution call out intensely fruity-sweet notes.
Sweet, somewhat pungent, buttery-creamy odor with floral notes upon proper dilution. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Faint, but very sweet and mildly pungent ““medicinal’’-Vanilla-like odor with notes re- calling Guaiacol, Salicylaldehyde, Coumarin and Vanillin at the same time
Sweet and very tenacious floral-spicy odor with a somewhat medicinal undertone. Less warm than the rnera-isomer, and not quite as Vanilla-like.
Caramellic-fruity odor with a distinctly buttery topnote and good tenacity.
owerful, spicy, Clove-like odor with a penetrating, warm, but also somewhat tarry undertone and good tenacity
Fresh batches may be almost odorless but carry a faint odor or acquire an increasingly perceptible, piney-woody odor of considerable tenacity and with a balsamic sweetness.
Sweet, and extremely diffusive, ethereal-fruity odor of very poor tenacity. In fact, one must hurry to smell it from a perfume blotter before it is completely evaporated.
Ethereal-green, winey odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Pungent, almost harsh, but warm, sweet and floral odor of moderate tenacity. The Methyl-derivative is more fruity in the direction of Methylbenzoate, and deep-sweet as Hydroquinone dimethyiether.
Ethereal, warm-herbaceous odor of poor tenacity
Powerful, sweet but somewhat choking odor when undiluted, sweet, almost floral, yet heavy in extreme dilution.
Very pure Methyl alcohol has only a mild odor, but commercial grade Methylalcohol will usually display a somewhat pungentgassy topnote followed by a sweeter ethereal odor of very poor tenacity,
This material has only a very faint odor, and is probably odorless when absolutely pure.
Mild and pleasant fruity odor, sweeter than iso-Amylacetate, less Pear-like, more Bananalike, moderate to poor tenacity
can be used in general as a floralizeriblender with some fixative value.
Powerful, but rather dry, floral odor of good tenacity. The floral notes are most perceptibk in actual -use, while the material per se displays a non-descript, slightly greenwood floralcy.
Powerful, floral-fruity, Jasmin-like odor of good tenacity and considerable radiation.
It offers a rare type of odor, only occasionally needed. But it gives pleasant effects with Olibanum and Opopanax, with Elemi, etc.
Penetrating, fruity-spicy light and volatile odor with resemblance to the fresher notes in Cinnamon bark.
Sweet-herbaceous odor with a deep floral undertone and a trace of a fruity character.
Buttery-caramellic, sweet and lasting odor.
Sweet-herbaceous, delicately floral odor of good tenacity. It bears some resemblance to Lilac, Lindenblossom and Magnolia.
Sweet and somewhat woody-floral odor of rather nondescript character, vaguely reminiscent of Rose, but with a chemical-woody undertone and considerable tenacity
Musty-fruity and somewhat dry-floral odor reminiscent of Concord grapes, Orangeblossom, and having good tenacity.
Warm and sweet, deepfloral, heavy odor, reminiscent of exotic flowers, Tuberose, Gar-denia, etc. and with a remote resemblance to refined Labdanum.
Pungent, heavy-sweet, deep-floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Its fruity undertones resemble Runes and Blackcurrant, while the heavy floral tones recall notes of Tuberose or Longoza.
Very faint odor, remotely rosy, sweet, musty. Overall softer and perhaps even weaker than Benzophenone.
Very sweet odor of rather gassy-pungent character when undiluted, becoming floralsweet, heavy, when diluted.
Powerful fruity and intensely sweet odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes resemble Cherry - milder and sweeter, less pungent than Benzyl acetate, also less floral.
Sweet woody, somewhat spicy and warm odor of moderate tenacity. It has undertones sometimes described as fruity,
Sweet and somewhat floral-green odor with a Honey-like undertone and moderate to poor tenacity.
Fresh-floral, slightly green and fruity odor with a Hyacinth-like note, remotely resembling that of Hydratropyl acetate.
Peculiar, rather sharp-metallic, fruity-rosy odor of poor tenacity.
Green, rather sharp and unnatural odor of moderate to poor tenacity, The odor bears some similarity to that of para-Cresol ethyl ether, but is not quite as floral.
Sweet floral-herbaceous and quite lasting odor, remotely reminiscent of Lilac. The sweetness resembles Anise and Vanilla
Warm and sweet, deep-floral, slightly fruity odor of moderate tenacity.
Very sweet, fruity-floral odor of moderate tenacity. The fruity notes are less pronounced, the sweet-floral notes more pronounced than in Benzylpropionate.
Powerful, oily-herbaceous, somewhat earthy, fungus-like odor of considerable radiance. Poor tenacity.
Powerful oily-green somewhat herbaceous, but overall “chemical” or lun-natural” odor of poor tenacity. Repeated inhalation of its vapors cause coughing.
Refreshing, green-ethereal, herbaceousfruity odor of poor tenacity.
Somewhat sharp-floral, Jasmin-like fruity odor of good tenacity.
trans-isomer: Powerful floral-woody and tenacious odor. cis-isomer: Camphoraceous-minty, powerful and tenacious odor.
Sweet, musty-fruity, somewhat floral odor with a dry-green undertone. Overall, not a very “natural” odor. Fair to good tenacity.
Sharp minty, herbaceous, Rue-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Sweet anisic-green, slightly earthy-spicyfruity odor with pulegonic-minty emphasis and fair to good tenacity.
Warm-caramellic, fruity odor reminiscent of Strawberry.
Sweet-fruity, ethereal flavor in dilutions below 20 ppm.
Sweet, somewhat woody-camphoraceous odor of good tenacity. The fruity topnote seems to be accompanied by a dry undertone which gives a very unusual and peculiar combination odor.
Warm, oily-herbaceous floral and sweetearthy odor resembling certain notes of the Jasmin fragrance picture. Moderate tenacity and excellent stability.
Herbaceous-fruity, slightly earthy odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, green-ethereal, gassy odor, unpleasantly choking when undiluted, but quite pleasant, fresh-green when diluted.
Powerful, choking odor when undiluted, but in extreme dilution the odor becomes tolerable, almost pleasant fruity -’’fermented” with a peculiar note resembling that of roasted Cocoa or Coffee.
Very diffusive and penetrating, sweet-ethereal, fruity odor. In extreme dilution reminiscent of Apple peel with a slightly fatty Peachlike undertone.
Milder and sweeter odor as compared to the n-butyrate, less Apple-like, more Apricotlike.
Pungent, acrid odor reminiscent of Roquefort cheese and other cheeses, but not quite as repulsive and ~inging as the odor of n-Valeric acid or i.w-Valerie acid.
Pleasant, fruity, slightly creamy odor with vague resemblance to Banana.
Peculiar, sweet-and-dry, fruity-woody odor of good tenacity.
Oily-winey, slightly fruity odor when pure. Samples containing traces of Decanoic caid will have a perceptible and usually undesirable fatty undertone.
Powerful ethereal and diffusive, sweet odor of Pineapple-Apricot type.
used in flavors
Powerful winey-fruity, Orange-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent, sweet-aromatic odor, somewhat related to the prototype .’Quinone”’-type odor, but heavier, less buttery, more medicinal. Very tenacious and penetrating.
Powerful, yet very tenacious, fruity -balsamic odor, in extreme dilution more fruity, Strawberry-like, less balsamic
Sweet, balsamic-floral, tenacious odor of  “Oriental” type. It is less “Cinnamon-like”, and more %tyrax-like” than Cinnamic alcohol,
Powerful, sweet-herbaceous, but primarily Cinnamon-spicy, warm odor of moderate tenacity.
Pleasant, sweet-oily, green and very faintly spicy -herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Mild, warm, oily -herbaceous, slightly greenwood odor.
Sweet and slightly spicy, warm, yet refreshing odor with distinctly fruity notes, in dilution appearing Strawberry-like. Good tenacity
the base prepared with alpha-Methylcinnamic aldehyde is only intensely yellow and has a powerful, deep-sweet, floral-balsamic odor of interesting possibilityies.
Sweet and refreshing Lemon-like fruity odor of moderate tenacity. Not nearly as ‘lemony” as Citral, but sweeter;
Virtually odorless when pure, the commercial material has a faint, ethereal-fruity, bland odor.
Sharp, but not harsh, Lemon-like and slightly green odor.
Refreshing, winey-green, fruity and Brandylike, Apple-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Sweet-rosy, moderately tenacious odor. Less minty, but also less fresh-diffusive when compared to Citronellol, overall lighter, milder, more lasting.
Fresh-rosy, green-leafy type of odor with a “wet vegetable” note of attractive naturalness. Moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful and rich, Tonka-like, sweet-herbaceous odor, somewhat drier than that of Coumarin.
Dry, hay-like, rather weak Coumarin-type odor of good tenacity.
Sweet, rather musty, herbaceous-woody, tenacious odor.
Semi-dry, herbaceous Tonka-like, but rather weak odor, more delicate than Coumarin, and more Fig- or Date-like in its fruity deep sweet ness.
Musty, slightly animal and leathery, tenacious odor with sweet-herbaceous undertones. The animal notes are very discrete, remotely resembling those of Costus, being more wood than herbaceous
Very weak, semi-sweet, woody-herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, sharp and greenfruity odor of poor tenacity.
Refreshing, vegetable-green, slightly earthy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Somewhat harsh, minty-almondy, rather chemical odor.
Fresh, camphoraceous-minty, but rather weak odor of poor tenacity. In the undiluted state, the material has a sharp topnote.
This isomer is the most pleasant-minty smsliing of the three. Although not possessing a very natural minty note, it is not as harsh or camphoraceous as one usually observes in chemicals of this type
Warm-herbaceous-spicy, penetrating and diffusive odor of Cumin-Caraway type.
Sweet-floral odor with rosy-fruity undertones and moderate tenacity.
Powerful, sweet-fruity-floral, Lavender-like odor of good tenacity

Powerful fruity and sweet odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes are rather violent, not “natural”, but may in proper dilution remind of Raspberry. There is a certain floralness of Jasmin character to the overall odor. The initial sharpness resembles that of Cedarleaf oil, camphoraceous-cineolic,
Intensely sweet, powerful, fruity odor of Raspberry-type with herbaceous-anisic undertones. Moderate tenacity.
Semi-sweet, woody-rosy odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet-floral, slightly green odor of moderate to good tenacity. The floral notes are rather nondescript, and the effect is more of a floral “lift” than truly an added floralcy.
Pungent-anisic, sweet odor of floral-herbaceous character and moderate tenacity.
Floral-green, powerful and moderately tenacious odor.
Sweet musky, pleasantly animal odor of excellent tenacity,
The odor of this isomer is musky, sweet and extremely tenacious,
Odor of Musk, sweet, extremely tenacious, but slightly weaker and not quite as sweet as that of Muscone
Delicate, but extremely tenacious musky odor, upon dilution developing more woody notes,
Green-leafy, herbaceous, slightly oily and “choking” odor of poor tenacity. Overall not nearly as natural as the alifatic alcohols.
Sweet and very powerful, caramellic-spicy odor, described by different individuals with quite a variation of terms and phrases: Walnut – Maple - Licorice - Celery - Tobacco etc.
Powerful, creamy -caramellic, buttery odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful caramellic, somewhat sharp, Walnut-like intensely sweet odor of good tenacity.
Very diffusive and penetrating green-fruity odor of Apple-Pineapple and green-Citrus type.
Powerful, sweet, diffusive green-fruity odor of Pineapple type.
Sweet, musky odor, but weaker and less “natural’’-soft, slightly more “woody “’ than Cyclopentadecanone, the desirable isomer.
Sweet-fruity, Pear-like odor, also with some resemblance to Benzylacetate.
Fruity, foliage-green odor of excellent diffusion and moderate tenacity.

Powerful, waxy-green, floral and slightly earthy odor of moderate tenacity. More waxy and more floral than the desirable Amyl heptincarbonate, which is generally considered the most “’Violet” like of the series.
Dry-waxy, moderately powerful, but tenacious odor. In dilution quite refreshing, but lacks the Ambregris-like notes of the lower homologue

Fruity, Orange-peel-like odor with sweetwaxy- floral notes, resembling part of the Orangeblossom-fragrance. There are fatty notes, but in suitable dilution only pleasantly fatty wit bout any trace of rancid notes.

Warm haylike, heavy-sweet, herbaceous odor with a Coconut undertone and excellent tenacity. It has a much softer, Coconut-like character than Coumarin, and does not have the pungent-herbaceous, New Mown Haylike note of that material.
Its odor differs considerably from that of the conventional members of the Eugenol family in that it is only slightly spicy, not very powerful, but sweet and somewhat herbal in character.
This chemical is briefly mentioned, although information about it is still very scarce.
Musty-sweet, deep-floral and fruity odor of good tenacity. It bears some resemblance to the odor of oil from Orange leaf water and Orange flower water, not really a refreshing odor.
Mild-green and floral, slightly balsamic, very tenacious odor of pleasant, natural overall character.
Sweet-caramellic odor with a mildly fruity undertone.
Mild winey-fruity, ethereal odor of poor tenacity.
Mild, green-rosy odor of good tenacity. Some observers find a fruity note in this odor
Sweet, mildly green-rosy, somewhat “metallic’”but overall pleasant odor of good tenacity.
This alcohol represents another type of many chemicals developed in search of new and interesting Sandalwood odors.
Sweet and refreshing, citrusy-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Heavy, sweet-floral and warm-herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
Very mild oily-floral, warm odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, Slightly spicy-floral odor of good tenacity. The floral notes resemble Rose, Tuberose, Gardenia, while the spicyfruity notes are of the Grape-Wintergreen theme.
Deep-sweet, Walnut-Celery-like, warm and tenacious odor with emphasis on the Nut-like character.
Very diffusive, minty-camphoraceous “bitter” odor of considerable penetrating effect
Powerful and diffusive, “gassy’’-green and slightly fruity odor of poor tenacity.
Peculiar green-floral, rather dry, mossy, almost leather-like odor (not phenolic, but sweet-leather, cured skins)

Fresh-green and floral, moderately tenacious odor. Sometimes described in literature as “leathery”, however, the author believes that such description must be based upon observations on impure material.
This phenolether has come out of extensive research in the Vanillin field.
Powerful, fruity-green, herbaceous and sweet odor of moderate tenacity. There is an almost Basil-like spiciness or anisic note of very natural character in this odor.
Ethereal, slightly nauseating odor, not exactly pleasant.

Its odor is somewhat similar to that of DMBC, however, more dry, slightly woodycamphoraceous, overall not so floral. It has a pleasant greenness and blends well with Oakmoss, Amylsalicylate, herbaceous oils, Terpineol, Heliotropine, Coumarin, etc., but does not point in any specific floral direction.
Fresh-floral, slightly green and fruity odor of fair to good tenacity.
Sweet caramellic-fruity, ethereal odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Sharper and less fruity, more caramellic-ethereal
Very sweet, powerfully fruity, Raspberrylike odor of good tenacity.
Sweet-herbaceous, slightly spicy odor of considerable diffusive power

Peculiar musty-tealike, warm and mildly spicy, slightly earthy, tenacious odor. The warm notes are mostly herbaceous, the spicy notes very subdued, and there is an overall resemblance to notes of Ginger and Tea.
Sweet and warm, mild floral-tealike, very slightly spicy and very tenacious odor. Of the common derivatives of Eugenol, it is one of the most Carnation-like.
Sweet, somewhat earthy-musty odor of excellent tenacity. The earthy sweetness resembles that of Walnut and Moss, but with emphasis on the wet-mossy type.
Very ethereal-diffusive odor of winey Chloroforme ype.
Balsamic-sweet, slightly fruity, tenacious odor.
Sweet-spicy,warm, and slightly caramellic odor
Fruity-woody odor, but rather sharp-green when undiluted. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Berry-like fruity, winey and rather heavy odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Some observers find a nauseating or fungus-like Tobacco odor.
Mild, but warm, Cinnamon-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Compared to Furanacrolein it is perhaps milder, but also less woody, softer and sweeter.
Fresh-rosy odor, sweeter and slightly more citrusy than Geraniol, moderate to poor tenacity.
Weak, but delicately rosy and tenacious odor. The mildness or weakness of this odor is often translated as “musky”,
Green-leafy, slightly “weedy”, oily-rosy, but overall refreshing “outdoorish” odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Sweet-floral, slightly fruity odor of Bergamot-Geranium-Rose type- and fair to g~od tenacity.
Fresh, yet warm-spicy, Cinnamon-like and simultaneously Coconut-like slightly fruity odor with sweet, oily-Nut-like undertones. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Fatty-oily, rather unpleasant sour odor, but not sweat-like, rancid as the normal Caprylic acid.
Intensely fruity, sweet and slightly oily odor of moderate tenacity. The odor is less herbaceous, also less floral than that of the normal Octyl acetate.
Oily-green, herbaceous-citrusy odor with resemblance to Coriander and unripe berries.
Oily-green, pungent-herbaceous, grassy and diffusive odor with fresh and green-fruity notes and moderate to poor tenacity
Oily-green, almost earthy or slightly mustyfungoid odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very powerful, penetrating vegetable-green foliage type odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Fruity-green, slightly waxy-berry-like odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive woody-green, also slightly citrusy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful fruity-green, slightly oily-floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, fruity-herbaceous and sweet-floral odor of good tenacity
Powerful, fatty-fruity, oily and slightly herbaceous odor. Overall not very pleasant.
Tart-green, fresh-foliage-like odor, resembling aldehydic-green odors.  The odor has been described as resembling that of freshly crushed berries of mountain ash.
Fruity-floral, slightly fatty and herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Green-musty, earthy-sweet and fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Sharp-green,’ very diffusive odor of very poor tenacity.
Powerful and very diffusive, foliage-green, somewhat pungent, but also sweet odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Delicately floral, fresh-’’aldehydic” odor, much less fatty than Nonanal, more rosy, Lily-like. Moderate tenacity.

The relatively pure chemical has a pleasant, mild-green, floral-leafy and somewhat musty odor, almost reminiscent of dry tea leaves. Its woody -herbaceous notes remind of Coriander with a citrusy freshness. The odor is distinctly less fatty than that of n-Octanol-l.
Fresh-green, slightly floral-dry odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, slightly green-spicy and fruity-rosy, sweet odor, remotely resembling notes of Opopanax.
They carry the almost conventional “camphoraceous-woody” note, although material (B) can be classified as primarily floral with an Ionone-like woody note.

Warm, mild, but tenacious musky-orrislike odor. The camphoraceous notes so often en-countered in Cyclohexanone derivatives, are pleasantly subdued and generally accepted as Orris-like rather tham Camphor-like.
Dry-woody, Orrisy and tenacious odor.
Soft, creamy-floral and sweet odor of moderate to good tenaeity
Warm-spicy, sweet-floral and diffusive, yet quite tenacious odor
Green-ethereal, fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Pleasant, floral, but bitter-green, slightly musty -herbaceous and “unripe-Apple’’-fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity.

Warm-herbaceous, also camphoraceous and slightly spicy-herbal odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The ,odor has little or no resemblance to Lavender, and is thereby distinguished from Methyl hexyl ketone.
Somewhat “gassy” and very diffusive, penetrating% warm-herbaceous and aromatic odor with a vinous note, suggestive of Chamomile and other sweet herbs.
Faint, sweet, warm and tenacious odor with only a remote resemblance to Vanilla. More earthy or Nut-like and balsamic.
Powerful green, but also richly sweet odor of moderate tenacity. The green note is accompanied by a peculiar woody note, reminiscent of Atlas Cedarwood oil.
Warm, but mild, balsamic-floral odor, spicier than Hydrocinnamic alcohol, and slightly sharper. Moderate tenacity.
Mild and sweet, oily-floral, warm odor with a faint undertone of fruity-spicy character and a good tenacity.
Sweet, warm-floral, tenacious odor with mildly spicy undertones.
Sweet and mild, balsamic-rosy odor of great depth and warmth.
Warm, floral-fruity, sweet odor of moderate tenacity. Resemblance to Lily, Magnolia, Lilac.
Warm, sweet-floral, powerful Jasmine-like and fruity odor of moderate to good tenacity

Sweet-herbaceous, floral-woody odor of considerable tenacity. The floral notes are only detectable when the material is incorporated in a composition, while the sweet-woodyherbaceous notes are predominant in the material itself.
Powerful oily-fruity, heavy Peach-like odor of outstanding tenacity. Not as fatty-grassy as Undecanolide-1 ,4, and not quite as tenacious, but in dilution more natural Peach-like.
Oily-ethereal, powerful, fruity-winey odor of considerable radiation. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Very sweet and extremely tenacious floral odor of Magnolia-Orangeblossom-Acacia type
Warm floral-herbaceous odor, suggestive of certain notes of Jasmin.
Powerful and diffusive, yet very tenacious animal-indolic odor, fresher and not as repulsive as Skatole. In fact, the animal notes of this isomer are rather attractive,
The odor of this material is similar to that of Indole, but not as powerful and not nearly as floral in use-dilution.
Intensely sweet, “jam-like” fruity preservetype odor with some resemblance to the odor of dried figs. Excellent tenacity with woody undertones.
Floral and sweet-oily odor of moderate tenacity.

It is extremely versatile in character, and effects ranging from sweet floral to tobacco-like or woody are obtainable with various grades of subject material. The most refined grades, which are quite expensive, often show a very attractive “creamy” topnote and a most uniform, powdery-sweet dryout performance.
Woody-warm odor, generally considered to be a 6eta-Ionone type
Light and warm-woody, floral and at the same time Ambregris-like odor of moderate tenacity
An odor description of this (and the iso-) is therefore of little value unless based upon a commercially available sample of high-purit y single isomer.
its odor has some similarity to that of the presently desirable isomer, alpha-iso-Methylionone.
The odor of this isomer of alpha-Irene seems to be stronger than that of afpha-Ionone, but weaker than that of alpha-Irene.
lonone-like odor, but more floral than alpha-Ionone.
Powerful floral-herbaceous, sweet-tenacious odor
Sweet-floral, tenacious, Jasmin-like odor.
Oily-fatty, winey and slightly floral odor with remote resemblance to Violet
Floral-woody odor, slightly sweeter, less woody and more floral than Linalool, but also much weaker,
Light, floral-herbaceous, slightly greenwood odor with a mildly camphoraceous undertone
Ethereal-fruity, relatively diffusive odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Odor of rotten cabbage, very diffusive and objectionable.
Intensely “fishy”, penetrating odor reminiscent of cooked lobster or crayfish.” In high concentration repulsive and decay-like,
Sweet, woody-musky odor with mildly camphoraceous undertones. The odor appears weaker than that of Musk Ambrette, less sweet, yet not Ambre-like.

Fruity-winey, Grape-like and Brandy-like odor, rather heavy-sweet and slightly animal, with good tenacity. The overall picture bears some resemblance to Cognac oil and Ambretteseed absolute with a fruit-jam-like undertone.
Sweet-balsamic and mildly fruity odor of good tenacity
Very sweet, balsamic-spicy, warm and tenacious odor. The main difference from the mem-isomer is the lack of fruity notes, and the increase in sweetness and warmth.
Very tenacious, dry-sweet, woody odor, with a minty-camphoraceous note which makes it somewhat harsh. The suggested and easier to appreciate in dilution or in composition.
Musty-floral, sweet and rather heavy Orangeblossom-Mandarin-peel like odor, wineyfruity undertones.
Powerful and “gassy-green”, diffusive odor, in extreme dilution leafy-green, but still sharp, almost pungent.
Pungent ethereal-fruity odor of poor tenacity.
Floral-woody odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet floral and mildly herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet caramellic-fruity and very tenacious odor. The fruity note has some resemblance to Strawberry and “cooked” Pineapple or Apricot-preserve.
Powerful, fatty-green, somewhat oily-waxy odor of good tenacity. The oily notes have a remote resemblance to those of Coconut meat.
Sharp-green, slightly oily-leafy” odor of moderate tenacity. The odor is sharper, less natural and also less oily than that of MethyL octincarbonate.
Powerful “gassy’’-green odor, less fatty but also less “vegetable’’-like than Methyl heptin carbonate. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, yet relatively ten-acious, dry-waxy, soapy and refreshing odor,  slightly camphoraceous, penetrating.
Powerful and very diffusive, “gassy’’-green odor of poor tenacity.
Sharp-fruity, pungent-sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet and refreshing, oily-floral and herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity. The floral notes are rose-lily-like, and the herbaceous notes blend well with Lavender or Clary Sage.
Sweet, mild, herbaceous-spicy odor, weaker than Methylsalicylate, more floral. Moderate tenacity.
Extremely powerful, diffusive and penetrating sweet-sulfuraceous odor, only in dilution becoming endurable and fruity-sweet.
Weak, oily -ornsy odor with a faint, honeylike undertone and good tenacity
Harsh, heavy-sweet, tenacious odor of Mandarin-Neroli type, but not as refreshing or light as Mandarin.
Sweet, floral, but rather harsh Orangeblossom-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet and very tenacious Orangeblossomtype odor with a remotely fruity undertone.
An ill-defined product, commercially a mixture of two chemicals and an incomplete reaction product.
Warm, but nauseating, sweet-herbaceous odor with mildly tobacco-like notes and moderate tenacity. In extreme dilution it displays a sweet-herbaceous, quite pleasant odor
Musty-camphoraceous, almost minty odor with only a subdued fruity undertone. Good tenacity.
Fruit y-winey, refreshingly Nut-Coconutlike odor of moderate tenacity.
Fatty-citrusy, almost woody and in dilution Orange-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Very powerful, dry-and-fatty, woody, Orrislike odor, in extreme dilution pleasant, fresh tobacco-likeand greenwith some resemblance to Mimosa.
Powerful green, oily-nutty odor of moderate tenacity. The green notes are somewhat hampered by the presence of waxy-oily undertones.
Powerful and diffusive, dry-Ambrelike, somewhat herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity. Although often described as “aldehydic” it has much more character than the “Laurie aldehyde” (Dodecanal).
Sweet-Ambre-like, mild and semi-dry odor of mildly cinnamic-balsamic undertone and good tenacity.
it may form part of the topnote complex in Citrus bases, aldehydic-citrusy complexes, etc
Powerful and very sweet, warm-floral and tenacious odor.
Powerful and diffusive, fresh-floral, slightly waxy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Fatty-oily-fruity odor with a relatively refreshing, almost citrusy note, distinctly different from the primary-Undecanol
Oily -herbaceous, warm odor with a rootlike spiciness. Odor descriptions often include the words “Gentian” and “Juniperberry”, both of which point at highly attractive odor types.

Powerful and relatively tenacious, fattygreen odor reminiscent of Violet leaf and Coconut at the same time. However, upon dilution, the fatty-nutty notes seem to vanish and give way to a purer foliagegreen odor
Fruity-rosy, Orange-like odor, slightly herbaceous and orrisy in its oily notes. Poorer grades may show acrid or sharp topnotes.
Waxy-fatty, “ozone*’-like, in dilution very refreshing and citrusy odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet-nut-like, herbaceous-musky odor of considerable tenacity
Fruity-green, foliage-type odor, rather sharp-green when undiluted, sweeter and more fruit y when diluted below 1 ~.. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Green, Violet-leaf-like and Mimosa-1ike odor, more delicate and less acrid than the Methyl heptin carbonate. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, refreshing, dry-citrusy odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful, citrusy-Orange-like, peculiar floral type odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Odor of fatty alcohol, but sweet floral, less fatty and more floral than n-Octanol.
Powerful green odor of fresh-cut grass type, but with pronounced fatty notes
Powerful green-vegetable, Cucumber-like odor with a fruity-juicy undertone.
Sweet-green, Violet-leaf and Cucumber peel type odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Bitter-green, earthy-green, Reseda-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful and intensely green odor, but rather fatty and not typical of Violetleaf, nor is it reminiscent of any distinct natural material.
Mild-fatty, oily odor of considerable tenacity. The oily notes are pleasant, natural and not rancid
virtually odorless
Warm, woody-herbaceous and quite tenacious odor
Faint, musty and not very pleasant odor
Vinous, earthy-green odor, giving a “bitter” odor impression, sometimes referred to as “metallic”.
Powerful, fruity-green, leafy, Geraniumgreen type odor of poor tenacity.
Very diffusive, fruity-green, Banana-like odor. Overall much fresher than Amylacetate, and somewhat similar to Prenyl acetate.
Sweet-fruity, slightly green and floral odor of fair to good tenacity.
Powerful, sweet-fruity, Pear-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful and penetrating, waxy-citrusy, in dilution fresh-floral, clean and light odor with some resemblance to Dodecanal, Cyclamal and Myristic aldehyde.
Fresh-leafy, citrusy-green, dry-fruity and very diffusive odor OLpoor tenacity.
Powerful green-floral, heavy and sweet odor of considerable tenacity
Fruity-sweet, powerful odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild, sweet, slightly green-fruity odor with a minty undertone.
Very diffusive, sharp-green and in high concentration “gassy” odor of poor tenacity. Leafy-green, but still somewhat “metallic” in dilution.
Odorless crystals.
Powerful and quite diffusive honey-musky odor with traces of Jasmin-floral notes and moderate to poor tenacity

Somewhat gassy-Geranium-like odor, in high concentrations rather unpleasant, almost Leek-like in pungent vegetable notes, but in proper dilution more green-herbaceous, yet still “acetylenic” in its overall type.
Sweet, fruity-caramellic, berry-like odor of good tenacity.
Earthy-musty, but sweet and also floral, quite tenacious odor of Lilac-Hyacinth type, but less floral than Hydratropic aldehyde.
Green-fruity, in dilution sweet and moderately tenacious odor
Powerful, sweet-fruity, honey-floral odor of moderate to good tenacity
Dry-floral, earthy-green, Lilac-Jasmin-Mimosa type odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful and penetrating, green-floral, in dilution more fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity.

Samples from different sources show such difference in odor characteristics, that one is tempted to claim that the absolutely pure material is virtually odorless. Commercial grades display variable amounts of Orangeblossom or Lilac or Narcisse-type odor, depending upon the method of production and of purity of the resulting ester
Practically odorless when pure.
Peculiar fruity-floral odor with Jasmin-like notes. Moderate to good tenacity and pleasant, natural-herbaceous undertone.
More ethereal-floral and less fruity than the n-butyrate (see preceding monograph). Jasmin-like and warm-herbaceous undertones and moderate tenacity.
Mild, fruity and sweet odor of good tenacity.
Sweet, heavy and oily-floral, at times almost fatty odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Practically odorless when pure and freshly prepared. When incorporated in a composition, it may lend balsamic-floral effects to the fragrance, and supply good fixation.
Powerful and dry, green-floral, balsamicwoody odor of Mimosa-Gardenia type. Moderate to poor tenacity
Practically odorless when pure.
Fruity-floral, sweet and green odor, more refined (less harsh) than the Acetate, more typical of Gardenia and Jasmin, with some resemblance to the green topnotes of Tuberose.
Practically odorless when pure, very faint, sweet odor of great tenacity. By some observers classified as “musky”.
Herbal-fruity, floral odor of Honeysuckle-Jasmin type. Moderate tenacity.
Sweet and relatively pleasant, floral odor of moderate tenacity. The floral notes resemble Lilac and Mimosa.
Sweet and mild, floral odor of Lilac-Rose type
Refined and delicately floral, balsamic-green and rosy odor. Undertones of green-musty, sweet-cinnamic character. Moderate tenacity.

Very powerful, diffusive and penetrating odor, warm-floral, but when undiluted rather “gassy’’-pungent. In dilution Jasmin-Tuberose-like, floral, sweet. In extreme dilution the odor is even slightly rosy.
Mild-fruit y, slightly Pineapple-like, sweet odor.
Woody-dry, camphoraceous odor of moderate tenacity. In dilution remotely reminiscent of Rose.
Very mild, herbaceous-woody-oily odor of good tenacity but of rather uninteresting type.
Woody-floral-rosy odor of considerable tenacity
Sweet woody-floral, mildly green odor of good tenacity.
Green-woody and slightly floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Woody-peppery, warm and moderately tenacious odor. In combination with floral materials it has the ability to enhance the floral notes, particularly Rose
Green-herbaceous, semi-dry odor with woody undertones, in dilution also floral and with fair to good tenacity.
Sweet, but slightly woody-spicy, caramellicfruity odor of good tenacity
Powerful, fruity-winey, fresh-floral and very sweet odor with balsamic-honey-like under tones. Moderate tenacity.
Pungent floral-balsamic odor of Hyacinth-Orangeblossom-Rose type. Moderate to poortenacity.
Sweet-floral, relatively powerful and herbaceous odor with a tobacco-like, warm undertone.
Very mild, dry-herbaceous, almost powdery odor of good tenacity
Pungent-dry, medicinal, but refreshing odor of moderate tenacit y. There is some similarity to the odor of Thymol, and the odor is pleasantly free from the “tarry” notes found in Carvacrol.
Citrusy-lemonlike odor, but rather “gassy”-Styrene-like when undiluted.
Green-earthy odor. The green being almost root-like green with vegetable and dry undertones, and a pleasant, somewhat sweeter, Pine-Savin-like and balsamic terminal note.
Very diffusive, ethereal-Rum-like odor, sweet and fruity of very poor tenacity.
Sweet Petitgrain-like and Grape-like odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, herbaceous-woody, in dilution floral and sweeter odor of good tenacity
Sweet, fruity-woody odor of moderate to good tenacity.

Warm-herbaceous, but also musty odor of considerable tenacity. The odor has been described as resembling that of dry leaves, and literature uses altematel~ the words “pleasant” and “unpleasant” odor of dry leaves
Warm-herbaceous, in dilution sweet and slightly spicy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, “culinary “-spicy odor of moderate tenacity.
Pleasant floral-woody odor of good tenacity. The woody notes are light and fresh, the floral tone is also light, almost green and sweet.
The title material has been suggested for use as a Sandalwood odor, but it has not been marketed yet under its proper chemical name.
Very powerful, penetrating, sulfuraceousherbaceous odor of Onion type, but non- Iachrymatory and not very tenacious. In extreme dilution sweet and more pleasant “natural” odor
Green-woody, floral and relatively sweet odor of good tenacity. The woody notes resemble Amyris and Sandalwood to some degree.
Mild and sweet, floral odor of delicately green, fresh and lasting character. Does not display the Melon-like greenness of the aldehyde, but is also without the power of that material.
Very faint, but tenacious, delicately floral and discretely green odor.
Odor resembling that of Cyclamen aldehyde, but sweeter and milder.
Sweet, balsamic-floral odor of very good tenacity, but overall weak
Mild, fruity-floral, sweet and very tenacious odor. Although attractive as an odor, it has very little power and no real character.
Mild, fruity-balsamic, sweet and tenacious odor.
Powerful and very diffusive, ethereal-fruity odor of “heavy” type
Diffusive, ethereal-camphoraceous odor, pleasant in dilution, somewhat pungentchoking when concentrated
Semi-sweet, green and floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Very powerful and penetrating, warm-herbaceous-oily odor of Onion-like character, particularly upon dilution.
Warm-herbaceous, very sweet and slightly Coumarine-like odor, overall resembling the odor of fresh hay.
Powerful and penetrating smokey-tarry odor, in extreme dilution sweet, woody-herbaceous, slightly animal. Poor tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous-animal, in dilution exotic -nauseatingly floral odor of poor tenacity. Trace impurities in commercial ~ade material often change the odor picture substantially.

There are fishy, “ashtray’’-like odors which seem to give way to sweeter, oily herbaceous notes in pure material. The tenacity is good, but the poor grade material has generally unpleasant terminal notes
Powerful, and in high concentration rather repulsive odor of animal-musty character. In extreme dilution the odor becomes pleasant, burnt-oily, herbaceous and floral-sweet of excellent tenacity.
This is the most floral of the five common isomers of Methylquinoline. In proper dilution it displays a sweet-animal, delicately floral and warm, persistent odor.
Powerful and tenacious, sweet-animal-floral odor with predominantly Civet-Honey-like character. Overall less floral, more Honey-like than the meta-isomer.
Powerful and penetrating, heavy nauseating odor in high concentration, but sweet, floraltobacco- like with a discrete Civet-like note when properly diluted
Virtually odorless when pure, but usually carries a faint, not unpleasant, oily-fatty, mild and bland odor
This aldehyde, closely related to the more popular safranal, is used much the same way, for “space’’-odors (room sprays, etc.), and for masking of offensive odors, including household odors.
Warm, sweet, rooty-fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Virtually odorless when pure, but may carry a faint or mild, “refined Castor oil” type of oily odor. Good tenacity.
Sweet, animal-herbaceous and very tenacious odor.
Powerful and diffusive Onion-and-meat-like odor, in dilution more pleasant, less Onionlike, reminiscent of “bouillon”.
Powerful and sweet soup-or-meat-like odor and flavor. In the undiluted form, the material dwplays a rather repulsive odor with perceptible notes of sulfuraceous character.
Very tenacious, powerful, sweet anisic-floral odor with some resemblance to notes in Y1ang-Ylang.
Rather dry-menthol-like, camphoraceous odor with a faintly woody note and moderate tenacity.
Sweet and green-floral odor with a mildly woody note and good tenacity. Overall rosy character
Intensely sweet, fruity-balsamic odor with variable amounts of Bitter-almond undertones.
Sweet, woody-fruity and very tenacious odor with considerable.resemblanceto the odor of dried figs
Delicately woody, tenacious and moderately sweet odor with some resemblance to certain types of Methylionone.
Sweet-camphoraceous, rosy-citrusy odor of moderate tenacity.
Intensely sweet, floral-citrusy and tenacious odor with a “metallic-fresh” topnote. The odor may vary considerably according to the composition of the condensation product
Very powerful and diffusive, penetrating odor of fresh Onion, greener and more ethereal than the odor of the Methyl propyl trisulfide. The tenacity is extremely poor.
