practically odorless
Sweet-herbaceous, but very faint odor. When heated, the crystals emit a more pleasant nut-like or deep-caramellic sweetness of great tenacity.
Sweet, oily-winey, almost honeylike and tenacious odor.
Very mild, “bland” odor of sweet-waxy, oily character, but not wiih the “fresh-laundry ’’-like odor of commercial Lauryl alcohol.
Light, fatty-green, mildly earthy-fungal odor with some resemblance to Brandy and Cognac
Floral-waxy, mildly green, but not very “leafy” odor of considerable tenacity
Mild-Ambre-like, semi-dry, waxy-resinous odor of good tenacity.
Warm-oily, herbaceous or delicately spicy, nut-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Pungent-ethereal, green-fruity Apple-like odor of very poor tenacity.
Pungent,ethereal, fruity-Apple-like odor
Powerful, pungent-acidulous odor, caramellic-sour. In extreme dilution pleasant oilyacidulous, herbaceous, but of poor tenacity.
Sour-pungent odor, in dilution sour-herbaceous, slightly green, of poor tenacity.
Unpleasant sour and penetrating odor. Less fatty-sweat-like than Gproic acid, more pungent.
Sweet and warm-herbaceous, oily-nut-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Very sharp and pungent, rather irritating and penetrating odor. In extreme dilution sweet-ethereal, not unpleasant
Mild, woody-floral, remotely rosy odor with some resemblance to Linalool or Ethyl linalool. Moderate tenacity.
Faint, musty-sour odor, varying with the  age and quality of the material. The commercial grade has almost always a sour note.
Sweet Ambregris-musk-like odor of good tenacity.
The commercial product usually has a faint, peptone-like odor, often simply called “meaty” or “’soupy”, but highly purified products show very little, if any, such odor.
Practically odorless.
Musky-sweet odor of type resembling Musk Ketone and Musk Ambrette, yet more creamyfloral, sweeter and more tenacious
Very soft, sweet and extremely tenacious musky, but not animal, odor.
Urine-ammoniacal odor,
Sweet, yet heavy, floral-musky odor of very good tenacity. The characteristic note of this Nitromusk is the floral tone of its muskiness.
Sweet and very tenacious musky odor with discrete animal note, less floral than Musk Ambrette, The characteristic note is the warm and mildly animal note.
Intensely sweet, floral-musky odor
Delicately sweet-musky, mildly, but unquestionably animal-like and very tenacious odor.
Sweet-musky and tenacious odor, rather harsh in its initial approach. This musk imparts sweetness but lacks the softness, floral or animal tonalities and overall power of the other Nitromusks.
Sweet-balsamic-resinous “gum” odor of poor tenacity. The odor of the purified Myrcene is refreshing, almost citrusy, but warmbalsamic, and ethereal-sweet
Fresh, floral-Lime-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The Lime note is inevitably accompanied by woody notes, but should not show “piney” notes
Fresh, diffusive, sweet citrusy-herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Fresh, green-citrusy odor with some resemblance to topnotes of Clary Sage oil. Moderate to poor tenacity
Sweet and fruity-balsamic odor with a mild citrus note. The odor has striking resemblance to that of “canned pears”, and some observers even claim that they find the “metallic” note in it.

Very faint, waxy-oily odor, almost odorless when pure, but since the commercial material is often contaminated with traces of unsaturated acids, etc., an acid-rancid or acrid odor may occur in older material.
Very faint, Coconut-oily, mildly waxy odor of considerable tenacity. A highly purified product is almost odorless.
Very faint, fruity -citrusy odor with an Ambre-incense note, somewhat dry and moderately tenacious.
Pleasant and warm-balsamic, slightly woody odor of good tenacity. The undiluted material shows some “pepperiness”.
Very powerful, in dilution refreshingly citrusy, in concentration rather choking, pungent odor of considerable tenacity, and with an undertone of fresh Oakmoss.
Refreshing, spicy-herbaceous odor of Bayleaf-Cinnamon character. The diffusive warmth is particularly typical (and appreciated).
Warm-herbaceous, slightly woody and discretely “medicinal”’-camphoraceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Pleasant, refreshing, sweet-herbaceous and very slightly spicy-warm odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent, choking dry-tarry odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very mild, sweet-floral-balsamic odor of considerable tenacity.
Intensely sweet and tenacious, fruity-floralwiney odor. In extreme dilution, the fruity notes dominate and resemble (with reasonable imagination) Raspberry
Sweet and fruity, very tenacious, delicately Neroli-Orangeblossom-floral odor.
Delicate and sweet, very tenacious floralfruity odor. Less fruity than the iso-Butylether, more Neroli-like in dilution
Insoluble in water; soluble in alcohol and oils, poorly soluble in Propylene glycol. The volubility in alcohol is much better than that of the -methylether

The odor of highly purified material is intensely sweet, Orangeblossom-Acacia-like, very tenacious, but many commercial grades are poorly refined and display rather harsh notes, an odor description generally used for this material.
Delicately sweet and tenacious, floral-balsamic odor of Neroli-Hyacinth-Narcisse type. There are notes in this complex of a pleasant fruity character, reminiscent of Apricot.
Very sweet and delicate fruity-floral odor of excellent tenacity. The floral notes are discretely neroli-like, while the fruity notes have a remote resemblance to Strawberry.
Intensely sweet, but unpleasant, almost choking odor. In high concentration it may remind the observer of Halogen-odor, and a great variety of phrases are used for description of its odor.
The result, often vew poorly purified, is a material with a rather harsh Orangeblossom odor. Much more dry than Methylanthranilate, and not nearly as versatile.
Very faint, woody-camphoraceous, musty odor
Peculiar, dry-green, musty-medicinal odor with warm-herbaceous character. Good tenacity
The material is virtually odorless
Practically odorless.
Virtually odorless.
Refreshing Menthol type odor, but not quite as sweet as Menthol
Warm-spicy and very tenacious odor with an almost choking sweetness often classified as “nauseating”.
Sweet rosy, refreshing and “wet” seashore odor of moderate tenacity
Mild and delicately woody-floral, slightly green odor with remote resemblance to Apple and Lily
Sweet-woody, tenacious and mildly greenrefreshing odor
Very sweet, fruity-woody, Bergamot-and-Pear-like, but delicate and very tenacious odor

Delicately woody, rather dry, but refined and discrete odor of moderate to good tenacity. It has a touch of floral note which, combined with the woody and green traces make this material almost “confined” to Muguet.
Fresh, but rather dry, delicately woody, remotely Pear-like odor of pleasant softness and good tenacity
Warm and bitter-sweet, green-floral, woody-Ieafy odor of moderate tenacity. The undertones are warm, almost Honey-like.
Very sweet, fruity-floral odor of Raspberry-Rose character, refreshing and moderately tenacious.
Very mild, floral-balsamic and slightly “metallic “-fresh odor, sometimes described as “green”. Excellent tenacity.
Delicate, leafy-floral, fruity Orange-like and very sweet odor of rrtoderate tenacity.
Very delicate, refreshingly floral-sweet and warm odor of moderate to good tenacity
Refreshing, sweet-rosy or fruity-herbaceous odor with emphasis on the fruity (fruit-preserve)-notes, and less floral than the lower esters of Nerol
Refreshing herbaceous-green and floral, delicately rosy (like hedgerose) odor of moderate tenacity.
Deep-sweet, very rich, but mild-rosy-honeylike, floral odor of considerable tenacity. The undertones may be ruined by a surplus of Phenylacetic acid if such is present.
Sweet and very fruity, “jam-like” odor reminiscent of the heavy syrup of fruit preserves, yet with a trace of fresh-floral notes and moderate tenacity.
Powerful and rich, sweet-herbaceous and fruity odor of good tenacity
Rich and sweet-herbaceous, Clary Sage and Hop-type odor with ethereal-fruity notes and good tenacity
Pungent and harsh or offensive, Bitteralmond type odor of poor tenacity.
Pungent, but sweet herbaceous-green odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Peculiar, but intensely sweet and pungentherbaceous odor, displaying a complex of green, anisic, almondy and woody -herbaceous notes.
Warm-medicinal, sweet “phenolic’’-tarry odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet-floral, warm-spicy and moderately tenacious odor, often described as resembling Cinnamon.
Pungent-sweet herbaceous-spicy odor with resemblance to Bitter-almond and remote similarity to Heliotropine. Good tenacity
Pungent, but very sweet, heavy odor, sweeter than that of Nitrobenzene, and not as offensive. Moderate to poor tenacity
Extremely powerful and ve “y diffusive green-vegetable odor, only in dilution reminiscent (strikingly) of Cucumber or Violet leaf
Powerful, fresh-green Cucumber odor, less oily and, in proper dilution, much fresher and lighter than the odor of the aldehyde itself
Extremely powerful and very diffusive oily -green, herbaceous and, in proper dilution, sweet, pleasant leafy-vegetable odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Very powerful, fatty-oily, but rich and sweet, mildly nut-like odor of excellent tenacity.
Very powerful and diffusive fatty-floral, waxy odor of moderate tenacity. In proper dilution, the fatty notes become more pleasant, floral-waxy, more rosy and sweet, fresh as Neroli.
Delicately green-oily, mildly herbaceousfloral odor of good tenacity.
Refreshing and relatively powerful citrusyfloral, oily-green odor of moderate tenacity

Powerful, oily-herbaceous, warm odor of moderate tenacity. Considerable variations are observed when studying the various brands. Notes of floral-Jasmin character, mushroom-like Lavender character or almost caramellic sweetness may be present, predominant or absent in one or the other specialty.
The pure chemical has a mildly nut-like, fatty and acid odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, oily-floral, fresh and “petal’’-like odor, rather fatty when undiluted, light and almost rosy when highly diluted
Herbaceous, mildly spicy-earthy, but overall sweet and oily odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The odor is not floral like the 1-Nonanol, and not “mushroomy” like- Vinyl hexyl carbinol.
Creamy, coconutty, delicately fruity (in extreme dilution) and floral-musky odor of excellent tenacity.

Powerful and, when undiluted, somewhat sharp or pungent grassy-herbal odor with green-fruity undertones. Upon dilution the herbal notes become more natural-sweet, mildly oily, remotely mushroomy-earthy, warm.
Herbaceous-fruity, warm-ethereal odor of moderate tenacity.
Practically odorless.
Refreshing, fruity-floral odor with a drywaxy, pleasant note and moderate tenacity.
Practically odorless when pure, but causes a violently burning taste sensation, even at very low concentration

Extremely powerful and diffusive, penetrating, fatty-orrisy odor in higher concentrations. In dilutions below 0.1 !4 the odor becomes more Orris-like, waxy, less fi!itty, slightly green and in extreme dilutions quite pleasant
Powerful and very diffusive, waxy-floral odor with balsamic-nutty note and moderate tenacity.
Powerful, refreshing, green-oily, herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful, earthy-herbaceous, in dilution refreshingly spicy-herbal odor of moderate tenacity.
Vegetable-green, mildly oily -herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity. The odor is sometimes described as resembling Artichoke
Faint, but pleasant, warm-woody-herbal odor with some resemblance to Ambregris. Excellent tenacity but rather poor stability.
less waxyfatty, more sharp-pungent than that of the aldehyde.
Powerful fruity-green, leafy and mildly earthy odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Fruity, but also heavy-herbaceous, “incense-like” odor with mildly green-earthy, Reseda-like notes
Very sweet, yet refreshingly “peel-like” Mandarin-Orange type odor with distinctly Orangeblossom-winey-fruity undertones and excellent tenacity.
Peculiar, warm-herbaceous, sweet-fruit y odor complex of considerable tenacity.
Heavy, sweet-fruity Orange-Rose, yet herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity
Delicately fruity, not as “deep” as the nbutyrate, yet a sweet-sharp Apricot-like, Orange-rosy, herbaceous-green odor of moderate tenacity.
Floral, mildly Coconut-Peach-like odor with musky undertone and excellent tenacity.
Weak, fatty-grassy oily odor with mildly musky undertone and excellent tenacity.
Winey-ethereal, mildly fruity and nut-like odor of moderate tenacity.
peculiar sweet-rosy, delicately earthyoily odor
Mild, but persistent woody-musky and soft-floral odor.
Refreshingly fruity-citrusy, sweet and lightly floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mildly green-herbaceous, sweet, Rose- Orangeblossom type odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent-herbaceous-ethereal, but sweet and warm odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild-fruity, oily-Orange-like odor of “aldehydic” character, but overall weak
Winey-ethereal, sweet-rosy and mildly waxyaldehydic odor of moderate tenacity
Warm-fruity, slightly musty-floral odor with some resemblance toHazelnut. Moderate tenacity.
Heavy-fruity, Apple-and-Hazelnut-like odor with citrus-winey notes. Moderate tenacity
Powerful, sweet-green, diffusive odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Various specialties of widely diiTerent composition and odor have been available of above or related identity.
The title material has an extremely powerful fruity, sweet and citrusy odor of good tenacity
Very mild, woody-camphoraceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity

Sweet, woody-fruity odor of moderate tenacity. Some similarity to Linalylacetate, however, less sweet, less fruity, more woody. Arefined grade of Nopyl acetate shows more sweetness, less woody-piney odor
Sweet, but rather heavy, warm-herbaceous, almost spicy-balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, mildly spicy odor of moderate tenacity
Very diffusive, gassy-piney, camphoraceouswoody odor
Warm-herbaceous, very diffusive odor of poor tenacity. The sweetness is almost floral, and there is an immediate similarity to Neroli oil in the odor of pure Ocimene.
Diffusive and refreshing camphoraceous- Lime-1ike odor with an undertone of floral OH sweetness

Its fruity notes resemble the odor of Bartlettpear (preserved) and the material showsgreat versatility in use. As a modifier for alltypes of herbaceous fragrances, includingClary Sage, and in combination with Oakmossand Styrax it gives new and attractive tonalities and pleasant freshness.
Very faint, waxy, tenacious odor. Pure material is free from any trace of harsh or rancid notes.
Virtually odorless when pure, but commercial grades normally have a faint, blandoily odor
Powerful and penetrating green-vegetable, grassy and somewhat fatty odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful and very diffusive, sweet-oily, almost creamy-buttery, yet green and vegetablelike odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful Coconut-coumarinic odor with herbaceous-spicy, almost Caraway-like and warm notes. Slightly greener, but less fatty than the n-Butyl butyrolactone, also more Caraway-like.
Minty-musty, camphoraceous odor of moderate tenacity
Powerful, and in undiluted state harshfatty, penetrating odor. In extreme dilution sweet, Orange-like, slightly fatty, Honey-like and of moderate to poor tenacity.
When absolutely free from aldehyde, this material has a pleasant sweet-woody, green and mildly floral odor, often including a winey or ethereal topnote.
Powerful oily-green and waxy-citrusy odor of poor tenacity.
Oily-rancid, sweat-like odor, repulsive to most people, even in dilution of less than 0.1 % acid.
Powerful, fresh, Orange-Rose-like, waxy and sweet odor of poor tenacity. Balsamicherbal undertones are often classified as Opopanax- like.
Sweet and powerfully herbaceous, oilynutty and warm odor
Sweet-herbaceous Coconut-like odor with an oily Tonka-bean-like undertone.
Powerful, herbaceous-fruity, mildly spicy odor of moderate tenacity

Fruity-floral and herbaceous odorcomplex. The fruity notes being of Apple citrus character the floral-herbaceous notes resembling part of Jasmin, while the earthy-herbaceous undertones point in the Foug&e direction
Refreshing and rather delicate, rosy-minty odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Relatively powerful, oily-musty odor, in dilution more fruity and pleasant. Moderate to good tenacity, but unpleasant when undiluted.
Fruity, slightly fatty, waxy-floral odor with a discretely green, Apple-1ike or almost “weedy” note, while the undertones are mildly woody.
Fresh-oily, herbaceous-floral and very sweet, tenacious odor of Sweet-Pea and NeroIi-type, often compared to “Frangipanni”
Rather weak, balsamic-oily odor of considerable tenacitv.

Peculiar, green-herbaceous, remotely Orange-like and mildly fatty-floral odor. The herbaceous notes resemble the warmer parts of Galbanum, while the floral notes are related to Rose. Moderate tenacity.
Refreshing, herbaceous and fruity-green, vegetable odor.
Fruity-rosy, floral and fresh odor of moder-ate to good tenacity. Fresher odor than that of the n-Butyrate. The fruity notes being light Melon-Peach-like.
Very tenacious, but delicately green-peachy odor with unquestionably musky undertones.

Bland-fruity, also mildly herbaceous odor of considerable tenacity. The odor seems to lack character, and its initial power is very limited. Only in composition with more vola-tile materials it may show some effect, generally fruity, Banana-like and mildly green or almost “metallic” as Parsley.
Weak, but persistent and sweet-herbaceous, almost tea-like odor
Very mild, but sweet and tenacious, balsamic odor. The sweetness is more herbaceous- spicy than fruity, and it is often described as Opopanax-like.
When this material is absolutely pure, it is virtually odorless
Mild, oily-woody, almost floral odor of considerable tenacity. The undiluted material may appear somewhat camphoraceous, but its effect is rather sweet and floral-woody in compositions.
Sweet and oily-floral, mildly balsamic-herbaceous odor of excellent tenacity.
Sweet-ethereal, diffusive odor.
In flavors, the ester finds its way into “tutti- -frutti” compositions, Peach and Apricot imitations and various Citrus types.
Very faint, sweet-oily, herbaceous-caramellic odor of considerable tenacity.
Mild, balsamic-sweet and remotely fruity odor of considerable tenacity.
Oily-green, mildly leafy and somewhat fatty odor of considerable tenacity. Less Violet-leaf- Iike than the lower homologies of these esters.
Oily-fruity, mildly green and fresh odor resembling the odor of unripe fruit. The oily notes are sweet and rather pleasant
Sweet and oily-herbaceous, slightly fruity odor of moderate tenacity.
Floral and fruity, rather heavy and power-ful, Jasmin-like, warm and discretely spicy odor of moderate tenacity
When absolutely pure, the ester is virtually odorless, but commercial samples have usually shown some degree of oily-fatty or blandfruity odor.
Powerful oily-green odor, sweet and green floral in dilution, the oily notes being freshnut-like, the green notes sweet, vegetable-like, with moderate tenacity.
Peculiar earthy-floral, and oily citrusy odor of excellent tenacity.
faint, dry-medicinal odor, but not as choking or distinctly “phenolic” as that of Phenol or Cresol

Mild, but very tenacious, sweet-floral odor of woody-Orange-Rose type. The Orange character seems to come from oily-sweet notes which may be concealed under Rose-honey notes if the ester is poorly balanced (
Oily-herbaceous, slightly earthy-woody and sweet-spicy odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet, oily-waxy and fruity-herbaceous odor, overall a relatively pleasant complex with many notes resembling food or condiment products.
Practically odorless when pure.
Fruity and relatively diffusive, Apple-Banana-like odor with fresh-’’aldehydic” notes and moderate tenacity.
Powerful, fatty-fruity, herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity. The herbaceous notes are rather heavy, almost spicy, and the terminal notes are “powdery” resembling the dryout of root-like odors.

Yet, it is not as “gassy” as the Styrene family, and not as ‘“gasoline’’-like as the Olefins or Paraffins. It is ethereal and sweet, of very poor tenacity, warm and remotely resembling the odor of Myrcene in its warm spiciness.
materials have a faint, bland-oily odor
Warm and sweet, nut-like, earthy-mossy odor of moderate tenacity.
Dry-woody-tarry, also Walnut-like odor of good tenacity.
Sweet, soft and extremely tenacious, discretely animal-musky odor
exquisite musk odor with a pleasant note resembling Ambrette-seed oil

Sweet, tenacious and intensely musky odor. Generally considered less powerful and less tenacious than Cyclopentadecanolide, and it does not have the attractive and highly appreciated “Ambrette-seed “-like note
Sweet and woody-floral, delicately green odor of good tenacity. The overall odor bears some resemblance to that of Cyclamen aldehyde.
Virtually odorless when absolutely pure.
Powerful, floral-green, sweet and Violetleaf-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very faint, but delicately fresh-floral odor of good tenacity,
Very faint, bland-waxy and discretely floral odor of excellent tenacity. An absolutely pure material is reported to be virtually odorless.
Faint, but sweet and delicate, etherealwiney, oily odor, Good tenacity.
rarely used in perfume compositions, Higher concentrations have acrid taste and repulsively acid odor, pungent and irritating.
Powerful and pungent Mustard-like odor of poor tenacity.
This alcohol has been used in perfume compositions as part of leafy-green topnotes, as a “lifting” ingredient, and in combination with Galbanum, Geranium and similar materials for powerful effects

Powerful and diffusive, green-fruity, somewhat pungent odor of poor tenacity. The fruitiness resembles that of Amyl acetate, but it is not nearly as sweet, the greenness is slightly gassy-leafy, Violet-like.
Woody and faintly citrusy odor with some resemblance to the odor of the Ionones, but inferior tenacity.

Warm and slightly spicy, Jasmin-like odor of excellent tenacity. Not as sweet as iso- Jasmone, but also less Celery-like in its warmspicy character. Overall less floral than the most popular iso-Jasmones and Didydro jasmones, etc.
Powerful, but not pungent, green-herbaceous odor of spicy-condiment-like type. The odor is often classified as “resembling that of Cuminaldehyde”,
When absolutely pure, the material has a pleasant, fresh-citrusy and peppery-woody odor with a discretely minty note.
Peppery -minty, refreshing and slightly citrusy odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful, sweet-green, tenacious odor
Peppery -minty, refreshing and slightly citrusy odor of poor tenacity.
This material has been suggested for use in perfume compositions as a modifier in .’green” and green-floral notes, particularly interest ing in Lilac and Muguet.
Very faint, acetic-sweet odor of considerable tenacity. The odor is not nearly as cloying as that of Phenylacetic acid, and not as Honey-like, but it is more ““sour”.
Sweet floral odor of good tenacity.
Sweet-fruity, rosy-floral, slightly honey-like odor of excellent tenacity. Good perfumery grades should show no “metallic” note, generally due to the presence of Glycol-impurities.
Warm, rosy-fruity, slightly earthy-herbaceous odor of good tenacity. Not as sweet as the iso-butyrate, but warmer.

Warm-fruity-floral odor of considerable tenacity. The tobacco-like notes seem to re-monophenylplace the honey-notes (in the lower esters), and the fruity theme is discretely Apple-like. The odor is not as herbaceous-fungoid as that of the propionate, but not as warm either.
Sweet, mild-fruity-honey-like, tenacious odor.
Very powerful and penetrating, pungentgreen, floral and sweet odor of Hyacinth-type.
Sweet-floral, somewhat earthy-fruity odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and delicately green-rosy, floral, tenacious odor.
Sweet and very tenacious, floral-honey-like odor.
Intensive, pungent-green odor, reminiscent of cut grass
Herbaceous-green, but not very pleasant odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, yet rather heavy-floral, sweet and tenacious odor.
Sweet-floral, delicately green, refreshing odor of good tenacity.
Mild and sweet-floral, slightly green and very tenacious odor.
Sweet-foliage-like, intensively green and moderately tenacious odor. More refined or delicate, less pungent-green than the Dimethylacetal.
Deep-sweet, heavy and rosy-herbaceous, slightly earthy odor of very good tenacity.
Earthy-green, pungent floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Sweet-earthy, green-floral Hyacinth type odor.

Sweet-green, warm-earthy odor of moderate tenacity. The green-earthy complex is generally  classified as “Reseda’’-like, which is highly appreciated in perfumery, ah bough very few perfumers know what Reseda smells like
Fresh-rosy, floral and sweet-green odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful green-earthy, flower-stem-like odor, not as pungent as that of the aldehyde,
Slightly musty, green-herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Clean and mild, fresh-rosy, leafy odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Very faint, sweet-green, rosy odor with peculiar semi-dry undertones. Moderate to good tenacity.
Slightly green-woody, very mild and delicate odor of moderate tenacity.
Peculiar oily-green, earthy -rooty, but mild and sweet odor of good tenacity.
Floral, but somewhat harsh odor of Lily-Jasmin type. Impure products may show phenolic notes, while a “metallic” note seems to be normal in this material.
Sweet, animal-honey-like odor of extraordinary tenacity. The sweet-honey-like character is predominant at very low concentration, while the animal-Civet-like notes appear at higher concentrations.
Faint, balsamic odor of excellent tenacity.
Very faint “metallic’’-sweet odor
Sweet and fruity-honey-like, relatively tenacious odor with discrete balsamic-floral character.
Warm, spicy-floral and balsamic odor,
Ethereal-rosy, green, slightly “gassy”, Geranium- type odor of poor tenacity
Light and sweet-herbaceous odor with discretely citrusy-lemony notes, overall resembling Verbena, although not nearly as “lemony”.
Very’ faint, sweet-floral odor of blossom-Honeysuckle type.
Very faint, balsamic-floral, metallic-green odor of excellent tenacity.
Very mild, green-rosy, slightly metallic odor, in solution developing a pleasant, sweet-tearosy odor type. Good tenacity
Warm and relatively powerful balsamicrosy odor of moderate tenacity
Sweet, but rather heavy, herbaceous-rosy odor, heavier and less rosy than Phenylethylalcohol, but more tenacious
Pungent-heavy, Honey-fruity odor with distinctly animal undertones
Very faint, but very tenacious, sweet-heavy, floral-honey-like odor.
Powerful, fruity-floral and sweet, tenacious odor
Very mild, faintly-balsamic, creamy and tenacious odor
Very faint, sweet, floral-balsamic odor
Very faint, sweet, oily-balsamic odor of considerable tenacity.
Extremely penetrating, repulsive and irritating odor when undiluted. “Soapy’’-sweet odor in extreme dilution.
The odor has occasionally been described as “’horseradish-like”, but the author believes that this description must refer to another material.
Very sweet, rosy-fruity, honey-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes are mostly peachy with a pleasant Ieafy-green tonality, the rosy notes very sweet, almost towards Gardenia.
Mild and warm, Rose-honey-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Poorer grades show earthy or pungent, more Hyacinth-like topnotes, or greener “gassy” notes

In spite of the apparent absence of odor, the material has an unquestionable effect when incorporated in a composition along with  more volatile, odorous chemicals. Its effect is then sweet-floral, deep-fruity, herbaceous-honey-like and it has outstanding tenacity.
Very faint floral-balsamic odor reminiscent of dry Rose leaves and petals with a soft, honey-like undertone and excellent tenacity
Fine and natural-rosy, warm, floral-fruity odor of moderate tenacity.
Refreshing fruity-rosy odor. More fruity than rosy, and overall fresher than the n-Butyrate. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Fruity-green, rosy, fresh-Pineapple-like, Banana-like odor type of good tenacity.
Mild, fruity-winey odor with a peculiar herbaceous-earthy, almost fungoid character, not uncommon in C-8 derivatives
Pleasant floral-balsamic odor, somewhat more powerful than Phenylpropyl alcohol and not as “delicate”. Moderate to poor tenacity

Fresh-floral and fruity-balsamic odor of mderate tenacity. The floral notes are mildly rosy, the fruity are reminiscent of Raspberry but the odor is overall very mild and quite versatile, although it camies a touch of greenness.
Very faint, but sweet and pleasant, balsamic odor of excellent tenacity. There is a mild, floral-fruity note in the sweetness of a very pure material.
Pleasant, dry-and-sweet, mildly rosy-musty odor with warm-herbaceous undertone. Tenacity is good.
Extremely tenacious, warm and mild-rosy, earthy-honey-like odor
Delicate, fresh-fruity-rosy odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-balsamic, floral and slightly earthygreen-spicy odor of moderate tenacity
Fresh-floral, mildly green-rosy and discretely balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Pleasant ethereal-alcohol-like, sweet and rather powerful odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful, green-herbaceous, rosy odor with some similarity to Chrysanthemum, Hyacinth and Watercress foliage. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Warm, fruity-caramellic, slightly earthy oily odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, oily-citrusy-fruity odor of Orange character but with distinctly earthy -herbaceous notes, almost fungoid.
Powerful, floral-green, sweet and tenacious odor,
Very faint, bland-sweet, fruity-ethereal odor, sometimes with a rosy note, presumably derived from a surplus of the alcohol parent.
Warm, ethereal-herbaceous, also caramellic- sweet odor of moderate tenacity.

Dry-and-sweet, ethereal-herbaceous rose odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The rosy notes are more “dry-leaf’’-notes than truly floral notes, a fact which gives impression of “Potpourri-rose”, or the old-fashioned Rosesachets.
Fresh and sweet, rosy-fruity odor of moderate to poor tenacity. More rosy than fruity, and not quite as sweet as Phenylethyl acetate.
Sweet, floral-fruity odor with a warm, oily-herbaceous undertone and moderate tenacity,
Sweet and warm, herbaceous-fruity odor
Mild and fresh, slightly green, fruity and sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, but tenacious, sweet, green-fruity, warm-herbaceous odor
Mild, warm-rosy and floral, refreshingly Muguet-like and tenacious odor.
Fresh, green-floral, Narcissus-Hyacinth-Lily type odor of good tenacity.
Sweetl earthy-rosy, mildly fungoid or mushroom-like, but overall pleasant and warm odor of good tenacity.
Mild and tenacious, herbal-fruity, warm odor with sweet-earthy notes
Faint and mild, but very tenacious, delicately rosy-honey-like odor, Undertones are discretely fruity, the floral notes resemble Freesia
Weak and faint, oily-ethereal, sweet odor of good tenacity.
Oily-sweet, delicately rosy, petal-like and mildly waxy, herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Heavy and very sweet, extremely tenacious, floral-balsamic odor which is sometimes described as “musky” (perhaps by observers who detect no special odor in the material), or “honey-like”
Very warm, herbaceous-rosy, deep-fruity and moderately tenacious odor with a delicately spicy note (warm-balsamic).
Mild and refreshingly green, rosy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Faint, but sweet and delicately balsamicfloral, Rose-Hyacinth and Carnation type odor of excellent tenacity.
Mild, deep-sweet, herbaceous-winey, discretely floral-balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent, but rich and earthy-sweet, almost nut-like Radish-Horseradish-like odor, sometimes  described as resembling the odor of crushed Rapeseed.
Mildly floral-rosy, also sweet-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity. The odor is strongly influenced by a surplus of one or the other parent component - sulfuraceous or rosy.
Very pleasant, warm-herbaceous, deeprosy, dry-leafy-green odor with balsamiccaramellic sweetness and good tenacity
Oily-fatty, sweet-Hay-Honey-like, warmherbaceous odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm, fruity-rosy, herbaceous-tobacco-like odor of good tenacity.
Fruity-rosy, Rose-petal-like, mildly balsamic odor of good tenacity. Not quite as warmherbaceous as the n-Valerate
Powerful ethereal-rosy, sweet-pungent odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very mild, warm-balsamic and sweet odor of excellent tenacity. Poorer grades may show “phenolic”character which is unacceptable and undesirable.
Pungent, rather sharp, green-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, sweet, caramellic-sour odor of considerable tenacity. A highly purified material is said to be virtually odorless.
Mild and weak, but sweet and pleasantly floral odor of excellent tenacity.
Very faint, sweet-floral, deep-fruity odor with a musty-leafy note.
Mild balsamic odor with a faint, but pleasant floral note of Lily-Hyacinth character, and very good tenacity.
Pleasant, somewhat heavy, Gardenia-Hyacinth-Lily type odor, more earthy than fruity, and with damp, not truly fresh, greenness.
Fruity-green, rather fresh and powerful odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Fruity-green, somewhat pungent, but not harsh, odor of moderate to poor tenacity.Ixss earthy and less harsh than the odor of the secondary-Pheny lglycol monoacetate
Harsh-green, also floral and slightly earthy odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Mild, balsamic-sweet, dry-floral or woodyfloral odor with a delicately green note and excellent tenacity.
Sweet and fruity Lily-Hyacinth-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Mild, ethereal-fruity, green-floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity, but considerable power.
Relatively powerful and heavy, fruity Gardenia-Narcisse-Hyacinth type of moderate tenacity.
Heavy and intensely sweet, floral-herbaceous and very tenacious odor of Honey- Gardenia type.
Mild, oily-rosy and delicately green, tenacious odor.

Refreshingly citrusy-green, delicately rosy odor of good tenacit y. The odor has sometimes been described as “Rose-Lime’’-like, a combination which is rather fashionable in soap and shaving cream fragrances again
Weak, but verytenacious,floral-Ambre type odor with mildly balsamic notes and variable amounts of Neroli-Orangeblossom notes, according to origin of material.
Heavy-sweet floral Honey-like odor of good tenacity but not very powerful
Very faint, warm-balsamic and sweet odor of Coumarin-Vanillin-type and excellent tenacity.
Balsamic-green, oily-earthy odor with warm-spicy undertones and moderate tenacity.
Warm, spicy-floral odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Warm-floral, tenacious odor with deepfruity notes and pleasant sweetness
Warm, green-floral, sweet and tenacious odor with mildly fruity notes
its odor is rather weak, very sweet, green-rosy and tenacious, overall not very unusual.
Warm and very tenacious, floral-fruity odor with sweet-earthy, discretely green notes

Powerful and sharp-green, pungent-vegetable type of odor with good tenacity. The odor is more spicy and heavy than that of Benzyl cyanide, although both odors are described as “Watercress’’-type odors.
Faint, but very tenacious, oily-balsamic, sweet odor.
Sweet, floral-fruity, warm and mildly balsamic odor of moderate tenacity

Warm and mild, balsamic-floral, sweet odor of moderate tenacity. The floral notes have a Lilac-Rose-Hyacinth character, but without the pungency of the Hyacinth, rather the delicate mildness of a Peony
Very mild, but extremely tenacious, sweetbalsamic, green-herbaceous odor with an almost vegetable type of sweet-green-herbal character.
Heavy, sweet-fruity and balsamic odor of moderate to good tenacity
Fruity-balsamic, tenacious, but refreshingly sweet odor.
Mild, oily-fruity, slightly green-bland odor reminiscent of unripe Banana, Melon, etc. and with a delicately floral-green undertone. Good tenacity.
Sweet, fruity-green odor of good tenacity
Sweet, oily-fruity and mildly balsamic odor of excellent tenacity.
Very tenacious, rosy -balsamic, delicately fruity odor. Basically mild, but rich and pleasant when pure
Powerful and pungent-herbaceous, deepgreen odor of moderate tenacity.
Pleasant, sweet, floral-herbaceous, Geranium-Hyacinth-type odor of moderate tenacity. Its undertones are mildly spicy, warm, cinnamon-like.
Semi-dry, very heavy, balsamic-spicy and discretely green odor of excellent tenacity. The peculiar dry-sweet topnote resembles the initial notes in Mimosa and Narcisse
Heavy and sweet, but pleasant floral. Lily- Rose-Hyacinth type odor of moderate tenacity.

Powerful, sweet-green and diffusive-floralwoody odor of moderate tenacity. The tenacity of a very pure material is actually poor, while in poorer grade material the residual notes are usually derived from the impurities, and should not be considered characteristic of the material.
Sweet-caramellic-fruity odor of moderate tenacity.
Fatty-rosy, heavy, floral and slightly greenherbaceous odor of excellent tenacity
Heavy-fruity, mildly spicy -balsamic, deep-sweet odor of good tenacity. The fruity notes are rather fruit-preserve-like, reminiscent of Raspberry-Strawberry jams.
Distinctly fruity, refreshing and Strawberry Prune-Plum-like, very sweet and tenacious odor.
Warm, pungent-floral, mildly green odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very mild and sweet, fruity-balsamic odor, like very subdued Wintergreen, also reminiscent of Benzyl salicylate, but not as floral
Intensely sweet, but also pungent, heavy, Honey-like odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, green-floral and very tenacious odor.
Warm and sweet-herbaceous, honey-like odor.
Pungent, sweet-camphoraceous, heavy odor of poor tenacity. In extreme dilution, the odor is less camphor-like, more honey-like and sweet, yet heavy.
Practically odorless
To most observers, this material is odorless. On a closer study, one may detect very delicate, floral-balsamic notes, resembling those of Nerolidol and Famesol
Virtually odorless and tasteless when absolutely pure, but normally carries a delicate, dry-leaf, tea-like and slightly caramellic-sweet odor.
Faint, but pleasant and discretely fruityacidulous odor of excellent tenacity. There is a trace of floral-balsamic note combining with the fruity note to a pleasing fragrance.
Powerful, sweet, bread-like, honey-like, dif-fusive odor of poor tenacity. Although the impression is that of a warm, aromatic and sweet odor
Warm, sweet and rather pleasant, herbaceous- caramellic odor of poor tenacity
Powerful and diffusive, ethereal-mintycamphoraceous, warm-sweet odor of poor tenacity.

Its odor is warm-resinous, refreshing Pine-Iike, but lower grades of this material may carry more pronounced “Turpentine’’-like odor, “Rosin’’-odor or even herbaceous-aromatic odor (common feature of autoxidizedalpha-Pinene).
Dry-woody, resinous-piney odor of poor tenacity.
Fresh, Camphor-Menthol type odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The dextro-isoisomer has a more dry, Bomeol-woody odor.
Warm-camphoraceous, Cedarleaf-like, slightly spicy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Warm-woody-balsamic, slightly piney-fennel-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Powerful camphoraceous-mint y odor of moderate to poor stability, but good diliusive power.
Powerful camphoraceous odor, diffusive and warm, of poor tenacity.
Heavy-sweet, nauseating, floral-animal odor of great diffusive power and poor tenacity.
Virtually odorless when pure
Powerful, sharp-minty, bitter-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Its odor is powerful, diffusive, sweeter than that of the Piperitenone, but equally minty, penetrating and of moderate tenacity.
Powerful, fresh-minty-camphoraceous odor. The material may turn darker yellow and its odor become more tobacco-herbaceous upon ageing.
Very delicate, sweet-powdery, musky-floral odor of excellent tenacity.
Piperonylic acid has a faint, but very tenacious, sweet-balsamic odor with a discretely animal undertone.
Delicate, yet relatively powerful floral odor of excellent tenacity
Very faint, sweet-balsamic-fruity odor of excellent tenacity. The odor varies according to origin and age of material.
They all have only very faint, warm-oily odor or practically no odor,
Odorless when pure.
Odorless when pure.
The dry material is odorless
Odorless
Fresh, herbaceous-fruity -green, somewhat Lavender-like odor of poor tenacity
Fresh and very diffusive, fruity, Banana-1ike and Bergamot-like odor of poor tenacity.
The reaction mixture has a pronounced odor of freshly baked bread,
Powerful and very diffusive, but rather pleasant, foliage-green, Geranium-leaf-like odor of poor tenacity. Gassy at high concentrations, but pleasant-sweet in extreme dilution.
Sweet, warm pungent, anisic-caraway-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Warm, sweet, but slightly “smokey” odor of good tenacity.

Intensely sweet, but in the dry state rather medicinal -phenolic odor, often described as “drug store odor”. The sweet odor is more perceptible at high dilution, while the phenolic odor seems to vanish at such low concentrations.
Powerful, sweet-rosy, slightly waxy odor of moderate tenacity.
Fresh, leafy-rosy, delicately green, almost vegetable-green odor of pleasant, yet powerful sweetness of Geranium type. Moderate tenacity.
Caramellic-sweet, very tenacious, warm and deep-spicy odor.
Mild, warm-spicy, moderately tenacious odor resembling the odor of dry leaves with the discretely phenolic, tealike odor, sometimes encountered in Chinese tea
Extremely powerful and penetrating odor of fresh Garlic.
Very diffusive and penetrating, suffocating odor with choking effect upon the respiratory system. Very poor tenacity. In extreme dilution an odor of roasted Coffee appears
Pleasant, ethereal-warm, diffusive odor, milder than that of Acetone, but similar in character.
Pungent sour odor reminiscent of sour Milk, Cheese or sour Butter
Warm-herbaceous, semi-dry~-but pleasant odor of haylike or cured tobacco-leaf-like character and moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, warm-floral, moderately pungent- herbaceous odor of rather poor tenacity
Diffusive and fresh, ethereal-fruity, Pearlike odor of poor tenacity
Very diffusive, fruity-ethereal odor of very poor tenacity..
Practically odorless. The commercial product may have a faint “alcoholic” odor, barely perceptible in a container with the ester, but not on a perfume blotter.
The commercial product has an alcoholic nauseating, sweet odor of very poor tenacity. Highly purified Propyl alcohol has only a very faint odor
Alcoholic-ethereal, Acetone-like odor. The similarity to Acetone in odor is characteristic of th: iso-Propanol, not the n-Propanol.
Mild and delicately sweet, winey-floral odor of good tenacity.
Sweet and mild, warm-floral-herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Rather weak, winey, Mandarin-Orange-blossom-type odor of good tenacity
This hydrocarbon is rarely, if ever, used as such in perfumes or flavors.
Warm, deep-herbaceous-balsamic-nutlike odor of moderate tenacity.
Heavy-fruity, almost pungent sweet odor  with floral undertone and moderate to poor tenacity. More ethereal-fruit y than the nPropylester.
Powerful, green-floral, diffusive and relatively tenacious odor with some resemblance to Cyclamen aldehyde, but sweeter and softer
Mild-green, sweet, somewhat damp-earthy odor of moderate to good tenacity
Fresh-earthy-green, sweet, foliage-type odor wit h delicate] y fresh floral undertones
Light, green-fruity, fresh, yet balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Refreshingly sweet-green, delicately floral and very tenacious odor.
Relatively powerful, fresh-fruity, sweet odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Vinous-oily, fruity, relatively refreshing odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful woody-citrusy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Heavy-fruity, Pineapple-like ethereal-pungent odor of poor tenacity
Powerful and diffusive, heavy-fruity, Pineapple type odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful and diffusive, pungent, Pineapple- Strawberry type odor of poor tenacity
Very diffusive, light, refreshingly fruity odor of modified Pineapple type with a Bergamot-Pear-like freshness
Rather harsh-herbaceous odor, yet with sweet-herbal notes, sometimes described as the odor of grass and hay at the same time.
Green, vegetable-woody, oily-fruity odor, sometimes described as resembling the odor of Ho oil
Sweet-fruity, rather heavy Pineapple-Blackberry type odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Refreshing, sweet and almost delicately fruity odor of Pineapple-Loganberry type.
Winey, oily-fruity, mildly Brandy-1ike and Berry-Grape-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Fruit y, oily, Berry-1ike odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Sweet-and-dry, powdery-balsamic, Ambrelike slightly floral odor of good tenacity
Balsamic, sweet-and-dry Ambre type odor of good tenacity.
Sweet, oily-herbaceous, warm and somewhat animal odor of good tenacity
Mild and sweet Clover-like, herbaceouswarm odor of moderate tenacity
More herbaceous-woody than floral, yet relatively sweet odor of some resemblance to Linalool, yet harsher, more metallic-camphoraceous. Moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild, floral-balsamic, but also woodycamphoraceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Woody-camphoraceous, piney odor with semi-sweet undertones and moderate to poor tenacity.
Woody -minty, sweet-camphoraceous odor with a discretely fruity note and moderate tenacity.
Very penetrating and powerful, diffusive odor of Garlic/Onion type, but with no lachrymatory effect
Odorless when absolutely pure.
The material itself is practically odorless
Very mild fruity-acetic odor
Mild, sweet-fruity, buttery odor when pure. Traces of free iso-Butyric acid are likely to override the odor of the material.
Mild, winey-fruity odor when pure, but acquires an unpleasant sour, cheesy off-odor upon improper storage or exposure to air and moisture.
Mildly fruity-ethereal-acetic odor
Mildly fruity-ethereal-acetic odor,
Virtually odorless when pure, but commercial material normally carries a mild, warm-oily, bland odor.
Ethereal, sweet, nauseating and very diffusive odor.
Warm and very sweet balsamic, Nut-like and Vanilla-like odor, but not nearly as powerful as Vanitrope. Excellent tenacity
Powerful and diffusive, ethereal, heavy, almost nauseating odor
Sweet-ethereal, very diffusive odor, fresher than Chloroform, not as pungent as n-Propylformate
Light, fruity, Strawberry-ApplePeel and Pear-like odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Pleasant, oily-woody, herbaceous-green odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Peculiar sweet-oily, herbaceous-earthy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Practically odorless when pure, but some commercial products may carry a faintly drymedicinal odor
Green-fruity, winey, slightly fatty odor of rather poor tenacity. The fruity notes resemble the odor of juice from green Grapes
Ethereal-fruity, mildIy green, Grape-juicelike or Apple-like odor of poor tenacity
Fruity, rather bland, mellow odor of poor tenacity. Not as green as the odor of the iso-Propyl heptylether
Green-fruity, ethereal odor, often described as resembling the odor of unripe Mountain ash berries
Very fruity, pungent-oily odor of moderate to poor tenacity. It is more fruity than Ethyl octyl ketone (3-Undecanone) and still more fruity than Methyl nonyl ketone (2-Undecanone).
Powerful and penetrating, rather sharpgreen, leafy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.

Powerful, refreshingly green, sap-like or “twig-like’* odor with a pungent (unless diluted) herbaceous character, yet overall sweet, slightly woody and rather heavy. In proper dilution the odor becomes similar to that of Willow leaves.
This material is virtually odorless
Powerful, warm-herbaceous odor, sweeter, but also sharper than Carvone, but with some resemblance to that ketone. The tenacity is rather poor
Powerful, very warm, spicy-herbaceous odor of good tenacity.
Penetrating, dry odor with faintly fecal note and usually also a naphthalenic odor. Overall not pleasant, not even in dilution.
Penetrating and heavy, but in dilution floral, sweet-animal odor of good tenacity.
Very powerful, penetrating and diffusive, Cabbage-like, sulfuraceous odor, unpleasant unless extremely diluted.
Mild, floral-woody odor, remotely rosybalsamic, and of moderate tenacity.
Although the odor of this aldehyde is not as fresh-powerful, penetrating and diffusive as that of Cyclamen aldehyde, there is considerable similarity in the odor of the two. it seems less green-fresh
Virtually odorless when pure, or displaying only a very faint, flat oily-fatty, but not rancid odor.
Sweet, intensely green, Violet-leaf type odor of moderate tenacity
Powerful, green-leafy, in dilution also fruity, not as sweet as the n-Propylester
Virtually odorless and tasteless when pure. Commercial grades may occasionally show mildly fatty-oily odor and bland-oily taste, but they should not have any trace of rancid odor.
Winey-fruity, Melon-like odor with a mildly fermented note and moderate to poor tenacity.
Refreshingly fruity-winey, mildly etherealoily odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes are rather nondescript, the winey character resembles “fermented” notes.
Powerful, sweet, herbaceous and slightly woody odor of moderate tenacity. Although the sweetness may be classified as “anisic”, there is very little resemblance to Anis or Estragon.
Dry-woody, warm, spicy-medicinal odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, green, refreshingly bark-woody or sap-like odor of moderate to good tenacity
Honey-like, but fresh and- light, fruity Apricot-Rose type odor of moderate tenacity.

Powerful, ethereal or winey-honey-like, sweet odor of moderate tenacity. Fresher than the odor of the n-propylester, but not quite as sweet. The odor has often been described as resembling that of dry leaves, but the author finds it difficult to underwrite this description. However, in extreme dilution, the material has a vague odor resemblance to tea
Weak and uninteresting, anisic-sweet, but also harsh odor of moderate tenacity.
Mildly green, woody-floral odor of moderate tenacity. The woody notes tend to become herbaceous upon dilution, and the green notes are rather sweet, not pungent.
Sweet-herbaceous, mildly oily-floral odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, earthy-floral, deep and warm odor of poor tenacity, but considerable diffusive power.
Powerful, sweet-green, refreshingly light, floral odor of good tenacity.
Fresh-ethereal, fruity-floral odor of very poor tenacity. The fruity notes being Apple-Pineapple-like, while the floral character is more of a general “lift” of sweetness.
Fresh-ethereal, fruity odor with fermentedwiney note and poor tenacity.
Peculiar, semi-dry, leafy-floral odor of considerable depth and tenacity.

Powerful, sweet and, when undiluted, nauseating odor. In dilution green-anisic, slightly minty and tobacco-like, exotic-heavy, with moderate tenacity. Some authors report a floral odor in this material
Powerful, sweet-nauseating, but in dilution heavy-herbaceous odor. Overall less minty, less sweet, and more heavy-pungent-herbaceous than the u~pha-isomer
Powerful and diffusive, yet very tenacious earthy-woody, root-like odor. Upon dilution, the odor becomes more spicy-earthy, warm, but still sharp.

The title ester represents the transition stage of Salicylates from the very sweet, fruity Wintergreen like character to the very heavy herbaceous-floral type as found in Amylsalicylate and higher esters.
Sweet-ethereal-herbaceous, yet quite tenacious odor with distinctly fruity character
Very mild, sweet-oily-ethereal odor
Sweet-animal-floral odor with heavy-mossy character and good tenacity. Pungent when undiluted, heavy-floral in dilution
Warm-herbaceous, slightly winey-sweet, moderately tenacious odor.
Very powerful and diffusive, Garlic-like odor, penetrating and repulsive when undiluted, but in extreme dilution rather pleasant, sweet-herbaceous, distinctly Garlic-like.
Lemon-citrusy, oily-winey, mild odor of good tenacity
Heavy-fruity-oily odor of moderate to good tenacity, Less vinous than the saturated ester (see previous monograph), yet still reminiscent of Brandy
Citrusy, oily-Orange-like, winey and Brandy- type odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Powwrful and relatively diffusive, fruity-ethereal, Apple-1ike and also Pineapple-like odor of ~ tenacity.
Light, powerful, slightly winey, fruity Apple-Pineapple type odor of poor tenacity. Fresher and more Pineapple-like than the n-Propyl-n-valerate.
Diffusive, ethereal-fruity, winey odor of Apple-Brandy-like character and poor tenacity.
Ethereal-fruity, diffusive and winey, Pineapple-type odor of poor tenacity,
This material has only a faint odor, normally not pleasant, rather medicinal, dry and weak.
Oily-balsamic, warm-floral odor of Jasmin- Violet character and good tenacity.
The title material was intended to be a powerful, sweetspicy, warm-citrusy odorant,
Powerful and very tenacious, floral-woody and powdery odor.
Powerful, oily-woody, discretely floral odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, sweet-and-dry-woody, mildly spicy and warm odor of great tenacity.
Powerful, herbaceous, sweet-minty, rosy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mint y-herbaceous, bitter-sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Powerful and relatively diffusive, herbaceous- minty, resinous odor
Powerful minty-woody, mildly green odor. Very diffusive and penetrating, not as sweet as Pulegone, not as tenacious

Fresh, green-minty, leafy, sweet-fruity (unripe fruit) odor of moderate tenacity. The odor of the enol-acetate is sharper, more green, while the iso-Pulegyl acetate has a condiment-spicy character, sometimes almost Dill-pickle-like.
Fruity-green, winey-minty, refreshingly herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Spicy-sweet, green-leafy and fruity odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Fresh-green, minty, slightly earthy odor of moderate tenacity.
Pungent, sweet odor, in dilution floral with remote resemblance to Heliotrope. Very diffusive, poor tenacity.
Pungent, penetrating and diffusive odor, generally described as nauseating, but in extreme dilution warm, “burnt”, smokey, of very poor tenacity.
Pungent Bitter-almond-like odor of poor tenacity. Not quite as stinging as Benzaldehyde, but slightly more bitter, unnatural. In extreme dilution quite pleasant, sweet, Bitteralmond and nut-like.
Woody-medicinal, rather dry odor of considerable tenacity.
Dry-woody, very tar-like odor, but not unpleasant in dilution. Also smokey, resembling odor of wood-fire, with no petroleum-tar type odor. Very good tenacity.
used in flavoring
Pleasant hay-like, herbaceous-warm odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Warm, slight ly pungent, hay-like herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Sharper than the odor of alpha-Pyrone, and not quite as hay-like as that isomer
Sweet and warm-ethereal, slightly bumt- nauseating odor, resembling the odor of Propyl formate. The odor of Pyrrole is often described in chemical literature as resembling that of Chloroform,
Penetrating Amine-type odor, reminiscent of Ammonia and Piperidine, nauseating and diffusive, of very poor tenacity.
Sour-acetic odor.
Pungent, stinging odor, very diffusive and of poor tenacity.
Practically odorless
Odorless,
Odorless.
Odorless.
Heavy, penetrating and nauseating, yet sweet odor of good tenacity. Not as pungentdiffusive as Pyridine, not nearly as anisic as iso-Quinoline (see next).
Heavy-sweet, balsamic-herbaceous odor with some resemblance to Benzaldehyde and Anethole.
Practically odorless when pure.
Warm, musky-woody, mildly nut-like and very tenacious odor
Refreshingly woody-mossy odor of good tenacity. Older samples may show acid or acetic notes, not typical of the pure acetate.

Very powerful, sweet-earthy and intensely nut-like odor, reminiscent of Hazelnuts (or Phiherts). The author finds that the odor is better described as resembling that of “old Hazelnuts”, just shelled and then crushed
The name “Rhodinol” has been used to describe single chemicals as well as a group of related chemicals
Sweet, light and refreshing Rose-M uguet type of odor with variable amounts of delicately green or leafy notes.
Mild, but very tenacious, deepsweet, rosybalsamic odor.
Intensely sweet, mellow-fruity, deep rosy odor of moderate to good tenacity. An acidfree ester may have an odor very closely resembling the petals of certain varieties of Rose (petal-odor).
Delicately fruity, fresh-floral and sweet, tenacious odor. Overall more fresh and delicate than the n-Butyrate, but not as natural rosy or “petal-like”.

The commercial product under the title name has a very delicate, refined balsamic, but also very weak, rosy odor of excellent tenacity. The odor has sometimes been described as resembling that of the white rose varieties.
Fresh, leafy-green, delicately rosy, yet powerful odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet and very “deep”, soft, honey-like Rose fragrance with considerable resemblance to the “fond” of Rose absolute.

Rich and sweet, fruity-floral Rose-Geranium type with a fresh, almost Verbena-1ike undertone and good tenacity. There is an overall balsamic character to this odor which makes it attractive, but also makes it rather inconspicuous.
Odorless,
Heavy-fruity, slightly earthy-green, but also sweet, rosy odor of good tenacity.
Heavy-rosy, intensely fruity odor of good tenacity. Overall more fruity, but less naturalrosy than the n-Valerate.
Penetrating and very diffusive, gassy-green or “hard” green, floral odor of poor tenacity. The resemblance to Geranium appears only upon dilution of the Rose oxide, and best in a composition.
Warm, oily-peppery, woody-herbaceous and spicy odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild, but very pleasant, warm, Ambre- Labdanum-like, woody-balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Odorless.
Sweet and warm-spicy, woody-floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm and sweet, soft, floral-anisic, mildly spicy and tenacious odor. Sweeter, more floral, more anisic, less woody-spicy than Safrole

The author agrees with the late Mr. E. S. Maurer (103-298) that the common description “pleasant floral New-Mown-Hay odor” is not only misleading, but also very incomplete. Even if the odor would be generally described as “pleasant and floral”, one should avoid phrases which almost imply or encourage a use of a hazardous material. In extreme dilution, the odor is warm, herbaceous, spicy-floral but the phenolic note remains perceptible

It has a refreshingly sweet-woody, very tenacious odor, by some observers considered superior to that of Santalol, at least with respect to strength. It is doubtful whether the pure material has yet been prepared, and it is apparently not commercially available.
Mild, sweet-woody odor of excellent tenacity. The odor is generally considered superior to that of bera-Santalene
Mild, woody odor, more dry, less sweet than the odor of the alpha-Santalene
Sweet and very rich, warm-woody, tenacious odor. Santalol is generally considered to be a refined edition of the Sandalwood oil odor.
Sweet, woody and very tenacious odor.
Delicately woody, faintly Sandalwood-like, musky-sweet odor of excellent tenacity. The absence of the “medicinal” notes of Sandalwood is characteristic of this ester.
vety delicate, fine, floral and sweet-tenacious odor, more floral than woody, and with practically no trace of Sandalwood- oil-odor.
Very faint, balsamic, delicately woodyfloral odor of excellent tenacity.
Balsamic-fruity, heavy and tenacious, woody Tearose type of odor.
Fruity-balsamic, sweet and woody, very tenacious odor, not as mellow or “round” as the odor of the n-Butyrate, but slightly fresher.
Very fine, but faint, floral-balsamic odor of excellent tenacity.
Sweet-ethereal-floral, also herbal, Sandalwood odor, without the “medicinal” character of the natural oil, yet more woody and dry. Good tenacity.
Very heavy, musky-rosy, waxy or honeylike, sweet and very tenacious odor.
Mild and delicately fruity-woody, tenacious odor, free from the “medicinal” character of Sandalwood oil
Very faint, sweet-balsamic-woody odor of excellent tenacity.
Heavy-fruity, delicately woody-herbaceous odor of excellent tenacity
Fruity-rosy, peppery-woody, delicate and tenacious odor.
Ethereal-gassy, sweet-camphoraceous odor, in high concentration rather unpleasant, but upon dilution sweeter, less gassy, more Camphene-like, balsamic. Poor tenacity.
Sweet-camphoraceous, diffusive odor. In dilution quite pleasant, not as “medicinal” / as Camphor, not “piney” as Camphene, but rather warm and balsamic.
The saponins are  used in food and flavor
Practically odorless.
Mild, bland, slightly fatty odor of excellent tenacity.
Powerful and warm, spicy-condiment-like, sweet odor of good tenacity.
The anhydride has a much stronger odor  than the acid, and older samples of the acid may therefore smell stronger.
Warm, herbaceous-spicy and very tenacious odor, suggestive of Celery.
Faint, but tenacious warm-woody, spicy and slightly camphoraceous odor.
Mild, sweet-woody, slightly peppery odor of good tenacity.
Mild, woody, warm, herbaceous-peppery odor of excellent tenacity. Less peppery than alpha-Selinene, but warmer, more herbaceous
Virtually odorless when pure.
Mild, warm-herbaceous, sweet odor.
Very powerful and diffusive, also extremely tenacious odor, in high concentration repulsively unpleasant, only in very low concentration pleasant, sweet, warm, animal, with a note of overripe fruit.
The type of Skatolene showing an intensely warmanimal odor, tenacious, sweet and uniform, with no traces of fecal note, is generally a preferred one.
Odorless, but may have a faint acidulous odor in moist air.
Odorless.
Odorless.
Odorless.
Odorless.
Odorless.
Used in food products
Practically odorless
Practically odorless.
Odorless.
Pure Sorbic acid is practically odorless, but I commercial grade material may have a slight, peculiar odor, varying according to the method of synthesis used
Used in food products
Odorless.
Clean, sweet, powerfully herbaceous-green, refreshing odor of Spearmint type
Mild, pleasant, soft-oily odor, normally without any trace of rancid note. Excellent tenacity.
Pure material is virtually odorless
Sweet and pleasant, balsamic-floral, rather heavy odor of excellent tenacity
Extremely diffusive, sweet-gassy, in dilution balsamic and almost floral odor of poor tenacity.
Powerful, balsamic-gassy, heavy and sweet, warm odor. Much less gassy and not nearly as diffusive as Styrene.
Odorless.
Practically odorless.
Stinging, suffocating odor, irritating to the mucous membranes.
Refreshing citrusy, mainly lemony, odor of poor tenacity.
Very strictly purified material is practically odorless, while commercial grade material has a faint, peculiar woody-medicinal odor.
Odorless.
Refreshing, Iemony-citrusy odor of poor tenacity.
It has a refreshingly herbaceouscitrusy odor, not as lemony as the alphaisomer, but somewhat warmer, with equally poor tenacity.
Dry-woody, piney and somewhat musty odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm-peppery, mildly earthy, musty-woody odor of moderate tenacity. The earthy-musty notes are pleasantly green
The odor of high-grade alpha-Terpineol being delicately floral and sweet of Lilac type, it is very strongly influenced in presence of minute amounts of impurities of different odor type,
Pungent-woody-earthy, but not piney, odor of moderate tenacity.
Soft and pleasant, sweet, almost floral odor of moderate tenacity
Faint, balsamic-piney, camphoraceous, sweet odor. A highly refined, freshly prepared material has very little odor.

Sweet, slightly medicinal-camphoraceouspiney odor of moderate tenacity. The sweetness is related to an anisic type of sweetness, the medicinal notes almost cineolic, but not as light or volatile, rather subdued.
Sweet-piney, oily and relatively pleasant odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Not nearly as harsh as Pinene, often slightly anisic in its sweetness, and generally free from Turpentinelike notes.

Mildly herbaceous, sweet and refreshing odor of spicy Bergamot-Lavender type, with variations into piney notes according to quality of the ester. Overall much weaker than Linalyl acetate, but of slightly better tenacity.
Musty, heavy, but sweet and Neroli-floral, very tenacious odor.
Weak, but tenacious, woody-floral, warm odor with a musky undertone

This ester is occasionally used in perfume compositions as a modifier in Oriental, Fougbre, Rose, Lilac, Lily and other fragrance types, often in combination with the herbaceous oils: Sage, Spike Lavender, Rosemary, etc.
Fruity-floral-herbaceous, refreshing and moderately tenacious odor. More delicate and “clean” than the n-butyrate, not as harshherbaceous.
Mild, sweet, floral-balsamic and very tenacious odor, resembling Perubalsam or Tolubalsam, and terpeneless Nutmeg to a certain degree. The immediate impression is that of a weak odor.
Fresh, floral-citrusy, tart-herbaceous, semidry odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Relatively weak, but rather heavy, sweetfloral and very tenacious odor of Rose-Lilac- Honey complex, with the usual variations according to the purity of t},e ester
Sweet-herbaceous, mildly fruity -piney, refreshing odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet, herbaceous-piney, almost Ambrelike, Citrus-incense type odor of moderate tenacity.
Peculiar sweet-piney, floral-incense-like, citrusy odor of moderate tenacity. Less herbaceous, more floral-fruity than the n-valerate
Powerful, sweet-musky, mildly animal odor with considerable resemblance to the odor of Cyclopentadecanolide, and with excellent tenacity.
Sweet-woody, nut-like, earthy and mildly medicinal-leathery odor of considerable tenacity.
powerful, sweet-green, leafy, delicately creamy odor, in dilution floral, and tenacious.
Powerful, very sweet, fruity-floral and tenacious odor.
Penetrating, sweet-gassy and warm, breadlike odor. Unpleasant in its diffusive power and pungency. Very poor tenacity.
Mild, fruity, Acetone-ethereal odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Mild, warm, oily -caramellic odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Heavy, sweet-fruity odor of Apricot-Pineapple type, moderate tenacity
Mild, sweet and very tenacious, balsamicwiney, slightly spicy odor.
Warm, caramellic-herbaceous, mildly balsamic odor, in dilution almost floral in its balsam-notes. Moderate tenacity.
Mild and heavy-sweet, very tenacious Honey-Rose type odor with a Raspberryfruity undertone.
Caramellic-sweet, fruity and soft-oily odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet, oily, warm and remotely caramellicfloral odor of moderate to poor tenacity. In dilution also winey
The title material has an unquestionable CedarWood-like odor

Fruity-sweet, in dilution somewhat floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The fruity notes are much more pronounced in this ketone than in Dlhydrojasmone, and the floral notes not nearly as warm-herbaceous.
Mild, sweet-herbaceous and discretely floral odor of moderate to poor tenacity. The odor is suggestive of Lavender, Clary Sage, Bergamot, etc.
Sweet, fruity -herbaceous odor, suggestive of Lavender, Bergamot and Clary Sage, yet warmer and more herbaceous than Linalyl acetate.
Very sweet, heavy, fruity-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity. The fruity-herbaceous notes have some resemblance to Clary Sage, while the deep-sweet fruitiness is somewhat Pineapple-like.
Fresh and sweet, fruity-herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity. Fresher and more fruity than the n-Butyrate, but not as nat ural-herbaceous.
Sweet-oily, delicately floral odor, less greenwood than Linalool, more floral and powdery, sweet-dry odor
Dry-floral, mildly herbaceous, pleasant odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet and warm, oily-herbaceous odor with green-floral notes and moderate to poor tenacity.
Powerful, sweet-herbaceous, rather pungent and “unnatural” odor, unless diluted, when it becomes more pleasant, sweet-herbal.

Very powerful and tenacious, sweet-animal odor with Honey-like undertone. Floral notes are perceptible upon extreme dilution of the material, but the undiluted quinoline has a rather unpleasant, Civet-like odor.
Tetrahydromuguol is therefore not further discussed in this work, while the Acetate of this alcohol-mixture is described under its name “Tetrahydro mugyl acetate”.
Refreshing, citrusy-herbaceous, mildly floral odor of moderate tenacity
The title material supplies the fresh, citrusy, Lime-like and “lifting” portion of the fragrance picture of “Tetrahydromuguol”
Intensely sweet, tenacious, warm-floral, slightly woody odor.
Peculiar, dry-sweet, woody-camphoraceous, relatively tenacious odor with unquestionable Ambregris character
Camphoraceous-minty, sweet-woody odor of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and sweet, herbaceous-earthy, rather heavy odor with mildly green notes, and moderate tenacity.
Sweet-floral, balsamic odor of rosy-woody character and moderate tenacity.
~arm, soft, oily-herbaceous odor with a floral undertone and moderate to poor tenacity.
Rather rough or harsh-caramellic-Honeylike, sweet odor with discrete animal character. Not as pronounced animal as Tetrahydropara- methylquinoline.
Powerful, green-leafy odor, very diffusive and of poor tenacity.
Delicately herbaceous, sweet-green odor, reminiscent of fresh wood-sap or fresh, wet bark. Poor storage may cause a slight deterioration, resulting in a perceptible cresylic note in the odor.
Warm, caramellic-fruity, slightly spicy or Nut-like odor of considerable tenacity.
Musty-woody-camphoraceous, semi-sweet odor of considerable tenacity. The similarity to Ambregris is more apparent in composition use than in the material as such
Musty, mildly woody, and in dilution Ambregris-like odor of good tenacity.
Semi-sweet, woody Ambregris-like odor of good tenacity, Less musty but also less power powerful than the aldehyde (see previous monograph) and overall sweeter

Very powerful, diffusive and penetrating bumt-caramellic-sulfuraceous odor. It has been claimed that highly purified material has only very faintly perceptible sulfuraceous or “Garlic-like” notes, while the bumt-caramellic notes predominate.
The odor of absolutely pure Thioglycollic acid is mildly sour with a “heavy” or slightly nauseating pungency and poor tenacity.
Powerful and penetrating, in the undiluted form very unpleasant and sulfuraceous odor. In extreme dilution of quite pleasant, bumtsmokey, warm-caramellic odor of moderate tenacity.
Commercial grade material normally shows Garlic-like, diffusive rubber-like odor, according to the degree of dilution.
“Onion lachrymator”.
Practically odorless when pure, but may carry faint odor depending upon method of production.
Powerful and penetrating, warm-herbaceous,minty-camphoraceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
It has a powerful, minty-camphoraceous, Lime-like character of odor and moderate tenacity.
Dry-woody, herbaceous-spicy odor of con- siderable tenacity. The herbaceous-spicy notes resemble Anise and Fennel, but do not have the palatable sweetness or attractive aroma of these oils.

Heavy-sweet, warm-spicy, almost nut-like earthy odor of considerable tenacity. The resemblance to Fennel is not very apparent in the undiluted material, but becomes more conspicuous in compositions or in dilution.

Powerful, sweet-medicinal, herbaceous and warm odor of moderate tenacity. The odor is much more pleasant than that of Phenol (or Cresol) and not nearly as “dry-tarry” as that of Carvacrol (isomer of Thymol).

Theoretically, Carvacrol is also a liquid isomer of Thymol, but the odor of the commercial i$o-Thymol does not at all resemble that of Carvacrol. It is weaker, less tarry, more typical “phenolic’’-medicinal.

Warm-herbaceous, earthy-rooty, mildly spicy odor of moderate tenacity. Odor descriptions often include the word “Thymollike”, but the author finds that a highquality ether has no resemblance to Thymol in its odor, except the warm-spicy character.
Warm-spicy-rooty, herbaceous odor with practically no trace of medicinal or “phenolic” notes, but rather a dry-leafy character. Moderate tenacity.
Mild, warm-spicy, herbaceous odor of good tenacity. The odor has little similarity to that of Thymol, being absolutely “non-medicinal” and much milder than that of Thymol
Spicy-rooty, sweet-sour herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity.
Very diffusive, penetrating odor, unpleasantly pungent, irritating when undiluted, but quite pleasant, fruity-herbaceous in extreme dilution. Very poor tenacity.
Mild, but in high concentration nauseating, sweet-herbaceous, almost tobacco-like odor, in dilution very pleasant, warm and herbaceous, of good tenacity.
The title aromatic hydrocarbon is not a perfume or flavor material, but it is included in this work because it is used as a solvent for extraction of active ingredients in plant materials, etc.
Warm, spicy-haylike and very tenacious odor

Powerful and refreshing green-fruity, “forest- like”, sweet, floral odor of moderate tenacity. The undiluted material has a rather sharp initial odor, but sweetness predominates in the diluted product.
Powerful, fruity-medicinal odor, in dilution sweet, floral and more pleasant. Poor tenacity.
Sweet, floral-fruity and mildly green-herbaceous odor of moderate tenacity. Sweeter and less harsh than Benzylacetate, longer lasting and richer.
Mild, floral odor, overall rosy, but also musty, sweet and moderately tenacious. The odor is more floral than that of Phtnylethyl alcohol, but somewhat weaker
Faint, but very pleasant, green-rosy, leafy and sweet-balsamic odor of moderate tenacity.
Sweet-herbaceous, Bitter-almond-like moderately tenacious odor. Not as pungent as Benzaldehyde, but more herbaceous-warm.
Sweet and mild Benzaldehyde-t ype odor, less harsh, less penetrating and more tenacious than Benzaldehyde, but not as typical “almondy”.
Warm and sweet Benzaldehyde-type odor of moderate tenacity.
Warm and mildly floral, sweet-spicy odor of Benzaldehyde-type, but more floral and tenacious, less penetrating or harsh.
A very pure and freshly distilled material is practically odorless.
Most commercial samples have been relatively impure, and odors vary from very faint or mild, sweet Jasmin-like to pungent Orangeblossom- Grape-like, all with good tenacity.

Very faint, but persistent Ieafy-rosy-musty odor. Like many other high-boiling, weaksmelling powders, it is very susceptible to odor contamination from processing or storage, and will easily adapt odors from exposure to odorous atmosphere.
Sweet-green, powerful but natural odor, resembling the outer peel (rind) of Cantaloupe or Melon. Moderate tenacity.
Very sweet, fruity-floral odor of good tenacity. The fruity notes are of Raspberry-Plumlike character, while the discretely floral notes have resemblance to the Gardenia fragrance
Very faint, but very persistent sweet-balsamic, warm odor.
its odor is extremely weak
Sweet-fruity, soft, but very tenacious odor.
Very faint, ethereal-fruity odor, occasionally with acetic note
Very faint, sweet-herbaceous, winey-fruity odor.
Sweet, mildly fruity, buttery-creamy odor. Decomposed material shows dominating acidbutyric odor and loss of “creamy” aroma.
Odorless
Very faint, metallic-green, musty-floral odor of good tenacity
Mild, at first very weak, green-rosy, balsamic odor of excellent tenacity. The odor is much more perceptible when the material is in solution.
Very faint, sweet, green-balsamic, warm and very tenacious odor.
Very faint, dry-rosy, warm and tenacious odor.
used in flavoring
the title material is not used in flavors or perfumes as such
Peculiar earthy, mossy-musty odor, sweetcamphoraceous, warm and having some of the typical notes of Patchouli.
Soft, creamy, mildly coconutty and discretely musky odor (non-animal) of excelJent tenacity.
Pleasant and rich, musky odor, slightly weaker than that of Tetradecamethylene carboxyiate (see monograph), and less tenacious.

Powerful waxy, fresh-citrusy, Grapefruit Grapefruitpeel- like odor with slightly floral, petal-like waxy character and good tenacity. The dry freshness has some resemblance to notes in the Ambregris complex.
Very faint, waxy-woody odor. A highly purified material may be virtually odorless.
Very faint, waxy-woody and sweet-fruity odor of good tenacity.
Powerful, waxy-citrusy, peel-like odor of moderate tenacity. More citrusy than the odor of Tndecanal.
Mild, fatty-fruity odor of Peach-Apricot type with a Lily-floral note
Powerful oily -citrusy odor of moderate tenacity.
Very mild, but sweet and pleasant, winey - fruity, Plum-1ike odor.
Almost odorless, or having a faint, musty odor.
Intensely sweet, warm-herbaceous odor, suggestive of Labdanum and Oakmoss.
Powerful oily-fruity, heavy-floral, sweet odor of moderate tenacity.
Peculiar, pungent-warm, Nut-like and earthy odor of considerable tenacity.
Warm-herbaceous, powerfully “dark”- green or “bitter’’-green odor of moderate tenacity. The greenness resembles that of cut flower stalks, or freshly cut Chrysanthemums.
Powerful, sweet-woody, Orris-Violet-like odor, more woody than alpha-Ionone, but softer and more tenacious than the average type Methyl ionone.
Powerful, green-fruity, but overall sweet and moderately tenacious odor.
Powerful Menthol-like odor, but more camphoraceous, less cooling than Menthol.
Powerful and warm-herbaceous odor, suggestive of cured Tobacco leaves. Excellent tenacity.
Powerful and very diffusive, green-bark-like, woody and mildly pine-like odor of moderate tenacity. The odor has been described as “Pine-sap-like”.
Powerful and rather pungent, but in dilut ion pleasant, warm-herbaceous and mintycamphoraceous odor, reminiscent of Tansy oil or Dalmatian Sage oil.
Soft-woody, sweet, balsamic-floral, tenacious odor. Products from different suppliers show considerable difference in odor characterist its.
Mild, sweet-minty, herbaceous odor of moderate to good tenacity
Warm-woody, sweet and tenacious odor of considerable resemblance to the Ionone type odors
Very diffusive, ethereal, pungent or nauseating odor, pleasant in dilution, slightly wineyfruity, Brandy-like.
Very powerful and di,~usive, dry-green, gassy odor, in extreme diiutian refreshingly vegetable-green (“aldehydic”), yet dry and slightly woody, of moderate to poor tenacity.
Relatively powerful, oily -herbaceous, in dilution sweet odor, but not nearly as floral as n-Nonylalcohol.
Woody-fruity, soft, refreshing odor of mild Orris-type, more fruity and discretely green, with moderate tenacity.

Sweet-woody, slightly oily and discretely piney odor of moderate tenacity. The resemblance to Sandalwood is not striking, but the effect in compositions suggests that the material can be used as a Sandalwood type fragrance chemical.
Powerful, oily-musty odor, suggestive of Leather and Oakmoss, in dilution more refreshing, remotely Ambre-like.
Sweet-balsamic, powdery, moderately tenacious odor of delicately woody character.
Warm, slightly musty, dry-sweet Sandalwood- like odor with an Ambregris note and excellent tenacity
Intensely sweet, floral-balsamic and tenacious odor.
Very powerful and very tenacious, sweetfloral, waxy-rosy odor, sometimes referred to as “ozone-like”
Pleasant, refreshing, floral-citrusy, rosyaldehydic and slightly oily-fatty odor of moderate to good tenacity.
The undiluted material has a sharp, almost irritating, but fresh-camphoraceous-cineolic odor, which becomes sweet, warm, herbaceous and pleasant upon dilution (near 1 %).
Sweet, but rather coarse, musky odor of good tenacity.
imperfect and unconfirmed data
the title material can not be classified as the principle of Tuberose fragrance yet.
Sweet-herbaceous, warm odor, very much resembling the odor of Coumarin, but not nearly as strong. Very tenacious.
Pungent and irritating, but in dilution rather pleasant, minty-Tansy-like, resinous- balsamic odor of moderate to poor tenacity.
Very powerful oily-caramellic, “bakedspicy” odor with citrusy undertones.
Powerful, sweet-creamy, warm odor with a Coconut-oily note in extreme dilution. The undiluted material has a rather repulsive, medicinal-sweet odor, similar to that of Diacetyl, although much weaker.
not described
Powerful, creamy-fatty and in dilution pronounced Peach-like odor of excellent tenacity.
