Musky, but not altogether sweet odor, faintly woody-camphoraceous notes of considerable tenacity.
Powerful and sweet, very tenacious musky odor with little or no trace of animal note.
Pleasant waxy-floral, refreshing odor with a discrete fruity overtone and moderate tenacity
Soft, oily-citrusy odor of moderate to good tenacity.
Fresh, oily-floral, citrusy odor with mildly herbaceous-green notes and moderate tenacity.
Oily-fruity, floral-citrusy odor, slightly fatty, but overall fresh and delicately rosy, in high dilution Mandarin-like.
Powerful, gassy-green and very diffusive, but in dilution pleasantly oily-herbaceous, vegetable-green, warm odor of moderate to poor tenacity.

Powerful, in dilution very refreshing, sweetcitrusy, Orange-peel like odor, diffusive and yet quite tenacious. The undiluted material is rather overwhelming in its odor intensity, difficult to appreciate.
The author suspects a confusion with 2-Undecen-l-al,
Powerful, mildly waxy, rosy-citrusy odor of moderate to good tenacity. The odor could be classified as one of the prototypes of the term: “aldehydic” odor.
Very powerful and diffusive, refreshingly citrusy-waxy, in extreme dilution dry-floral, “clean” odor.
Very soft, oily -citrusy, and in extreme dilution mildly citrusy-fruity, and Brandy-like, sweet odor.
Very powerful, sweet-oily, in dilution floral, rosy, softly waxy odor of moderate tenacity.
Fresh, but rather fatty odor (variable amount of fatty notes in different grades of this alcohol) with citrusy-waxy and rosy, petal-like notes.
no described odor
Mildly fruity, fatty-floral, Honey-Rose type odor of good tenacity. Variations in this odor picture are observed in products from different suppliers.
Relatively powerful, oily-fruity, rather heavy odor of considerable tenacity. The fruity notes tend to appear winey, Plum-1ike, depending upon the concentration.

Peculiar, dry-sweet, very rich, unripe-fruity odor of good tenacity. The author has been unable to undersign odor descriptions including terms such as “fermented Honey”, “acetous odor”, “sharp”, etc. but it is quite conceivable that such notes may appear in decomposed ester.

Very faint, oily-winey odor of considerable tenacity. Upon intense study, one may ob-serve a delicate greenness which is much more perceptible once the material is composed with more volatile materials,
Very faint, but very tenacious, sweet, fruitymusky odor.

Oily-fruity, mildly winey-fruity and very tenacious odor. The overall impression is that of a fruity, more than a floral type, although in suitable composition, the material is very compatible with Rose notes.
Mild, oily-ethereal, soft-fatty, rosy odor of considerable tenacity.
Sweet, fatty-musky odor with variable amounts of fruity or Coconut-type oily-fatty, but pleasant notes of very considerable tenacity.
The odor varies enormously in different grades of the acid, from oily, mildly acid and heavy-fruity, overall pleasant, to acrid-acrid, repulsively sour-fatty.
Dry-oily, mildly herbal or discretely green odor, reminiscent of certain dried herbs, without being “aromatic”.

Very weak, fatty-aldehydic odor with considerable variations according to originVery weak, fatty-aldehydic odor with considerable variations according to origin. A high-grade material has practically no odor, while a normal commercial grade smells oily-fatty in a mild, sweet and not unpleasant manner, and with good tenacity.
Very powerful and diffusive, penetrating, acrid-pungent odor, in the concentrated form repulsively choking, cough-provoking. In extreme dilution dry-fruity, musty, Nut-like.
Very powerful, penetrating, acrid-pungent odor, causing cough-reflexes unless highly diluted.
Warm-spicy, ethereal-herbaceous odor with resemblance to Celery
Heavy, herbaceous-earthy, but overall sweet and tenacious odor. Samples of different origin have shown considerable difference in odor characteristics.

Very powerful and penetrating, diffusive, acid odor, pungent when undiluted, but more unpleasant when diluted. In fact it becomes more animal- and perspiration-like in dilution. Only in extreme dilution the odor becomes again more pleasant, fruit y, warm.

Very diffusive, acid-acrid, in moderate dilution cheesy, unpleasant odor of poor tenacity - although the difficulty in removing minute traces from the human skin, and the power of the odor, give impression of considerable tenacity. In extreme dilution the odor becomes more agreeable, herbaceous, more dry than the odor of the n-Valerie acid.
Its odor is very pungent, acrid, oflensive, dry-sour
Warm, sweet, Hay- and Tobacco-like, herbaceous odor of moderate to poor tenacity
Fresh-fruity, also sweet and discretely floral odor of moderate tenacity.
Fresh-fruity, sweet and moderately tenacious odor. The fruity notes are fresher, less floral than those of the n-Valerophenone.
Although it has a very strong and acceptable musk odor, its production cost does not warrant any further encouragement to use this musk.
The odor is heavy-pungent, warm, spicy, rather unpleasant in the pure state, but becomes very attractive, agreeable at lower concentrations, clearly resembling the odor of Celery.
Warm-herbaceous, spicy and very tenacious odor, in extreme dilution resembling Celery, but in the concen-trated form rather unpleasant, pungent ‘burnt"
The pure material is virtually odorless, and has only a mild, warm, breadlike taste, varying from slightly unpleasant (towards stale bread) to quite agreeable.
Virtually odorless when pure.
Intensely sweet and very tenacious creamy- Vanilla-like odor
Practically odorless when cold; mild, floralherbaceous or Hay-like at room temperature, and very sweet, balsamic-Vanilla-like when heated above 60° C.
it has an unquestionable odor of Vanillin-type, rather soft, but quite pleasant and not exactly weak, its aqueous solution or the dry material itself has hardly any taste at all.
Intensely sweet, balsamic-floral odor of very good tenacity.
Pratt ically odorless
Mild, sweet-balsamic, delicately floral odor  of good tenacity. The odor has only little in common with the Vanilla-odor, and it does not have the deep warmth of Vaniliin
Ve@ mild, sweet, balsamic-VaniIla-like odor of moderate tenacity.
Very sweet, warm and tenacious odor of balsamic-creamy Vanillatype, although more spicy, less delicate than Vanillin.
Very faint, sweet-floral, cate odor of good tenacity
Warm and sweet, Vanilla-1ike odor, stronger than Vanillin, but weaker than “Ethyl vanillin”.
Very sweet, woody-Vanilla-like or Heliotrope Heliotrope- like odor of excellent tenacity. Some observers find a haylike or Coumarin-like note in this material.
Sweet-creamy, rather pungent odor which upon dilution becomes very Vanilla-like.
It is normal to find a soft, warm-resinous,  slightly spicy odor of moderate tenacity, while minty-camphoraceous notes should not be dominating.
Sweet, distinctly musky, and soft-creamy odor of good tenacity.

The odor of this product varies considerably according to origin, quality, age, etc. A warm, sweet, mildly earthy-balsamic and extremely tenacious odor is common and generally desirable, Sharp, green or pronounced “root-like” notes are generally undesirable.
Sweet-and-dry, fresh-woody and exceptionally tenacious odor. Poorer grades display conspicuous notes of Vetiver oil

Fresh, yet sweet-floral, delicately fruity-oily or mildly waxy odor of outstanding tenacity. The woody notes are hardly perceptible, while the floral notes are more predominant, the fruity less so than in the Acetate.
Delicately sweet-floral, semi-dry odor with peculiar musky-animal note and outstanding tenacity.
Delicate, dry-sweet, powdery odor of excellent tenacity. Poorly stored material often show sharp or pungent (formic) notes.
Musty-sweet, mildly fruity and discretel> woody-rosy odor of outstanding tenacit>. Considerable variations are observed in materials of different origin.
Very tenacious powdery-fruity, mildly woody odor.

Delicately herbaceous-fruity, musty-woody, dry-and-sweet, very tenacious odor. Variations in this odor are observed when studying samples of different origin. It is quite possible that the iso-Valerate has a more fruity odor and the n-Valerate a more musty-animal, or almost musky odor

alpha-Vetivone has a powerful, warm, pleasant, Orris-Vetiver-Ambre-like odor of outstanding tenacity. It is generally considered the most desirable odor of the two. Unfortunately, it appears to be the minor component of the total ketones in Vetiver oil. beta-Vetivone has a more balsamic-floral, sweet, but very mild or relatively weak odor, although also of excellent tenacity. It is the major ketonic component of Vetiver oil.
Fruity-ethereal, rather sharp, but sweet odor of considerable diffusive power and very poor tenacity.
Pungent, warm-spicy, but also moderately medicinal-woody odor of considerable tenacity
Sweet-ethereal odor of poor tenacity.
Very diffusive, nauseating-ethereal, but sweet odor of poor tenacity. The odor carries some similarity to that of Ethyl ether (Ether).
Balsamic-woody odor of deep sweetness, but much less spicy than 4-Viny lguaiacol. Moderate tenacity.

Diffusive, penetrating and rather unpleasant odor, in dilution appearing fresh-green with distinct Onion-notes. Solutions in Diethylphthalate of concentration less than 10. have a fresher odor, the “Onion” character being almost imperceptible.
Pungent, “gassy”, kerosene-like odor, but not nearly as powerful as that of Toluene, not as nauseating as Benzene. Overall sweeter and milder than the two.
Heavy, sweet odor of Bitter-Almond-type, but not nearly as pungent as Benzaldehyde, yet not as soft as Tolylaldehyde.
may be encountered in perfumery as an odor problem to overcome
Sweet, mildly floral odor with Bitter- Almond type note.
Mild, sweet-floral, soft-balsamic odor, fresh-er than Phenylpropylalcohol (Hydrocinnamic alcohol), but less rosy and less balsamic.
Sweet-spicy, warm, heavy-floral, mildly animal-balsamic and Vanilla-like odor with excellent tenacity.
Freshly prepared material has a warm, woody-spicy and very tenacious odor with a peculiar deep sweetness,
